        THIS_IS_MY_WIFE_SWANTJE_OF_WHOM_I                                     = 7639,  -- This is my wife Swantje, of whom I spoke. And this, my dear, is the industrious young man/woman] who has brought the gems that will make me--<ahem!>, I mean us--rich beyond our wildest dreams!
        SO_HOP_TO_IT_HONEY_WORK_YOUR_MAGIC                                    = 7640,  -- So hop to it, honey. Work your magic on these beauties!
        WAHID_MUST_YOU_TRULY_GO_ON_WITH_THIS                                  = 7641,  -- Wahid... Must you truly go on with this?
        EVEN_THE_MOST_PRECIOUS_GEM_THAT_NEVER_LEAVES                          = 7642,  -- Even the most precious gem that never leaves its jewel casket is naught but a lonely rock.
        BASTOK_IS_AT_WAR_OR_HAVEN_T_YOU                                       = 7643,  -- Bastok is at war...or haven't you noticed? In these hard times, it is all folk like us can do to get through each day with food on our tables and our loved ones' lives intact. Still you look only to profit off the sale of these luxuries?
        AHAHAHA_BWAHAHAHA_COUGH_HACK_PLEASE_STOP_MY_DEAR                      = 7644,  -- Ahahaha! Bwahahaha--<cough, hack>. Please stop, my dear, lest I bust a gut from laughter!
        TIS_PRECISELY_BECAUSE_OUR_LIVES_MAY_END_AT                            = 7645,  -- 'Tis precisely because our lives may end at any moment that I choose to make the most of the time I have. If some vainglorious goodwife is willing to lighten her purse to that end, who am I to stand in the way? Would you deny me that?
        BUT_WAHID_IS_THERE_NOT_A_GREATER_GOOD                                 = 7646,  -- But Wahid...is there not a greater good we could be serving?
        A_TRUER_CAUSE_THAT_CALLS_FOR_OUR_AID                                  = 7647,  -- A truer cause that calls for our aid?
        IN_THESE_TRYING_TIMES_IT_IS_NOT_LAVISH                                = 7648,  -- In these trying times, it is not lavish baubles that renew people's spirits, but hopes and dreams of a brighter future!
        HERE_IS_WHAT_I_PROPOSE_FORGET_PRECIOUS_GEMS                           = 7649,  -- Here is what I propose. Forget precious gems. We can fashion a new line of goods to sell at a more modest price.
        WHAT_IF_YOU_COULD_FIND_YES_THE_MYSTIC                                 = 7650,  -- What if you could find...yes, the mystic stones spoken of in the old legends. I could fashion them into good-luck charms. Anything to give the fearful townsfolk a dose of hope and courage.
        MYSTIC_STONES_GOOD_LUCK_CHARMS_BWAHAHAHAHAHAHA                        = 7651,  -- Mystic stones? Good-luck charms? Bwahahahahahaha!
        YOU_RE_QUITE_THE_JOKESTER_TODAY_MY_DEAR                               = 7652,  -- You're quite the jokester today, my dear! Even if such things existed--which I doubt they do--why should I break my back hunting down pebbles that would bring but a pittance in return?
        YOU_MAY_HAVE_TALENT_BUT_LET_US_NOT                                    = 7653,  -- You may have talent, but let us not forget that it's me and my prodigious gem acquisition skills that put the food on our table.
        HOPES_DREAMS_COURAGE_P_SHAW_I_M_A                                     = 7654,  -- Hopes? Dreams? Courage? P'shaw! I'm a businessman--a successful one at that--and I intend to stay that way.
        IF_THE_MUSHY_SENTIMENTS_OF_THE_RABBLE_ARE                             = 7655,  -- If the mushy sentiments of the rabble are of such concern to you, maybe you should go find your precious "mystic stones" yourself!
        THERE_SHE_GOES_AGAIN_OH_WELL_CAN_T                                    = 7656,  -- There she goes again. Oh well, can't say I didn't try to talk some sense into her.
        I_M_AFRAID_WE_LL_HAVE_TO_PUT                                          = 7657,  -- I'm afraid we'll have to put our little transaction on hold.
        SHE_S_A_WILLFUL_ONE_BUT_WITHOUT_HER                                   = 7658,  -- She's a willful one, but without her skills, those stones won't sell for a tenth of what I offered you.
        BUT_WORRY_NOT_FRIEND_SHE_LL_COME_AROUND                               = 7659,  -- But worry not, friend! She'll come around, as she always does. My infallible merchant's instincts tell me so.
        IT_WON_T_BE_LONG_BEFORE_WE_RE                                         = 7660,  -- It won't be long before we're all rolling in gil. Ahahaha! Bwahahahahahaha--<cough, hack>.
        OH_HO_THERE_YOU_ARE_SORRY_YOU_HAD                                     = 7661,  -- Oh ho! There you are! Sorry you had to witness our little lovers' spat the other day. Hohoho...
        ACTUALLY_SPEAKING_OF_MY_WIFE_YOU_HAVEN_T                              = 7662,  -- Actually, speaking of my wife... You haven't perchance seen her around, have you?
        IT_PAINS_ME_TO_SAY_THIS_BUT_SHE                                       = 7663,  -- It pains me to say this, but she hasn't been back home since that day.
        WHEREVER_COULD_SHE_HAVE_RUN_OFF_TO                                    = 7664,  -- Wherever could she have run off to?
        I_DON_T_MEAN_TO_TURN_YOU_INTO                                         = 7665,  -- I don't mean to turn you into my errand boy/girl], but perhaps you could take a look around for her?
        IT_APPEARS_MY_INFALLIBLE_MERCHANT_S_INSTINCTS_AREN                    = 7666,  -- It appears my infallible merchant's instincts aren't quite what they used to be. Ahahaha!
        PLEASE_DO_LET_ME_KNOW_IF_YOU_FIND                                     = 7667,  -- Please do let me know if you find any word of my wife. Hahaha, what's gotten into me? A businessman like me should have nerves of darksteel...
        OH_IT_S_YOU_PRAY_TELL_HAVE_YOU                                        = 7668,  -- Oh, it's you. Pray tell, have you any news of Swantje?
        BREAK_THE_NEWS_TO_WAHID_YES_NOT_YET                                   = 7669,  -- Break the news to Wahid? Yes. Not yet.
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_SAY_YOU_EXPECT_ME                                     = 7670,  -- What's that you say!? You expect me to believe such nonsense?
        AFTER_ALL_IT_S_NOT_AS_IF_YOU                                          = 7671,  -- After all, it's not as if you have any proof, correct? No, a shrewd businessman trusts no eyes but his own!
        AH_TIS_A_SHAME                                                        = 7672,  -- Ah...'tis a shame.
        SHOULD_YOU_UNCOVER_ANY_WORD_OF_SWANTJE_ANYTHING                       = 7673,  -- Should you uncover any word of Swantje--anything at all!--come back at once. I beg of you!
        AH_I_VE_BEEN_WAITING_FOR_YOU_HAVE                                     = 7674,  -- Ah, I've been waiting for you! Have a look at this letter. I found it as I was searching my house just a moment ago.
        HERE_YOU_CAN_READ_IT_ALONG_WITH_ME                                    = 7675,  -- Here, you can read it along with me. Perhaps it might offer us a clue as to Swantje's whereabouts.
        MY_DEAREST_HUSBAND_FORGIVE_ME_FOR_RUNNING_OFF                         = 7677,  -- @@My dearest husband, @@ @@Forgive me for running off in a huff like that...sometimes I allow my emotions to get the better of me. @@
        I_IMAGINE_YOU_RE_ASKING_YOURSELF_WHERE_I                              = 7678,  -- @@I imagine you're asking yourself where I came up with that far-fetched notion of mystic stones. @@
        I_MEANT_NOT_TO_ANGER_YOU_STILL_I                                      = 7679,  -- @@I meant not to anger you. @@Still, I fear that if I were to say this face-to-face, I would succeed only in incurring your ire once more. @@And so, I put ink to parchment. @@
        DO_YOU_REMEMBER_THE_RING_YOU_GAVE_ME                                  = 7680,  -- @@Do you remember the ring you gave me on our wedding day? @@
        SO_UNIQUE_SO_LOVELY_IT_PIQUED_MY_CURIOSITY                            = 7681,  -- @@So unique, so lovely...it piqued my curiosity from the start. @@Recently I learned that it was one of the early works of a highly celebrated goldsmith. @@
        THE_STORY_HAS_IT_THAT_THIS_GOLDSMITH_INTENDED                         = 7682,  -- @@The story has it that this goldsmith intended to set the ring with one of the stones of legend. @@Though they do not shine as bright as diamonds--nor any other precious gem--it is said that they @@would bring lifelong happiness to any couple.
        DID_YOU_KNOW_EVER_THE_BUSINESSMAN_YOU_WERE                            = 7683,  -- @@Did you know? @@Ever the businessman, you were doubtless more concerned with its glitter than its history... @@
        STILL_IN_THESE_DARK_TIMES_I_THOUGHT_WE                                = 7684,  -- @@Still, in these dark times...I thought we could work together to provide that same hope and @@happiness to the disheartened populace. @@I wanted this with all my heart. @@
        CALL_ME_A_SENTIMENTAL_LITTLE_GIRL_BUT_THIS                            = 7685,  -- @@Call me a sentimental little girl, but this is why I sought your aid in finding the stones. @@And why I now go in search of them...on my own... @@
        I_KNOW_YOU_ARE_STILL_ANGRY_AT_ME                                      = 7686,  -- @@I know you are still angry at me. But I promise you... @@I will find the stone and fashion the most beautiful ring the three nations have ever seen. @@That day, I hope you can forgive me. @@
        YOURS_SWANTJE                                                         = 7687,  -- @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@Yours, @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@Swantje @@
        WHAT_IS_THAT_WOMAN_THINKING_SHE_S_ALWAYS                              = 7688,  -- What is that woman thinking!? She's always been pigheaded, but to think she was actually serious about going on that wild crystal chase! And alone, to boot!
        HMMM_WHAT_WAS_THAT_LOOK_ON_YOUR_FACE                                  = 7689,  -- Hmmm? What was that look on your face just now? Is there something you're not telling me?
        SHOW_WAHID_THE_YES_NOT_YET                                            = 7690,  -- Show Wahid the %? Yes. Not yet.
        YOU_CAN_T_PULL_ONE_OVER_ON_OLD                                        = 7691,  -- You can't pull one over on old Wahid. There's something you're not telling me. Now, out with it!
        WHY_THIS_THIS_IS_THE_WEDDING_RING_I                                   = 7692,  -- Why, this...this is the wedding ring I gave Swantje!
        WHAT_WERE_YOU_DOING_WITH_IT                                           = 7693,  -- What were you doing with it?
        WHERE_DID_YOU_FIND_THIS_I_SAY                                         = 7694,  -- Where did you find this, I say!?
        YOU_RE_HIDING_SOMETHING_FROM_ME_I_KNOW                                = 7695,  -- You're hiding something from me, I know it! Out with it before I lose my patience!
        NO_IT_CAN_T_D_DAMN_YOU_YOU                                            = 7696,  -- No...it can't... D-damn you! You're...you're trying to trick me... You--
        YOU_ARE_THE_JEWELER_WAHID_CORRECT                                     = 7697,  -- You are the jeweler Wahid, correct?
        I_AM_AFRAID_I_BRING_SOMBER_NEWS_OUR                                   = 7698,  -- I am afraid I bring somber news. Our border patrol has reported a citizen slain in the vicinity of the Palborough Mines.
        THE_VICTIM_HAS_BEEN_CONFIRMED_AS_YOUR_WIFE                            = 7699,  -- The victim has been confirmed as your wife, Swantje.
        IT_APPEARS_SHE_WAS_TARGETED_BY_A_BAND                                 = 7700,  -- It appears she was targeted by a band of Quadav raiders.
        NO_IT_CAN_T_BE_TRUE_OH_GODDESS                                        = 7701,  -- No...it can't be true... Oh, Goddess! Why do you forsake me so? How could you lead her into harm's way! M-my...my Swantje...<sob>
        ID_7702                                                               = 7702,  -- ...
        YOUR_WIFE_WAS_HOLDING_THIS_IN_HER_HAND                                = 7703,  -- Your wife was holding this in her hand. I know your grief is still fresh, but take it. It is yours.
        COULD_IT_BE                                                           = 7704,  -- Could it be...? %!
        BACK_IN_THE_DAYS_WHEN_I_WAS_BUT                                       = 7705,  -- Back in the days when I was but a fledgling shop owner, without the resources to procure precious gems, Swantje would bring these home, and polish them until they sparkled like the starlit night sky...
        AT_THE_TIME_I_THOUGHT_THEM_LITTLE_MORE                                = 7706,  -- At the time, I thought them little more than pebbles...
        AH_TO_RETURN_TO_THOSE_DAYS_OUR_STORE                                  = 7707,  -- Ah, to return to those days! Our store was but a shack, these stones bringing in barely enough coin to afford the ramshackle roof over our heads...
        AND_YET_OUR_TRAVAILS_BROUGHT_US_CLOSER_THAN                           = 7708,  -- And yet, our travails brought us closer than we had ever been before...or have been since. Looking back...those were probably the happiest years of our lives.
        SWANTJE                                                               = 7709,  -- Swantje...
        YOUR_WIFE_S_REMAINS_ARE_BEING_HELD_IN                                 = 7710,  -- Your wife's remains are being held in the military morgue, should you wish to pay your last respects.
        OH_IT_S_YOU_AGAIN_PLEASE_FORGIVE_ME                                   = 7711,  -- Oh...it's you again. Please forgive me for the other day...the grief was too much to bear.
        SINCE_THAT_DAY_THIS_HAS_NEVER_LEFT_MY                                 = 7712,  -- Since that day, this % has never left my hand. It's worth no more than a pebble, and isn't even much to look at. But I shall cherish it more than the most precious diamond.
        I_VE_DECIDED_TO_TAKE_IT_UPON_MYSELF                                   = 7713,  -- I've decided to take it upon myself to realize Swantje's unfulfilled dream. I shall collect stones like the one she gave her life to find, and do what I can to bring hope and good fortune to the people.
        SUCH_IS_THE_LEAST_I_CAN_DO_TO                                         = 7714,  -- Such is the least I can do to honor her memory. And when the day comes that I leave this world to rejoin her side, I can only hope she will forgive me...
        THIS_WAS_ONE_OF_HER_MOST_BELOVED_TOOLS                                = 7715,  -- This % was one of her most beloved tools.
        PLEASE_TAKE_IT_YOU_RE_FAR_MORE_OF                                     = 7716,  -- Please take it. You're far more of a goldsmith than I. Perhaps someday, when you become a master, you can fashion Swantje's stone into a ring worthy of her memory.
        A_HUNT_REGISTRY_HAS_BEEN_PLACED_HERE_BY                               = 7717,  -- A hunt registry has been placed here by the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network (A.M.A.N.). Its pages are laden with the names of spine-chilling monsters.
        A_HUNT_REGISTRY_HAS_BEEN_PLACED_HERE_BY_2                             = 7718,  -- A hunt registry has been placed here by the Servicemen's Mutual Aid Network (S.M.A.N.). Its pages are laden with the names of spine-chilling monsters.
