        A_FINE_NAME_INDEED                                                    = 11899,  -- %... A fine name, indeed.
        VERY_WELL_THE_CLIENT_IS_EXPECTING_YOU_AT                              = 11900,  -- Very well, %. The client is expecting you at the waterfall in North Gustaberg. Do not keep him waiting.
        THE_CLIENT_IS_EXPECTING_YOU_AT_THE_WATERFALL                          = 11901,  -- The client is expecting you at the waterfall in North Gustaberg. Do not keep him waiting.
        THE_PEOPLE_OF_BASTOK_LIVE_UNDER_A_CLOUD                               = 11902,  -- The people of Bastok live under a cloud of uncertainty. It's times like this that music can lift the weary spirit, don't you agree?
        YOU_HAVE_MET_WITH_SENATOR_WERNER_THEN_YOU                             = 11903,  -- You have met with Senator Werner? Then you have your instructions: bring the % here to me.
        YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_THE_EXCELLENT_THE_SENATOR_WILL                       = 11904,  -- You have brought the %? Excellent, the senator will be pleased.
        DID_YOU_EXPERIENCE_ANY_TROUBLE                                        = 11905,  -- Did you experience any trouble?
        SENATOR_WERNER_WAS_TRAILED_BY_ONE_OF_CHAIRMAN                         = 11906,  -- Senator Werner was trailed by one of Chairman Pale Eagle's spies?
        THE_CHAIRMAN_IS_A_SENIOR_MEMBER_OF_THE                                = 11907,  -- The chairman is a senior member of the Republican government, appointed to his position by President Prien himself...
        HE_OFTEN_CLASHES_WITH_SENATOR_WERNER_IN_MATTERS                       = 11908,  -- He often clashes with Senator Werner in matters of military policy.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_SCHEMES_THE_CHAIRMAN                                = 11909,  -- I don't know what schemes the chairman has in motion, but you would do well to keep an eye out.
        OH_AND_THERE_S_ONE_MORE_THING_I                                       = 11910,  -- Oh, and there's one more thing I meant to ask.
        YOU_RE_NOT_THE_AGENT_I_WAS_EXPECTING                                  = 11911,  -- You're not the agent I was expecting, are you?
        I_WAS_TOLD_TO_WELCOME_THE_ONE_WHO                                     = 11912,  -- I was told to welcome the one who brought me %.
        IT_WASN_T_UNTIL_LATER_THAT_I_DISCOVERED                               = 11913,  -- It wasn't until later that I discovered the real agent had collapsed at the gates to the city.
        IF_THE_SENATOR_SHOULD_REALIZE_I_VE_INTRODUCED                         = 11914,  -- If the senator should realize I've introduced him to the wrong operative...!
        OH_AND_IT_S_NOT_JUST_MY_NECK                                          = 11915,  -- Oh, and it's not just my neck that's on the line--the senator is a very thorough man.
        YOU_MUST_CONTINUE_TO_ACCEPT_SENATOR_WERNER_S                          = 11916,  -- You must continue to accept Senator Werner's tasks as if nothing were amiss. Your continued well-being, not to mention mine, depends on it.
        A_CHANCE_MEETING_HAS_LANDED_YOU_RIGHT_IN                              = 11917,  -- A chance meeting has landed you right in the thick of things, my friend. I have a feeling we'll be getting to know each other very well indeed.
        AH_I_HAVE_YOUR_REMUNERATION_JEUNO_CURRENCY_UNTRACEABLE                = 11918,  -- Ah, I have your remuneration. Jeuno currency. Untraceable.
        IS_PRESSED_INTO_S_HAND                                                = 11919,  -- % is pressed into %'s hand!
        I_M_GLAD_YOU_VE_RETURNED_THE_SENATOR                                  = 11920,  -- I'm glad you've returned. The senator has set us a new task.
        YOU_WILL_ACCEPT_WON_T_YOU                                             = 11921,  -- You will accept, won't you?
        ACCEPT_THE_TASK_IT_SEEMS_I_HAVE_LITTLE                                = 11922,  -- Accept the task? It seems I have little choice... I won't be threatened!
        THE_SENATOR_DOESN_T_MAKE_THREATS_HE_ONLY                              = 11923,  -- The senator doesn't make threats--he only makes promises.
        A_WISE_DECISION_HERE_S_THE_SITUATION                                  = 11924,  -- A wise decision. Here's the situation.
        WE_RE_SEEING_SOME_UNREST_IN_A_SECTION                                 = 11925,  -- We're seeing some unrest in a section of the Galkan population... No, let's be perfectly clear: they are planning an uprising.
        THE_MASTERMIND_BEHIND_THIS_REVOLUTION_APPEARS_TO_BE                   = 11926,  -- The mastermind behind this revolution appears to be none other than Chairman Pale Eagle.
        AS_YOU_MIGHT_BE_AWARE_PRESIDENT_PRIEN_WAS                             = 11927,  -- As you might be aware, President Prien was elected on the strength of his campaign promises--improvements to living conditions and education for all.
        BUT_WITH_THE_OUTBREAK_OF_WAR_THESE_IMPROVEMENTS                       = 11928,  -- But with the outbreak of war, these improvements have failed to materialize, and the Galka who supported Prien's campaign have grown disillusioned and angry.
        UNDER_COVER_OF_THE_CHAOS_SOWN_BY_THE                                  = 11929,  -- Under cover of the chaos sown by the Beastman Confederate, the ambitious chairman is attempting to capitalize on the dissatisfaction of the Galkan citizens to seize power for himself.
        DURING_HIS_MILITARY_DAYS_THE_CHAIRMAN_WAS_KNOWN                       = 11930,  -- During his military days, the chairman was known as the Eagle of Grauberg. If the soldiers still loyal to this former general join in the coup, the ensuing civil war will tear Bastok asunder!
        THANKFULLY_SENATOR_WERNER_IS_ONE_STEP_AHEAD_OF                        = 11931,  -- Thankfully, Senator Werner is one step ahead of his rival...
        YOUR_TASK_WILL_BE_TO_CONFIRM_CERTAIN_INFORMATION                      = 11932,  -- Your task will be to confirm certain information that will defuse this civil war before it even begins.
        CHAIRMAN_PALE_EAGLE_HAS_HAD_DEALINGS_WITH_THE                         = 11933,  -- Chairman Pale Eagle has had dealings with the Galkan elder Werei and his friend Gumbah.
        THERE_ARE_RUMORS_THAT_THESE_TWO_ARE_HOARDING                          = 11934,  -- There are rumors that these two are hoarding a stockpile of weapons in preparation for the coming uprising.
        OUR_SOURCES_ALSO_TELL_US_THAT_THIS_WEREI                              = 11935,  -- Our sources also tell us that this Werei is teaching swordplay to the youngster Pagdako. Does he mean to arm even the children in this madness...?
        FIND_THESE_GALKA_AND_LEARN_THE_TRUTH_BEHIND                           = 11936,  -- Find these Galka, and learn the truth behind their motives.
        THERE_ARE_RUMORS_THAT_THE_GALKAN_ELDER_WEREI                          = 11937,  -- There are rumors that the Galkan elder Werei and his friend Gumbah are hoarding a stockpile of weapons. Go, and discover the truth behind their motives.
        YOU_WANT_TO_MEET_WITH_WEREI_AND_GUMBAH                                = 11938,  -- You want to meet with Werei and Gumbah? What for?
        SO_YOU_VE_COME_TO_INVESTIGATE_THE_TROUBLEMAKERS                       = 11939,  -- So, you've come to investigate the troublemakers as well, have you?
        NO_NEED_TO_ANSWER_IT_S_WRITTEN_PLAIN                                  = 11940,  -- No need to answer. It's written plain on your face.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHO_PUT_YOU_UP                                           = 11941,  -- I don't know who put you up to this, but we have no interest in igniting a civil war.
        I_WON_T_TRY_TO_CONVINCE_YOU_THAT                                      = 11942,  -- I won't try to convince you that more than a few Galka aren't unhappy with the president's rule.
        THAT_S_WHY_WEREI_IS_MAKING_THE_ROUNDS                                 = 11943,  -- That's why Werei is making the rounds, trying to calm the rising anger.
        THIS_CONVERSATION_IS_OVER_DON_T_NEGLECT_YOUR                          = 11944,  -- This conversation is over. Don't neglect your sword practice, Pagdako. The road to becoming a Mythril Musketeer is a long one.
        ELDER_WEREI_ALWAYS_SAYS_THAT_TO_ME_I                                  = 11945,  -- Elder Werei always says that to me. I wonder if I'll ever be a Mythril Musketeer...
        ELDER_WEREI_IS_TEACHING_ME_THE_ART_OF                                 = 11946,  -- Elder Werei is teaching me the art of swordfighting. One day, I'll be just as good as Sir Raogrimm!
        HAVE_YOU_LEARNED_ANYTHING_USEFUL                                      = 11947,  -- Have you learned anything useful?
        WEREI_AND_GUMBAH_MAKE_FREQUENT_VISITS_TO_GRAUBERG                     = 11948,  -- Werei and Gumbah make frequent visits to Grauberg, you say?
        GRAUBERG_THAT_MOUNTAIN_IS_RIDDLED_WITH_CAVES_THE                      = 11949,  -- Grauberg... That mountain is riddled with caves--the perfect place to hide a stockpile of weapons.
        I_SHALL_COMMUNICATE_THIS_INFORMATION_TO_SENATOR_WERNER                = 11950,  -- I shall communicate this information to Senator Werner. Meanwhile, head to Grauberg and see if you can confirm my suspicions.
        HEAD_TO_GRAUBERG_AND_SEE_IF_YOU_CAN                                   = 11951,  -- Head to Grauberg and see if you can confirm my suspicions about the stockpile of weapons.
        ELDER_WEREI_AND_GUMBAH_HAVE_BEEN_ARRESTED_WHAT                        = 11952,  -- Elder Werei and Gumbah have been arrested! What's going on!?
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_THE_NEWS                                               = 11953,  -- Have you heard the news!?
        S_S_SENATOR_WERNER_RUMORS_ARE_FLYING_AROUND                           = 11954,  -- S-S-Senator Werner... Rumors are flying around that he was assassinated in the Metalworks!
        THE_DETAILS_ARE_STILL_UNCLEAR_OTHERS_ARE_SAYING                       = 11955,  -- The details are still unclear. Others are saying it was nothing more than an unauthorized intruder. I wish I could find out more, but the Metalworks is under tight security...
        I_HOPE_THE_SENATOR_WAS_UNHARMED                                       = 11956,  -- I hope the senator was unharmed...
        THE_METALWORKS_HAS_BEEN_LOCKED_DOWN_FOR_SECURITY                      = 11957,  -- The Metalworks has been locked down for security reasons. Only authorized personnel may enter!
        WHAT_NEWS_OF_THE_SENATOR                                              = 11958,  -- What news of the senator?
        YOU_D_BEST_SEE_FOR_YOURSELF_AND_THESE                                 = 11959,  -- You'd best see for yourself. And these men...?
        SECOND_DIVISION_MILITARY_POLICE_WE_WERE_IN_THE                        = 11960,  -- Second Division Military Police. We were in the midst of discussing a separate matter.
        WHEN_WE_HEARD_THAT_THE_SENATOR_OF_DEFENSE                             = 11961,  -- When we heard that the Senator of Defense was attacked, they insisted on accompanying me to the scene.
        YOU_HAVE_OUR_FULL_COOPERATION                                         = 11962,  -- You have our full cooperation.
        HM_AREN_T_YOU                                                         = 11963,  -- Hm? Aren't you...
        A_COLLEAGUE_OF_YOURS                                                  = 11964,  -- A colleague of yours?
        THIS_IS_THE_INFORMANT_THAT_WAS_INSTRUMENTAL_IN                        = 11965,  -- This is the informant that was instrumental in Werei's arrest.
        I_SEE_WELL_IF_WE_RE_DONE_WITH                                         = 11966,  -- I see. Well, if we're done with the introductions, it's time we were heading inside.
        HM_WHERE_DO_YOU_THINK_YOU_RE_GOING                                    = 11967,  -- Hm? Where do you think you're going!?
        ID_11968                                                              = 11968,  -- ...!
        SENATOR_WERNER                                                        = 11969,  -- Senator Werner!
        DEAD_WHEN_I_FOUND_HIM_HE_WAS_LAST                                     = 11970,  -- Dead when I found him. He was last seen heading into the Metalworks after meeting with the president in the Consul's Office.
        ACCORDING_TO_THE_MEDIC_THERE_ARE_MULTIPLE_VICIOUS                     = 11971,  -- According to the medic, there are multiple vicious stab wounds to the chest. This crime was motivated by anger...
        AND_THE_INTRUDER_ESCAPED                                              = 11972,  -- And the intruder escaped?
        THE_ASSASSIN_WAS_NEVER_SEEN_WE_LOCKED_DOWN                            = 11973,  -- The assassin was never seen. We locked down all exits as soon as the body was discovered--the guards are currently performing a thorough sweep of the entire building.
        FIRST_WEREI_AND_GUMBAH_S_ARREST_AND_NOW                               = 11974,  -- First Werei and Gumbah's arrest, and now this murder right under our very noses...dammit!
        WHERE_ARE_WE_ON_THIS_TALK_OF_AN                                       = 11975,  -- Where are we on this talk of an uprising? Surely the rumors aren't true...!?
        WE_STILL_DON_T_KNOW_FOR_SURE_ELDER                                    = 11976,  -- We still don't know for sure. Elder Werei and Gumbah are in the custody of the Second Division Military Police.
        THE_INVESTIGATION_IS_PROCEEDING_AS_WE_SPEAK                           = 11977,  -- The investigation is proceeding as we speak.
        WE_COULD_CERTAINLY_USE_SOME_ANSWERS                                   = 11978,  -- We could certainly use some answers.
        CAPTAIN                                                               = 11979,  -- Captain!
        MISTER_PRESIDENT_YOUR_PLANS_TO_INSPECT_THE_BATTLEFIELD                = 11980,  -- Mister President! Your plans to inspect the battlefield...?
        CANCELED                                                              = 11981,  -- Canceled.
        HOW_COULD_SUCH_VIOLENCE_BE_PERPETRATED_WITHIN_A                       = 11982,  -- How could such violence be perpetrated within a stone's throw of the President's Office!?
        NOT_ONLY_WAS_OUR_SECURITY_BREACHED_BUT_A                              = 11983,  -- Not only was our security breached, but a senior member of the government assassinated... Never have the Musketeers failed so completely in their duty!
        AS_COMMANDING_OFFICER_I_WILL_SUBMIT_MYSELF_TO                         = 11984,  -- As commanding officer, I will submit myself to any forthcoming punishment...!
        LIFT_YOUR_HEAD_KLARA                                                  = 11985,  -- Lift your head, Klara.
        SENATOR_WERNER_WAS_A_BRILLIANT_MAN_WHO_DEVOTED                        = 11986,  -- Senator Werner was a brilliant man, who devoted his entire being to the future of the Republic.
        THE_MOST_FITTING_TRIBUTE_TO_HIS_LIFE_WILL                             = 11987,  -- The most fitting tribute to his life will be to catch the criminal behind this and bring down the full force of Republican law.
        FOR_NOW_I_SUGGEST_WE_PRAY_FOR_THE                                     = 11988,  -- For now, I suggest we pray for the peace of his soul.
        WHO_WAS_RESPONSIBLE_FOR_SECURITY_DURING_SENATOR_WERNER                = 11989,  -- Who was responsible for security during Senator Werner's visit?
        I_WAS                                                                 = 11990,  -- I was...
        ZEID_I_FIND_IT_HARD_TO_BELIEVE_YOU                                    = 11991,  -- Zeid. I find it hard to believe you of all people were lax in your vigilance. How did this intruder slip past our defenses...?
        I_M_PUTTING_YOU_IN_CHARGE_OF_THIS                                     = 11992,  -- I'm putting you in charge of this investigation, Zeid. Restore the good name of the Musketeers!
        UNDERSTOOD_2                                                          = 11993,  -- Understood.
        VOLKER_YOU_ARE_TO_ASSIST_HIM                                          = 11994,  -- Volker! You are to assist him.
        YES_CAPTAIN                                                           = 11995,  -- Yes, Captain!
        I_WILL_CONVENE_AN_EMERGENCY_MEETING_OF_THE                            = 11996,  -- I will convene an emergency meeting of the Republican Defense Council and the Galkan Elders.
        AND_I_WILL_ASSUME_THE_DUTIES_OF_THE                                   = 11997,  -- And I will assume the duties of the Senator of Defense for the time being. We have work to do, Captain.
        SIR                                                                   = 11998,  -- Sir!
        WHY_DO_WE_HAVE_UNAUTHORIZED_PERSONNEL_IN_HERE                         = 11999,  -- Why do we have unauthorized personnel in here?
        YES_I_M_TALKING_ABOUT_YOU_LEAVE_THE                                   = 12000,  -- Yes, I'm talking about you. Leave the premises immediately!
        THEY_RE_GOING_TO_DO_MORE_THAN_CUT                                     = 12001,  -- They're going to do more than cut my pay for letting that informant slip through a security lockdown...
        YOU_DON_T_THINK_YOU_LL_PASS_BY                                        = 12002,  -- You! Don't think you'll pass by me twice!
        THE_RUMORS_OF_THE_ASSASSINATION_WERE_TRUE                             = 12003,  -- The rumors of the assassination were true!?
        SENATOR_WERNER_IS_DEAD                                                = 12004,  -- Senator Werner is dead...
        RECENTLY_AN_UNKNOWN_AGENT_HAD_BEEN_TRAILING_HIS                       = 12005,  -- Recently, an unknown agent had been trailing his every move--I'd bet the future of the Republic that's the assassin they're looking for.
        WITH_THE_SENATOR_GONE_I_DOUBT_I_LL                                    = 12006,  -- With the senator gone, I doubt I'll have any more tasks for you. Thank you for your competent, albeit brief, service.
        TAKE_THIS_YOUR_FINAL_REMUNERATION_FROM_THE_SENATOR                    = 12007,  -- Take this. Your final remuneration from the senator...
        A_HERO_S_STORY_THE_DEEDS_OF_IN                                        = 12008,  -- %, a hero's story! The deeds of %, in all their gloryt
        A_TRAVELING_BARD_WALKS_FAR_AND_NEAR_WHILE                             = 12009,  -- A traveling bard walks far and near While wand'ring this celestial sphere From bustling towns to godforsaken lands. But none I love more than the swell Inhabitants of Vana'diel, Espec'lly when their gil comes to my hands.t
        PAY_ME_WHAT_YOU_THINK_I_M_WORTH                                       = 12010,  -- Pay me what you think I'm worth And songs of legend may spring forth.t
        OPEN_YOUR_EARS_AND_TAKE_A_RATION_OF                                   = 12011,  -- Open your ears and take a ration Of my melodic cantillation.t
        HOW_MUCH_WILL_YOU_GIVE_THE_BARD_NOTHING                               = 12012,  -- How much will you give the bard? Nothing. # gil. # gil. # gil. # gil. # gil. # gil. Let the bard decide your title. Unlock achievement.
        I_CANNOT_WEAVE_A_BALLAD_FAIR_OUT_OF                                   = 12013,  -- I cannot weave a ballad fair Out of moonbeams and thin air.t
        THIS_STARVING_ARTIST_YOUR_GIL_FEEDS_NOW_TELL                          = 12014,  -- This starving artist, your gil feeds Now tell me of your mighty deeds!t
        WHICH_TITLE_DO_YOU_RETURN_TO_NONE                                     = 12015,  -- Which title do you return to? None. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %.
        I_LL_ADD_YOU_TO_MY_REPERTOIRE_AND                                     = 12016,  -- I'll add you to my repertoire And sing of you! So, au revoir!t
        THE_POWER_OF_SONG_A_MYSTICAL_THING_THAT                               = 12017,  -- The power of song, a mystical thing That comes forth only when you sing. A minstrel's job in life is never done. So sing a doodle-doodle-lay And be upon your merry way-- And check your title, too, oh worthy one.t
        A_HERO_OF_OUR_TIME_THE_NAME_OF                                        = 12018,  -- %, a hero of our time! The name of % throughout the world will chimet
        OH_WHAT_A_SOUL_INTREPID_AND_BOLD_TO                                   = 12019,  -- Oh, what a soul, intrepid and bold To care not how your name is toldt
        UNLOCK_WHICH_ACHIEVEMENT_NONE_JOB_LEVEL_SYNTHESIS_SKILL               = 12020,  -- Unlock which achievement? None. Job Level. Synthesis Skill 100. San d'Oria Rank 10. Bastok Rank 10. Windurst Rank 10. Zilart Missions. Promathia Missions. Aht Urhgan Missions. Mercenary Rank. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. View next page.
        UNLOCK_WHICH_ACHIEVEMENT_NONE_ARTIFACT_RELATED_QUESTS_GUILDWORKERS    = 12021,  -- Unlock which achievement? None. Artifact related Quests. Guildworkers' Union Entry. Wings of the Goddess Missions. Past Vana'diel Nation Quests. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Support Jobs. Extra Jobs. %. %. %.
        UNLOCK_WHICH_ACHIEVEMENT_NONE_LEVEL_75_WARRIOR_LEVEL                  = 12022,  -- Unlock which achievement? None. Level 75 Warrior. Level 75 Monk. Level 75 White Mage. Level 75 Black Mage. Level 75 Red Mage. Level 75 Thief. Level 75 Paladin. Level 75 Dark Knight. Level 75 Beastmaster. Level 75 Bard. Level 75 Ranger. Level 75 Samurai. Level 75 Ninja. Level 75 Dragoon. Level 75 Summoner. Level 75 Blue Mage. Level 75 Corsair. Level 75 Puppetmaster. Level 75 Dancer. Level 75 Scholar.
        YOU_HAVE_NO_ACHIEVEMENTS_TO_UNLOCK                                    = 12023,  -- You have no achievements to unlock.
        IF_YOU_SEEK_ADMISSION_TO_THE_KNIGHTS_OF                               = 12024,  -- If you seek admission to the Knights of the Iron Ram, speak with Sir Mainchelite.
        LOOKING_TO_JOIN_THE_FIGHTING_FOURTH_SPEAK_TO                          = 12025,  -- Looking to join the Fighting Fourth? Speak to Centurion Adelbrecht. He'll assist you.
        SO_YOU_THINK_YOU_HAVE_WHAT_IT_TAKES                                   = 12026,  -- So you think you have what it takes to be a Cobra? Well, then talk to Miah Riyuh and hope that she's in a good mood!
        FOR_THE_LION                                                          = 12027,  -- For the lion!
        GIVE_EM_HELL                                                          = 12028,  -- Give 'em hell, %!
        SHOULDN_T_YOU_BE_OUT_CAMPAIGNING_NOW_GET                              = 12029,  -- Shouldn't you be out campaigning? Now get!
        I_SEE_YOU_SERVE_UNDER_ANOTHER_NATION                                  = 12030,  -- I see you serve under another nation.
        I_SEE_YOU_RE_WORKING_FOR_ANOTHER_NATION                               = 12031,  -- I see you're working for another nation.
        SAYS_HERE_YOU_VE_ALREADY_GONE_AND_JOINED                              = 12032,  -- Says here you've already gone and joined some other nation's forces.
        IF_YOU_SEEK_ADMISSION_TO_THE_KNIGHTS_OF_2                             = 12033,  -- If you seek admission to the Knights of the Iron Ram, speak with Sir Mainchelite.
        IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_TO_JOIN_THE_FIGHTING                                = 12034,  -- If you're looking to join the Fighting Fourth, speak to Centurion Adelbrecht. He'll assist you.
        IF_YOU_VE_FINALLY_COME_TO_YOUR_SENSES                                 = 12035,  -- If you've finally come to your senses and decided on joining the Cobras then talk to Miah Riyuh...and hope that she's in a good mood!
        IF_YOU_SEEK_TO_REGAIN_ADMISSION_TO_THE                                = 12036,  -- If you seek to regain admission to the Knights of the Iron Ram, you must first sever ties with your nation of allegiance...and that will require Allied Notes.
        THOUGH_IF_YOU_WANT_TO_REJOIN_THE_FOURTH                               = 12037,  -- Though if you want to rejoin the fourth, I think something can be worked out. You have some Allied Notes, don't you?
        BUT_IF_YOU_VE_FINALLY_COME_TO_YOUR                                    = 12038,  -- But if you've finally come to your senses and decided to return to the Cobras, I think I can pull a few strings...for a price. You're carrying Allied Notes, right?
        PLEASE_NOTE_THAT_UPON_CHANGING_ALLEGIANCE_YOU_WILL                    = 12039,  -- Please note that upon changing allegiance, you will be required to return the two most prestigious campaign medals you possess. There is no penalty if you have yet to earn any medals.
        EXCHANGE_ALLIED_TO_TRANSFER_FROM_TO_YOU_CURRENTLY                     = 12041,  -- Exchange # Allied [Note/Notes] to transfer from [/the Knights of the Iron Ram/the Fourth Division/the Cobra Unit] to [/the Knights of the Iron Ram/the Fourth Division/the Cobra Unit]? You currently possess # [Allied Note/Allied Notes].
        PROCEED_WITH_THE_TRANSACTION_YES_NO_2                                 = 12042,  -- Proceed with the transaction? Yes. No.
        ARE_YOU_ABSOLUTELY_SURE_YES_NO                                        = 12043,  -- Are you absolutely sure? Yes. No.
        YOUR_TRANSFER_FROM_TO_IS_COMPLETE                                     = 12044,  -- Your transfer from [/the Knights of the Iron Ram/the Fourth Division/the Cobra Unit] to [/the Knights of the Iron Ram/the Fourth Division/the Cobra Unit] is complete.
        YOU_CANNOT_PLEDGE_YOUR_ALLEGIANCE_TO_ONE_NATION                       = 12045,  -- You cannot pledge your allegiance to one nation while undertaking initiation procedures of another. Withdraw your current application before attempting a transfer.
        YOU_RETURN_YOUR                                                       = 12046,  -- You return your %.
        YOU_ARE_NOW_A_MEMBER_OF_THE                                           = 12047,  -- You are now a member of the [/Knights of the Iron Ram/Republican Legion's Fourth Division/Cobra Unit]!
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_ENOUGH_ALLIED_NOTES_TO_2                           = 12048,  -- You do not possess enough Allied Notes to change your allegiance.
        FOURTH_LEGION_SEVENTH_COHORS_AH_HERE_WE_ARE                           = 12049,  -- Fourth Legion, Seventh Cohors... Ah, here we are. %, right? Legion Engineer Aurelius at your service.
        THE_CENTURION_HAS_GIVEN_ME_ORDERS_TO_ASSIST                           = 12050,  -- The centurion has given me orders to assist all legionnaires in understanding the inner-workings of the Allied Campaign.
        WHAT_CAN_I_HELP_YOU_WITH_TODAY_WHAT                                   = 12051,  -- What can I help you with today? What is the Allied Campaign? What are campaign operations? What are freelances? Nothing.
        THE_ALLIED_CAMPAIGN_IS_THE_COMPREHENSIVE_NAME_GIVEN                   = 12052,  -- The Allied Campaign is the comprehensive name given to the various operations carried out by the Forces of Altana against the Beastman Confederate.
        ARTICLE_1_DOMINION_IS_GRANTED_THE_NATION_THAT                         = 12053,  -- Article 1: Dominion is granted the nation that provides the largest contribution in regaining control of an area occupied by the beastmen.
        ARTICLE_2_IN_EXCHANGE_FOR_THE_RENOUNCING_OF                           = 12054,  -- Article 2: In exchange for the renouncing of all claims to lands seized by their army, campaign arbitration has been bestowed upon the Grand Duchy of Jeuno.
        THE_LEADERS_OF_JEUNO_WERE_FIRST_TO_RECOGNIZE                          = 12055,  -- The leaders of Jeuno were first to recognize that it would be difficult for the nations of Bastok, Windurst, and San d'Oria to cast aside all past differences and join hands on the battlefield.
        AND_THAT_S_WHY_THE_DUCHY_FELT_IT                                      = 12056,  -- And that's why the Duchy felt it necessary to motivate the armies by offering rewards for their valor. In other words, we can still compete against those dogs in San d'Oria even though we have to fight alongside them.
        AS_YOU_KNOW_OUR_NATION_S_WEALTH_LIES                                  = 12057,  -- As you know, our nation's wealth lies in the natural resources that lie beneath the arid plains of Gustaberg. However, by taking advantage of Article 1 of the Allied Campaign charter, Bastok can lay claim to the fertile lands to the north, thus bolstering our economy even further!
        AS_A_PROVISIONARY_MEMBER_OF_THE_FIGHTING_FOURTH                       = 12058,  -- As a provisionary member of the Fighting Fourth, you will be required to participate in various campaign missions and operations to help ensure the prosperity of the Republic.
        CAMPAIGN_OPERATIONS_ALSO_KNOWN_AS_CAMPAIGN_OPS_IS                     = 12059,  -- Campaign operations, also known as Campaign Ops, is the term used for the long list of small-scale missions authorized by the Allied War Council in Jeuno.
        WHEN_AN_OPERATION_IS_SUCCESSFULLY_COMPLETED_THE_NATION                = 12060,  -- When an operation is successfully completed, the nation is rewarded with an increase in battle funding, paid for by the Repositorium--an international bank founded by the four nations of Mindartia and Quon, and located in Jeuno.
        TO_PUT_IT_BLUNTLY_THE_HARDER_YOU_WORK                                 = 12061,  -- To put it bluntly, the harder you work, the richer the Republic becomes.
        NOW_DON_T_GET_THE_WRONG_IDEA_THAT                                     = 12062,  -- Now don't get the wrong idea. That money is for the Republican Legion, not for you to spend at the local pub. No, you'll be rewarded with Allied Notes, which can be used to purchase supplies and equipment. You'll also be allowed to participate in more sensitive operations.
        NOW_UNLESS_YOU_HAVE_ANY_MORE_QUESTIONS_YOU                            = 12063,  -- Now unless you have any more questions, you are to report to First Centurion Hieronymus on my left.
        HE_WILL_ASSIST_YOU_IN_APPLYING_FOR_AN                                 = 12064,  -- He will assist you in applying for an operation. Good luck, %.
        AH_ITCHING_TO_GET_OUT_ON_THE_BATTLEFIELD                              = 12065,  -- Ah, itching to get out on the battlefield now, are we? Alright, just let me explain a little about the Allied Campaign map, and then you can go.
        TO_VIEW_THE_CAMPAIGN_MAP_FIRST_SELECT_REGION                          = 12066,  -- To view the campaign map, first select Region Info, and then Campaign.
        THE_SWORD_INDICATES_AREAS_WHERE_BATTLES_ARE_CURRENTLY                 = 12067,  -- The sword indicates areas where battles are currently being waged.
        IF_YOU_ARE_NOT_SIGNED_UP_FOR_ANY                                      = 12068,  -- If you are not signed up for any operations, then hurry to the frontlines and join your fellow legionnaires.
        THE_HEROISM_GAUGE_INDICATES_LOCATIONS_WHERE_THE_BATTLES               = 12069,  -- The heroism gauge indicates locations where the battles have become quite heated. Who knows what may occur in an area with a full gauge?
        THAT_IS_ALL_NORMALLY_WAR_DOESN_T_LET                                  = 12070,  -- That is all. Normally, war doesn't let you choose your battles, but this time it's different. We trust that you will choose wisely.
        FREELANCES_IS_THE_COLLECTIVE_TERM_GIVEN_TO_ROGUE                      = 12071,  -- Freelances is the collective term given to rogue commandos who have not pledged allegiance to any nation.
        THESE_GROUPS_DO_NOT_FALL_UNDER_CONTROL_OF                             = 12072,  -- These groups do not fall under control of the Allied Forces, and only fight when and where they feel like it. Heroes for hire, you could say.
        HOWEVER_MANY_OF_THEM_ARE_PROVEN_FIGHTERS_AND                          = 12073,  -- However, many of them are proven fighters, and that is something an army can never have too many of.
        IF_YOU_EVER_COME_ACROSS_ONE_OF_THESE                                  = 12074,  -- If you ever come across one of these freelances, see if you can't convince them to lend their swords to a just cause. The worse they can do is say no, right?
        MIGHT_YOU_BE_THINKING_ABOUT_JOINING_THE_REPUBLICAN                    = 12075,  -- Might you be thinking about joining the Republican Legion? If that's the case, then go speak with Centurion Adelbrecht. He'll assist you.
        YOU_RE_NOT_A_MEMBER_OF_THE_REPUBLICAN                                 = 12076,  -- You're not a member of the Republican Legion, are you? If you're thinking about signing up, then you'll first have to pledge allegiance to Bastok. Speak with Centurion Fridolin for assistance.
        I_M_TERRIBLY_SORRY_BUT_CHOCOBO_SERVICES_ARE                           = 12077,  -- I'm terribly sorry, but chocobo services are currently unavailable.
        THROUGH_THIS_TUNNEL_LIE_THE_FOURTH_DIVISION_BARRACKS                  = 12078,  -- Through this tunnel lie the Fourth Division barracks. While far from luxurious, the rooms provide troops with a place to store their belongings, receive packages, and rest up before missions.
        SALUTATIONS_I_AM_CAMPAIGN_EVALUATION_OFFICIAL_ALFRED_HOW              = 12079,  -- Salutations, I am Campaign Evaluation Official Alfred. How might I be of assistance?
        GREETINGS_I_AM_CAMPAIGN_EVALUATION_OFFICIAL_ANNABELLE_HOW             = 12080,  -- Greetings, I am Campaign Evaluation Official Annabelle. How can I help you today?
        HELLO_I_M_CAMPAIGN_EVALUATION_OFFICIAL_LLEWELLYN_HOW                  = 12081,  -- Hello, I'm Campaign Evaluation Official Llewellyn. How can I help you today?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_REQUIRE_NOTHING_AN_EVALUATION_INFO                        = 12082,  -- What do you require? Nothing. An evaluation. Info on the duration of my medal. An overview of evaluations. Info on medals. Info on the benefits of medals. Info on evaluation process.
        EVALUATIONS_ARE_CONDUCTED_ON_ALL_PARTICIPANTS_OF_THE                  = 12083,  -- Evaluations are conducted on all participants of the Allied Campaign. Individual data is collected by the Allied War Council from various sources, such as Campaign Arbiters and the leaders of the armies in which the soldiers serve. This data is then used to determine whether or not a decoration is to be conferred.
        SOME_OF_THE_AREAS_THAT_ARE_CONSIDERED_IN                              = 12084,  -- Some of the areas that are considered in this evaluation are performance in campaign operations, as well as valor shown during campaign battles.
        THE_MORE_AN_INDIVIDUAL_IS_DECORATED_THE_MORE                          = 12085,  -- The more an individual is decorated, the more responsibility he or she will be given within the Allied Forces. And with more responsibility comes the promise of larger compensation in exchange for services.
        HOWEVER_THE_PRESTIGE_THAT_ACCOMPANIES_THE_MEDALS_ALSO                 = 12086,  -- However, the prestige that accompanies the medals also carries with it a great weight. To maintain one's status, he or she must continue to exceed previous expectations. If a soldier fails to fulfill the duties that are required of all those who possess a certain medal, then the Allied War Council will be forced to confiscate that decoration.
        TO_PUT_IT_SIMPLY_ONLY_THOSE_WHO_FIGHT                                 = 12087,  -- To put it simply, only those who fight with fervor and precision...only those who put the glory of the Allied Campaign above all else...will be allowed to reap the benefits that come with victory.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_LEARN_MORE_OF_THE                                      = 12088,  -- If you wish to learn more of the Allied Campaign, please speak with [/Lady Fiaudie/Centurion Aurelius/Kolin-Olin].
        THERE_ARE_TWO_MORE_THINGS_OF_NOTE                                     = 12089,  -- There are two more things of note.
        ONCE_AN_EVALUATION_HAS_BEEN_REQUESTED_THE_ALLIED                      = 12090,  -- Once an evaluation has been requested, the Allied War Council will require [five days/one hour] (Earth time) to come to a conclusion.
        DURING_THAT_TIME_INDIVIDUALS_MAY_JOIN_AS_MANY                         = 12091,  -- During that time, individuals may join as many operations or battles as they wish, but will only be considered for a single medal.
        HOWEVER_THE_SAME_RULES_APPLY_FOR_AN_INADEQUATE                        = 12092,  -- However, the same rules apply for an inadequate performance. No matter how low one scores, the maximum number of decorations that can be confiscated is one.
        ALSO_INDIVIDUALS_MUST_NOT_FORGET_THAT_ALL_MEDALS                      = 12093,  -- Also, individuals must not forget that all medals come with expiration dates. While an extremely unorthodox practice, this measure was deemed necessary to prevent the forgery of allied decorations by those persons with dubious intentions.
        UPON_CONFERRAL_ALL_MEDALS_ARE_MARKED_WITH_A                           = 12094,  -- Upon conferral, all medals are marked with a magical seal that dissipates after a period of thirty days (Earth time). Once the seal has vanished, the medal will become void and its owner will no longer be able to participate in campaign operations or battles, among other things.
        IT_IS_HIGHLY_RECOMMENDED_THAT_YOU_KEEP_TRACK                          = 12095,  -- It is highly recommended that you keep track of the time remaining on your medal and apply for evaluations regularly.
        IS_THERE_ANYTHING_ELSE_YOU_WISH_TO_ASK                                = 12096,  -- Is there anything else you wish to ask?
        CAMPAIGN_MEDALS_ARE_OFFICIAL_REWARDS_GIVEN_TO_THOSE                   = 12097,  -- Campaign medals are official rewards given to those individuals who perform exemplary deeds for the Allied Forces.
        THESE_DECORATIONS_ARE_INTERNATIONALLY_RECOGNIZED_AS_SYMBOLS_OF        = 12098,  -- These decorations are internationally recognized as symbols of strength, loyalty, and honor. They not only garner respect, but provide their bearers with privileges not offered civilians.
        THOSE_WHO_HAVE_BEEN_DECORATED_WITH_THE_MORE                           = 12099,  -- Those who have been decorated with the more prestigious medals will also be highly regarded among their army's ranks, and thus entrusted with increasingly difficult and important missions.
        ON_THE_OTHER_HAND_DISLOYALTY_TO_ONE_S                                 = 12100,  -- On the other hand, disloyalty to one's nation is highly frowned upon. If, for any reason, an individual wishes to leave their current army of employment and pledge allegiance to another, they will be required to return their two most distinguished medals.
        TO_THE_POINT_ARE_WE_VERY_WELL_I                                       = 12101,  -- To the point, are we? Very well, I shall list the merits those in the possession of medals may receive.
        FIRSTLY_THE_MORE_PRESTIGIOUS_AN_INDIVIDUAL_S_MEDAL                    = 12102,  -- Firstly, the more prestigious an individual's medal, the more weight his/her] army's [/curate/supply commander/Morale Manager] will grant his/her] opinion.
        SECONDLY_THE_TYPES_OF_CAMPAIGN_OPS_AVAILABLE_TO                       = 12103,  -- Secondly, the types of Campaign Ops available to an individual will increase based on the medals that he/she] has in his/her] possession. More advanced operations will earn participants increased amounts of EXP and Allied Notes, as well as have a heavier influence on performance evaluations.
        THIRDLY_BENEFITS_RECEIVED_DURING_CAMPAIGN_BATTLES_WILL_VARY           = 12104,  -- Thirdly, benefits received during campaign battles will vary depending on the variety of medals an individual carries. The better the medals, the larger the opportunity to earn EXP, Allied Notes, and reputation. The selection of temporary items available for purchase will also improve.
        HOWEVER_THE_MORE_PRESTIGIOUS_THE_MEDAL_THE_MORE                       = 12105,  -- However, the more prestigious the medal, the more that will be expected of its bearer. The Campaign Arbiters will not go easy on those who have already proven themselves.
        UNDERSTOOD_3                                                          = 12106,  -- Understood?
        GREETINGS_MY_LEDGER_STATES_THAT_THE_EARLIEST_YOU                      = 12107,  -- Greetings, %. My ledger states that the earliest you can apply for an evaluation is in # day[/s].
        GREETINGS_MY_LEDGER_STATES_THAT_THE_EARLIEST_YOU_2                    = 12108,  -- Greetings, %. My ledger states that the earliest you can apply for an evaluation is in # hour[/s].
        GREETINGS_MY_LEDGER_STATES_THAT_THE_EARLIEST_YOU_3                    = 12109,  -- Greetings, %. My ledger states that the earliest you can apply for an evaluation is...any moment now.
