        SUPERB_WELL_THAT_TAKES_CARE_OF_ONE_ASSIGNMENT                         = 12233,  -- Superb! Well, that takes care of one assignment.
        JUST_TO_LET_YOU_KNOW_I_HAVE_SEVERAL                                   = 12234,  -- Just to let you know. I have several assignments which I would be more than happy to receive your able assistance with. If you ever want to see about getting some more attire, just let me know.
        UH_OH_I_KNOW_THAT_LOOK_SOMEBODY_WANTS                                 = 12235,  -- Uh-oh, I know that look! Somebody wants some more clothes. Am I right? Which means somebody wants to help me with my research! Right?
        I_KNOW_I_KNOW_I_HAVEN_T_GOTTEN                                        = 12236,  -- I know, I know. I haven't gotten to where I am today by not being able to read people. So, what will it be this time, %?
        MARVELOUS_THAT_COMPLETES_ALL_OF_MY_ASSIGNMENTS                        = 12237,  -- Marvelous! That completes all of my assignments!
        I_HAVEN_T_THE_WORDS_TO_THANK_YOU                                      = 12238,  -- %... I haven't the words to thank you!
        HMMM_YOU_DON_T_QUITE_SEEM_COMPLETE_YET                                = 12239,  -- Hmmm... You don't quite seem...complete, yet. Something is still missing, to be sure. Unfortunately, I am fresh out of assignments for you to help me with.
        HAHAHA_HAHA_HA_COUGH                                                  = 12240,  -- Hahaha! Haha! Ha! <cough>!
        WELL_I_WAS_ABLE_TO_GET_THROUGH_ALL                                    = 12241,  -- Well, I was able to get through all of my assignments without any major hang-ups. I expect cleeear sailing from here on out. All thanks to you. I truly am most grateful!
        BY_THE_WAY_THERE_IS_A_CERTAIN_TYPE                                    = 12242,  -- By the way, there is a certain type of material that cannot be obtained without fulfilling certain...requirements, first. Keep an eye out!
        LONG_TIME_NO_SEE_NO_DOUBT_NEWS_OF                                     = 12243,  -- Long time no see, %. No doubt, news of the serial killings has already reached your ears. The victims number four, and counting...
        THAT_IS_OF_COURSE_UNLESS_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS                       = 12244,  -- That is, of course, unless the Mythril Musketeers have anything to say about it. Orders to conduct an investigation have already been issued from above, or so I'm told.
        BUT_TO_BE_HONEST_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_ARE                           = 12245,  -- But to be honest, the Mythril Musketeers are a little short-handed at the moment. They could certainly do with your help again, %.
        DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_ARE_YOU_ABSOLUTELY_POSITIVE                       = 12246,  -- ...Darksteel Hurricane? Are you absolutely positive?
        THE_MOST_RECENT_VICTIM_S_POST_IN_THE                                  = 12247,  -- The most recent victim's post in the Department of Industry...
        THE_CRUELLY_METHODICAL_MANNER_IN_WHICH_HE_WAS                         = 12248,  -- The cruelly methodical manner in which he was slain...
        AND_LASTLY_THE_MARK_CARVED_INTO_HIS_FOREHEAD                          = 12249,  -- And lastly, the mark carved into his forehead.
        ALL_OF_THIS_STRONGLY_SUGGESTS_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_S                   = 12250,  -- All of this strongly suggests Darksteel Hurricane's involvement.
        CURSES_BUT_NOTHING_HAS_BEEN_HEARD_OF_THAT                             = 12251,  -- Curses! But nothing has been heard of that cold-blooded killer for years!
        IT_S_NOT_UNCOMMON_FOR_CRIMINALS_TO_GO                                 = 12252,  -- It's not uncommon for criminals to go into hiding for a time, waiting for the authorities to slip into complacency.
        HM_HOW_FARES_THE_INVESTIGATION                                        = 12253,  -- Hm... How fares the investigation?
        I_FEAR_THERE_IS_LITTLE_TO_REPORT_AT                                   = 12254,  -- ...I fear there is little to report at present. Time has scarcely elapsed since the investigation orders were issued.
        IS_THAT_SO_I_M_INCLINED_TO_BELIEVE                                    = 12255,  -- Is that so...? I'm inclined to believe differently.
        WELL_DO_I_KNOW_OF_THE_CIRCUMSTANCES_WHICH                             = 12256,  -- Well do I know of the circumstances which led to the Mythril Musketeers being relieved of its customary role as the president's personal escort, and truly do I empathize with your desire to rid your unit of the burden of ignominy.
        BUT_IT_CANNOT_BE_DENIED_THAT_YOUR_UNIT                                = 12257,  -- But it cannot be denied that your unit is severely undermanned for an undertaking of this magnitude. Therefore, I offer you the full cooperation of my First Brigade.
        ID_12258                                                              = 12258,  -- ...
        I_WAS_UNDER_THE_IMPRESSION_THAT_THE_FIRST                             = 12259,  -- I was under the impression that the First Brigade had been assigned the security of His Excellency the President in our stead.
        A_SUPERFLUOUS_CONCERN_A_GOOD_HALF_OF_MY                               = 12260,  -- A superfluous concern. A good half of my forty soldiers can easily be spared for the investigative effort without compromising the president's safety.
        WE_ARE_GRATEFUL_FOR_YOUR_OFFER                                        = 12261,  -- ...We are grateful for your offer.
        ONE_MORE_THING                                                        = 12262,  -- One more thing.
        THERE_IS_A_THEORY_WHICH_EXPLAINS_HOW_DARKSTEEL                        = 12263,  -- There is a theory which explains how Darksteel Hurricane was able to evade capture during his previous reign of terror. That is, the presence of an informant--a traitor within our ranks.
        BE_CAREFUL_WHOM_YOU_PRIVILEGE_WITH_ACCESS_TO                          = 12264,  -- Be careful whom you privilege with access to classified information.
        YOUR_CONCERN_COULDN_T_BE_MORE_MISPLACED_THE                           = 12265,  -- Your concern couldn't be more misplaced. The bond of mythril my people share is stronger than that of any steel. I trust each and every one of them with my life.
        HAHAHA_THAT_IS_MOST_REASSURING_VERY_WELL_THEN                         = 12266,  -- Hahaha, that is most reassuring. Very well then. I will set my people to work at once.
        FULL_COOPERATION_PSHAW_THAT_S_ONE_THINLY_VEILED                       = 12267,  -- Full cooperation? Pshaw... That's one thinly veiled war declaration if you ask my humble opinion.
        I_M_SORRY_ALL_OF_THIS_IS_MY                                           = 12268,  -- I'm sorry... All of this is my doing...
        DON_T_PAY_IT_ANY_MIND_FIVE_MOONS                                      = 12269,  -- Don't pay it any mind, Five Moons. All we have to do is locate and apprehend the killer before those novice investigators do--as simple an operation as they come.
        YOU_RE_RIGHT_IT_S_THE_LEAST_I                                         = 12270,  -- You're right. It's the least I can do to repay the president for the kindness he showed me.
        THAT_S_MORE_LIKE_THE_OLD_FIVE_MOONS                                   = 12271,  -- That's more like the old Five Moons! Let's go knock that Iron Musketeers captain off his gilded saddle!
        CAPTAIN_I_VE_BEEN_MEANING_TO_ASK_YOU                                  = 12272,  -- Captain, I've been meaning to ask you about your ailment. Have your bouts of dizziness abated?
        I_STAND_BEFORE_YOU_DON_T_I_THERE                                      = 12273,  -- I stand before you, don't I? There'll be time enough later to fret over my health.
        BEST_WE_FOCUS_ALL_OUR_EFFORTS_NOW_ON                                  = 12274,  -- Best we focus all our efforts now on capturing our man before the First Division can get their ambitious hands on him.
        EXPLOIT_ALL_INFORMATION_NETWORKS_TO_THE_FULLEST_EXTENT                = 12275,  -- Exploit all information networks to the fullest extent, be it underworld or beastman, and spare no coin to procure the intelligence we need. The operation is commenced!
        A_MOMENT_CAPTAIN_THERE_S_ONE_THING_I                                  = 12276,  -- A moment, Captain. There's one thing I'd like to ascertain before our investigation begins in earnest.
        AS_CAPTAIN_BARTHOLOMAUS_MENTIONED_EARLIER_NO_INCIDENT_LINKED          = 12277,  -- As Captain Bartholomaus mentioned earlier, no incident linked to Darksteel Hurricane has occurred in years.
        SO_WHY_NOW_WHY_MAKE_A_RETURN_TO                                       = 12278,  -- So, why now? Why make a return to the fray now, when the climate of discontent during the recent Galkan uprising would've been infinitely more auspicious to his cause?
        CAPTAIN_I_MUST_CONFESS_TO_BEING_PLAGUED_WITH                          = 12279,  -- Captain... I must confess to being plagued with similar doubts.
        THE_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_OF_OLD_EXCLUSIVELY_TARGETED_HIGH              = 12280,  -- The Darksteel Hurricane of old exclusively targeted high-ranking officials--those who'd only dare travel in the company of a small army.
        BUT_THIS_TIME_AMONG_THE_VICTIMS_ARE_GOVERNMENT                        = 12281,  -- But this time, among the victims are government officers of no notable standing and even family members who were unfortunate enough to witness the unspeakable deed. This indiscriminate slaughter of innocent citizens tells me that something is sorely amiss.
        ID_12282                                                              = 12282,  -- ...
        CAPTAIN_COULD_OUR_SUSPECT_IN_FACT_BE_A                                = 12283,  -- Captain, could our suspect in fact be a copycat, rather than the real Darksteel Hurricane?
        ALL_POSSIBILITIES_MUST_BE_TAKEN_INTO_CONSIDERATION                    = 12284,  -- All possibilities must be taken into consideration.
        BUT_NOW_IS_THE_TIME_FOR_ACTION_NOT                                    = 12285,  -- But now is the time for action, not speculation. Lives may be lost while we stand here dwelling on inconsequential details.
        YES_MA_AM                                                             = 12286,  -- Yes, ma'am!
        ID_12287                                                              = 12287,  -- ...
        DEBUG_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_LOOP_YES_NO                                      = 12288,  -- Debug: Do you wish to loop? Yes. No.
        UWAAAH_GODDESS_HAVE_MERCY                                             = 12289,  -- Uwaaah! Goddess have mercy!
        OH_IT_S_JUST_YOU_DON_T_SNEAK                                          = 12290,  -- Oh, it's just you, %... Don't sneak up on me like that.
        H_HEY_DON_T_GET_THE_WRONG_IDEA                                        = 12291,  -- H-hey, don't get the wrong idea now. It's not like I'm afraid of having a run-in with Darksteel Hurricane or anything. As a matter of fact, I'd welcome the opportunity to bump into that despicable fiend in a dark alley. Y-yeah...that's right. A-and when I do, I'll send him to dreamland with an authentic Galkan chokehold. He'll be down for the count before he even has a chance to fumble for the hilt of his razor-sharp, blood-stained blade that's rumored to slice through limbs as if they were pumpkin pie... Ahaha...ha... <Ulp>...
        AH_HOW_GOES_THE_INVESTIGATION_WERE_YOU_ABLE                           = 12292,  -- Ah, %. How goes the investigation? Were you able to unearth any clues pointing towards Darksteel Hurricane?
        I_SEE_IMPRESSIVE_DETECTIVE_WORK_AS_ALWAYS_NOW                         = 12293,  -- I see. Impressive detective work as always, %. Now, contingent upon the manner of intelligence we acquire from Blatherix...
        HM_WHAT_S_THIS_TALK_OF_GOBLINS_YOU                                    = 12294,  -- Hm? What's this talk of Goblins, you ask? Well, determining the suspect's appearance and characteristics is but the beginning. Narrowing down his location is the next logical step. For this, I've a mind to tap into the Goblins' expansive information network.
        YOU_VE_ALREADY_ACQUAINTED_YOURSELF_WITH_BLATHERIX_IF                  = 12295,  -- You've already acquainted yourself with Blatherix, if I'm not mistaken?
        IN_THAT_CASE_I_D_BE_MOST_OBLIGED                                      = 12296,  -- In that case, I'd be most obliged if you could seek him out and see if he can offer us anything on Darksteel Hurricane. I'd see to it myself, but there're still a few leads that I'd like to verify, preferably sooner than later.
        HM_SEARCHIN_FOR_ONE_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_ARE_WE                        = 12297,  -- Hm? Searchin' for one Darksteel Hurricane, are we? The fellow that's been makin' headlines for all the wrong reasons? Sounds kinda dangerous to me, but business is business. So, whatcha got on him so far?
        UH_HUH_UH_HUH_GOES_AROUND_HIDIN_HIS                                   = 12298,  -- Uh huh, uh huh... Goes around hidin' his forehead...decked out in darksteel armor...wields a great sword...
        HMM_I_COULD_VE_SWORN_SEEIN_NO_WAIT                                    = 12299,  -- Hmm... I could've sworn seein'... No, wait... I've gotten my swords all mixed up.
        SORRY_BUDDY_BUT_I_GOT_ZILCH_FOR_YOU                                   = 12300,  -- Sorry buddy, but I got zilch for you this time.
        BUT_I_KNOW_GUYS_FELLOW_GOBBIES_IN_THE                                 = 12301,  -- But I know guys--fellow Gobbies in the information network--who might have whatcha lookin' for.
        TODAY_S_YOUR_LUCKY_DAY_WE_RE_MEETIN                                   = 12302,  -- Today's your lucky day. We're meetin' in a bit, so you can tag along.
        THERE_S_JUST_ONE_TEENY_WEENY_LITTLE_PROBLEM                           = 12303,  -- There's just one teeny-weeny little problem, though. It's a Gobbies-only meetin', and no outsider who's filched a gander has ever been allowed to walk out in one piece.
        BUT_IF_WE_USE_GOBLIN_DUST_YEAH_THAT                                   = 12304,  -- But if we use Goblin Dust... Yeah, that might just work.
        YOU_BRING_ME_AND_AND_I_LL_COOK                                        = 12305,  -- You bring me %, %, and %, and I'll cook you up a dose of Goblin Dust. Get it? Got it? Good!
        THINGS_SURE_HAVE_TAKEN_A_TURN_FOR_THE                                 = 12306,  -- Things sure have taken a turn for the worse around here of late. That's why everyone is closing up shop.
        THE_BRILIOTH_ESTATE_LIES_IN_THE_RESIDENTIAL_AREA                      = 12307,  -- The Brilioth Estate lies in the residential area. They are certainly the most notable family of dancers in these parts.
        THEY_SAY_THE_ONLY_DAUGHTER_LAILA_IS_DOING                             = 12308,  -- They say the only daughter, Laila, is doing her dancer training now under the strict tutelage of her mother.
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_THE_RUMORS_THERE_HAVE_BEEN                             = 12309,  -- Have you heard the rumors? There have been several sightings of these so-called maws outside the city. People are saying they may have been unleashed by the beasthordes!
        ALL_ACCOUNTS_CLAIM_THAT_THEY_FLOAT_JUST_ABOVE                         = 12310,  -- All accounts claim that they float just above ground, wreathing about, with gaping mouths like great voids that never shut... It gives me the chills just to think about it.
        AN_ENORMOUS_COMET_IS_VISIBLE_IN_THE_NIGHT                             = 12311,  -- An enormous comet is visible in the night sky as of late.
        I_M_NOT_QUITE_SURE_WHY_BUT_WHENEVER                                   = 12312,  -- I'm not quite sure why, but whenever I see a comet like that, it just puts a flutter in my chest.
        I_LL_ADMIT_I_WASN_T_SURE_HOW                                          = 12313,  -- I'll admit, I wasn't sure how things would turn out when Selbina suddenly declared its independence.
        SENATOR_WERNER_DISPATCHED_THE_REPUBLICAN_LEGION_AND_TOOK              = 12314,  -- Senator Werner dispatched the Republican Legion and took control of the situation with such incredible speed. Even the president himself was amazed by the senator's show of skill.
        THERE_S_A_MINING_SPOT_IN_GRAUBERG_WHERE                               = 12315,  -- There's a mining spot in Grauberg where you can dig up some very good quality crystals.
        APPARENTLY_THE_QUADAV_SHIELDWARRIORS_WILL_STOP_AT_NOTHING             = 12316,  -- Apparently the Quadav Shieldwarriors will stop at nothing to gain control of mining resources. That's the reason for the continuing conflict between them and the Republic.
        BEFORE_THE_ONSET_OF_WAR_PRESIDENT_PRIEN_RALLIED                       = 12317,  -- Before the onset of war, President Prien rallied the strong support of the Galkan citizenry. That was the key to his winning the election.
        BUT_IT_SEEMS_HIS_CAMPAIGN_PROMISES_OF_IMPROVING                       = 12318,  -- But it seems his campaign promises of improving living standards have been complicated by the outbreak of hostilities.
        I_M_A_HUGE_FAN_OF_LAILA_S                                             = 12319,  -- I'm a huge fan of Laila's dancing! She's such an artist!
        EVERYONE_AGREES_THAT_SHE_IS_A_CHILD_PRODIGY                           = 12320,  -- Everyone agrees that she is a child prodigy. It's undeniable!
        UNFORTUNATELY_SHE_S_ALSO_FAMOUS_FOR_NOT_SIGNING                       = 12321,  -- Unfortunately, she's also famous for not signing autographs. Promise if you ever get one, you'll give it to me!
        DUE_TO_THE_ENCROACHING_THREAT_OF_THE_QUADAV                           = 12322,  -- Due to the encroaching threat of the Quadav Shieldwarriors, entry to Southern Gustaberg is currently prohibited. The Republic appreciates your understanding.
        THIS_FACILITY_IS_FOR_THE_TEMPORARY_IMPRISONMENT_OF                    = 12323,  -- This facility is for the temporary imprisonment of beastman prisoners of war. For your own safety, you are advised to keep your distance.
        WHEN_THE_BEASTHORDES_SIEGED_SAN_D_ORIA_PRESIDENT                      = 12324,  -- When the beasthordes sieged San d'Oria, President Prien wasted no time in putting the entire Republic on a wartime footing.
        IN_RETROSPECT_IT_WAS_CERTAINLY_THE_RIGHT_THING                        = 12325,  -- In retrospect, it was certainly the right thing to do. If not for his unwavering leadership, we would most likely have begun the war well behind the already expanding beasthordes.
        THE_ALLIED_FORCES_OF_ALTANA_HAVE_BEEN_FORMED                          = 12326,  -- The Allied Forces of Altana have been formed collectively by Jeuno and the three nations to combat the Beastman Confederate.
        WE_VE_NO_BUSINESS_IN_AN_ALLIANCE_WITH                                 = 12327,  -- We've no business in an alliance with Windurst, if you ask me. Those Windurstians are not to be trusted. Am I the only one who remembers the Elshimo Campaign!?
        YOU_VE_HEARD_WHAT_THEY_SAY_THAT_THE                                   = 12328,  -- You've heard what they say, that the heat of combat will make you see things you've never seen before?
        IT_S_TRUE_IN_BATTLE_I_SAW_A                                           = 12329,  -- It's true... In battle I saw a...horrific monster. Not like any of the other beastmen. Covered in mangy black and white fur...
        AT_FIRST_I_THOUGHT_IT_SOME_KIND_OF                                    = 12330,  -- At first, I thought it some kind of wicked Mithra. But no... That was no Mithra!
        I_HEAR_LOTS_OF_PEOPLE_SAYING_THEY_WISH                                = 12331,  -- I hear lots of people saying they wish they hadn't been born to witness such dark and troubled days. But I, for one, am glad I'm alive to witness this war.
        UNDOUBTEDLY_THERE_ARE_HARDSHIPS_TO_BE_ENDURED_BUT                     = 12332,  -- Undoubtedly there are hardships to be endured, but this is a heroic battle that will surely live on in our histories! I would count myself blessed to be able to see it through to completion!
        THIS_HERE_S_AS_USEFUL_A_CHOCOBO_AS                                    = 12333,  -- This here's as useful a chocobo as you'll ever see. Capable of anything from battle mount to messenger chocobo!
        SENATOR_WERNER_IS_ADAMANT_ABOUT_HAVING_A_TECHNOLOGICALLY              = 12334,  -- Senator Werner is adamant about having a technologically advanced military. He even goes so far as to visit the Metalworks from time to time.
        IT_SEEMS_CHIEF_ENGINEER_CID_IS_EXTREMELY_BUSY                         = 12335,  -- It seems Chief Engineer Cid is extremely busy after taking up the additional post as head of the Gunpowder Room.
        SENATOR_WERNER_WAS_ALWAYS_ADAMANT_ABOUT_HAVING_A                      = 12336,  -- Senator Werner was always adamant about having a technologically advanced military. He even used to go so far as to visit the Metalworks from time to time.
        THE_GALKAN_BRIDGE_IS_CURRENTLY_CLOSED_TO_PREVENT                      = 12337,  -- The Galkan Bridge is currently closed to prevent infiltration by beastman spies.
        THE_GALKAN_BRIDGE_SHOULD_BE_REOPENED_IMMEDIATELY_I                    = 12338,  -- The Galkan Bridge should be reopened immediately. I don't know what the president could be thinking. He claims to have roots in the miner's faction, but just what does he think of the Galka in the mining district?
        IT_IS_TIMES_LIKE_THIS_WHEN_I_WISH                                     = 12339,  -- It is times like this when I wish that Talekeeper Raogrimm were still around to carry us through.
        IT_HAS_BEEN_ALMOST_TEN_YEARS_SINCE_RAOGRIMM                           = 12340,  -- It has been almost ten years since Raogrimm disappeared in the wintry cold of the north. We can only pray that he is still alive...somewhere.
        THE_METALWORKS_HAVE_BEEN_PLACED_UNDER_THE_JURISDICTION                = 12341,  -- The Metalworks have been placed under the jurisdiction of the military in order to develop and produce arms for the war. Neither townspeople nor low-ranking soldiers are permitted to enter.
        MINING_ACTIVITIES_WERE_FORCED_TO_A_HALT_WHEN                          = 12342,  -- Mining activities were forced to a halt when a squadron of Quadav sieged the entrance to the Palborough Mines.
        NOT_TO_SAY_THAT_MINING_DAY_AFTER_DAY                                  = 12343,  -- Not to say that mining day after day is a bag of laughs, but having no work at all is even worse. Maybe I'll volunteer for the Legion...
        DO_YOU_KNOW_WHAT_A_SAHAGIN_IS                                         = 12344,  -- Do you know what a Sahagin is?
        YOU_KNOW_THOSE_FISH_LIKE_BEASTMEN_THEIR_DEMOLITION                    = 12345,  -- You know, those fish-like beastmen. Their demolition tactics have reduced Port Bastok to a shadow of its former glory. The Third Division of the Republican Legion is working tirelessly to rebuild it.
        AND_THE_CRUSHING_DEFEAT_AT_GRAUBERG_LEFT_EVEN                         = 12346,  -- And the crushing defeat at Grauberg left even the Fourth Division nearly annihilated. At this rate, who knows what will become of our republic...
        THIS_IS_THE_FREIDRICH_BATTERY_IT_BEARS_THE                            = 12347,  -- This is the Freidrich Battery. It bears the name of President Freidrich, our great leader during the First Battle of Konschtat.
        THE_BATTERY_HAS_BEEN_REINFORCED_WITH_THE_FINEST                       = 12348,  -- The battery has been reinforced with the finest Bastokan artillery to repel the siege of the beasthordes.
        WE_GALKA_LIVE_SOME_200_YEARS_BEFORE_SETTING                           = 12349,  -- We Galka live some 200 years before setting off on our journey of rebirth. But none of us wish to embark on that journey now. Not with the fate of our nation, and world, so unsure.
        AT_THE_BATTLE_OF_VUNKERL_INLET_THE_REPUBLICAN                         = 12350,  -- At the battle of Vunkerl Inlet, the Republican Legion's Third Division encountered a gigas raiding party approaching by sea.
        THE_FIENDS_EVENTUALLY_MADE_LANDFALL_BUT_THEIR_ADVANCE                 = 12351,  -- The fiends eventually made landfall, but their advance was stopped cold by the brilliant tactics of Legatus Invincible Shield. No doubt his military genius will become the stuff of legend.
        MOST_PEOPLE_WOULDN_T_AGREE_WITH_ME_BUT                                = 12352,  -- Most people wouldn't agree with me, but I'm glad to be alive in this age of strife. The battlefield is where I belong!
        YOU_DISCOVER_AND_COLLECT_A_SUSPICIOUS_OBJECT                          = 12353,  -- You discover and collect a suspicious object.
