        WE_HAVE_RECEIVED_UNCONFIRMED_REPORTS_THAT_A_MEDIUM                    = 12855,  -- We have received unconfirmed reports that a medium-sized Beastman force is stationed in [Xarcabard/Beaucedine Glacier/The Eldieme Necropolis/Crawlers' Nest/Garlaige Citadel/Batallia Downs/the Rolanberry Fields/Sauromugue Champaign/Jugner Forest/Pashhow Marshlands/the Meriphataud Mountains/Vunkerl Inlet/Grauberg/Fort Karugo-Narugo/East Ronfaure/North Gustaberg/West Sarutabaruta].
        WE_HAVE_RECEIVED_UNCONFIRMED_REPORTS_THAT_A_SMALL                     = 12856,  -- We have received unconfirmed reports that a small-sized Dark Kindred force is stationed in [Xarcabard/Beaucedine Glacier/The Eldieme Necropolis/Crawlers' Nest/Garlaige Citadel/Batallia Downs/the Rolanberry Fields/Sauromugue Champaign/Jugner Forest/Pashhow Marshlands/the Meriphataud Mountains/Vunkerl Inlet/Grauberg/Fort Karugo-Narugo/East Ronfaure/North Gustaberg/West Sarutabaruta].
        WE_HAVE_RECEIVED_UNCONFIRMED_REPORTS_THAT_A_BEASTMAN                  = 12857,  -- We have received unconfirmed reports that a Beastman supply convoy has been spotted in [Xarcabard/Beaucedine Glacier/The Eldieme Necropolis/Crawlers' Nest/Garlaige Citadel/Batallia Downs/the Rolanberry Fields/Sauromugue Champaign/Jugner Forest/Pashhow Marshlands/the Meriphataud Mountains/Vunkerl Inlet/Grauberg/Fort Karugo-Narugo/East Ronfaure/North Gustaberg/West Sarutabaruta].
        WELL_THAT_LL_DO_ER_S_ALL_WE                                           = 12858,  -- Well, that'll do 'er. S'all we got. Now's your time to shine, %. Get them tactical juices flowin'!
        WHERE_DO_YOU_WANT_US_TO_SEND_A                                        = 12859,  -- Where do you want us to send a supply convoy?
        WHERE_WOULD_YOU_SEND_THE_SUPPLY_CONVOY_XARCABARD                      = 12860,  -- Where would you send the supply convoy? Xarcabard. Beaucedine Glacier. The Eldieme Necropolis. Crawlers' Nest. Garlaige Citadel. Batallia Downs. Rolanberry Fields. Sauromugue Champaign. Jugner Forest. Pashhow Marshlands. Meriphataud Mountains. Vunkerl Inlet. Grauberg. Fort Karugo-Narugo. East Ronfaure. North Gustaberg. West Sarutabaruta.
        EASY_ENOUGH_NEXT_HOW_MUCH_CARGO_DO_YOU                                = 12861,  -- Easy enough. Next, how much cargo do you figure we should load 'em up with?
        OF_COURSE_BEING_THE_BRANIAC_THAT_YOU_ARE                              = 12862,  -- Of course, being the braniac that you are, you realize that the more supplies there are, the happier the troops on site will be.
        WHAT_AMOUNT_DO_YOU_RECOMMEND_A_LARGE_AMOUNT                           = 12863,  -- What amount do you recommend? A large amount. A moderate amount. A small amount.
        FAIR_ENOUGH_THERE_S_A_COUPLE_OF_DIFFERENT                             = 12864,  -- Fair enough. There's a couple of different ways to get from Point A to Point B. What type of route do you suggest?
        WHICH_ROUTE_DO_YOU_ENDORSE_THE_QUICKEST_SHORTEST                      = 12865,  -- Which route do you endorse? The quickest, shortest route possible. The normal route used in peacetime. The safest detouring route.
        EVERY_CONVOY_S_GOTTA_BE_PROTECTED_HOW_LARGE                           = 12866,  -- Every convoy's gotta be protected. How large an escort force do you reckon we oughta send?
        WHAT_SIZE_ESCORT_DO_YOU_RECKON_A_MEDIUM                               = 12867,  -- What size escort do you reckon? A medium-sized force. A small-sized force. A minimum-sized force.
        THAT_LEAVES_ONE_LAST_ISSUE_WE_HAVE_TO                                 = 12868,  -- That leaves one last issue. We have to issue orders for a course of conduct just in case the convoy runs into some beastmen. Whaddya say?
        FIGHT_OR_FLIGHT_ENGAGE_IN_OPEN_BATTLE_AVOID                           = 12869,  -- Fight or flight? Engage in open battle. Avoid conflict at all cost.
        ALRIGHT_THAT_S_ALL_FROM_THIS_END_SURE                                 = 12870,  -- Alright, that's all from this end. Sure you don't wanna change any of your orders before I run them up to high command?
        EDIT_YOUR_SUBMISSION_NO_IT_S_SOLID_ON                                 = 12871,  -- Edit your submission? No, it's solid. On second thought, yes.
        GREAT_LESS_WORK_FOR_ME_I_LL_TRY                                       = 12872,  -- Great, less work for me. I'll try and get your strategy here put in place for tomorrow's mission.
        SINCE_YOU_RE_THE_BRAINS_BEHIND_THIS_OPERATION                         = 12873,  -- Since you're the brains behind this operation, you'd better head on over to the target stronghold and watch over things. Make sure it's carried out all proper and whatnot.
        LET_S_DO_THIS_THING_MAY_THE_GODDESS                                   = 12874,  -- Let's do this thing. May the Goddess be with us all.
        WHAT_NOW_GET_ON_OVER_TO_THAT_STRONGHOLD                               = 12875,  -- What now? Get on over to that stronghold and get your watch on!
        YOU_HAND_THE_CLERK_THE_AND_GIL_AND                                    = 12876,  -- You hand the clerk the % and # gil, and your set of armor is returned.
        HELLO_SIR_MA_AM_HAVE_YOU_EVER_FOUND                                   = 12877,  -- Hello, sir/ma'am]. Have you ever found yourself throwing away items because your Mog Safe is overflowing with dusty sets of armor collected on your many adventures? My colleagues and I have heard the cries of our fellow adventurers and joined together to aid all those in need.
        TRADE_ME_A_FULL_SET_AND_FOR_A                                         = 12878,  -- Trade me a full set, and for a small fee (payable on pickup) we will hold on to it, all the while protecting it from thieves, moths, and any/all acts of god and/or goddess.
        PLEASE_BE_FOREWARNED_THAT_WE_CANNOT_STORE_ANY                         = 12879,  -- Please be forewarned that we cannot store any high-quality equipment, and that the signatures on any pieces of collected armor will be lost.
        HOW_MAY_I_BE_OF_SERVICE_TODAY                                         = 12880,  -- How may I be of service today?
        WHAT_TO_DO_NOTHING_VIEW_LIST_OF_STORABLE                              = 12881,  -- What to do... Nothing. View list of storable armor sets. Have stored armor returned.
        WE_ARE_CURRENTLY_OFFERING_STORAGE_SERVICE_FOR_THE                     = 12882,  -- We are currently offering storage service for the following armor sets:
        LET_ME_SEE_AH_YES_LORD_LADY_WE                                        = 12883,  -- Let me see... Ah yes, Lord/Lady] %. We are currently holding the following garments...
        NONE_LEVEL_24_30_ARMOR_LEVEL_31_40                                    = 12884,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set from storage?] None. Level 24`30 armor. Level 31`40 armor. Level 41`50 armor. Artifact armor/High level gear. Relic armor.
        NONE_IRON_CHAINMAIL_SHADE_HARNESS_BRASS_SCALE_ARMOR                   = 12885,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None. Iron Chainmail. Shade Harness. Brass Scale Armor. Wool Robe. Eisenplatte Armor. Soil Gi. Seer's Tunic. Studded Armor. Centurion's Scale Mail. Mercenary Captain's Doublet. Garish Tunic. Noct Doublet.
        NONE_CUSTOM_ARMOR_HUME_MALE_CUSTOM_ARMOR_HUME                         = 12886,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None. Custom Armor (Hume Male). Custom Armor (Hume Female). Magna Armor (Elvaan Male). Magna Armor (Elvaan Female). Wonder Armor (Tarutaru). Savage Armor (Mithra). Elder Armor (Galka). Linen Cloak. Padded Armor. Silver Chainmail. Gambison. Iron Scale Armor. Cuir Armor. Velvet Robe. Opaline Dress. Royal Squire's Chainmail. Plate Armor. Combat Caster's Cloak. Argent Attire.
        NONE_ALUMINE_HAUBERT_CARAPACE_ARMOR_BANDED_MAIL_HARA                  = 12887,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None. Alumine Haubert. Carapace Armor. Banded Mail. Hara-Ate. Raptor Armor. Steel Scale Armor. Wool Gambison. Shinobi Gi. Mythril Plate Armor. Iron Musketeer's Cuirass. Tactician Magician's Cloak. White Cloak. Austere Robe. Crow Jupon.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS                          = 12888,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, %, %, %, and %.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_2                        = 12889,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, %, %, and %.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_3                        = 12890,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, %, %, and %.
        THIS_SET_IS_COMPRISED_OF_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_4                        = 12891,  -- This set is comprised of the following items: %, and %.
        A_STORAGE_FEE_OF_GIL_WILL_BE_REQUIRED                                 = 12892,  -- A storage fee of # gil will be required upon pickup of this particular set.
        NONE_AT_THIS_TIME_FIGHTER_S_ARMOR_TEMPLE                              = 12893,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None at this time. Fighter's Armor. Temple Attire. Healer's Attire. Wizard's Attire. Warlock's Armor. Rogue's Attire. Gallant Armor. Chaos Armor. Beast Armor. Choral Attire. Hunter's Attire. Myochin Armor. Ninja Garb. Drachen Armor. Evoker's Attire. Magus Attire. Corsair's Attire. Puppetry Attire. Dancer's Attire. Dancer's Attire. Scholar's Attire. Amir Armor Set. Pahluwan Armor Set. Yigit Armor Set.
        THE_STORAGE_FEE_FOR_YOUR_ARMOR_COMES_TO                               = 12894,  -- The storage fee for your armor comes to # gil.
        DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PAY_THE_FEE_NOT                                        = 12895,  -- Do you wish to pay the fee? Not at this time. Yes.
        I_AM_SORRY_SIR_MA_AM_GIL_IS                                           = 12896,  -- I am sorry, sir/ma'am]. # gil is required before we can return your armor.
        VERY_WELL_SIR_MA_AM_WHEN_YOU_WISH                                     = 12897,  -- Very well, sir/ma'am]. When you wish to have your armor returned, remember to present this claim slip along with the #-gil storage fee at any of our five convenient pickup locations around Vana'diel.
        REGULATIONS_DO_NOT_ALLOW_ADVENTURERS_TO_STORE_MORE                    = 12898,  -- Regulations do not allow adventurers to store more than one set of the same armor.
        THE_ITEMS_YOU_ATTEMPTED_TO_TRADE_HAVE_BEEN                            = 12899,  -- The items you attempted to trade have been returned.
        NONE_AT_THIS_TIME_WARRIOR_S_ARMOR_MELEE                               = 12900,  -- [View which set?/Remove which set?] None at this time. Warrior's Armor. Melee Attire. Cleric's Attire. Sorcerer's Attire. Duelist's Armor. Assassin's Attire. Valor Armor. Abyss Armor. Monster Armor. Bard's Attire. Scout's Attire. Saotome Armor. Koga Garb. Wyrm Armor. Summoner's Attire. Mirage Attire. Commodore Attire. Pantin Attire. Etoile Attire. Argute Attire.
        DEBUG_PRESS_A_KEY_TO_CONTINUE                                         = 12901,  -- DEBUG: Press a key to continue.
        ID_12902                                                              = 12902,  -- @@
        HEAR_ME_MY_FELLOW_GALKA_FOR_FAR_TOO                                   = 12903,  -- Hear me, my fellow Galka. For far too long have we lived under the oppressive rule of the Humes. In the name of their twisted justice, at this very moment one of our own is being accused of a crime he did not commit.
        WE_ALL_KNOW_THIS_HERO_S_NAME_DO                                       = 12904,  -- We all know this hero's name, do we not?
        PALE_EAGLE                                                            = 12905,  -- Pale Eagle!!!
        WILL_WE_STAND_BY_AND_WATCH_AS_PALE                                    = 12906,  -- Will we stand by and watch as Pale Eagle suffers the same humiliation to which our comrades, Werei and Gumbah, were subjected?
        NO_WE_WILL_NOT                                                        = 12907,  -- No!!! We will not!!!
        I_THANK_YOU_MY_BROTHERS_YOUR_SUPPORT_IS                               = 12908,  -- I thank you, my brothers. Your support is indispensable in this dark hour.
        IT_IS_TIME_TIME_FOR_THE_GALKAN_RACE                                   = 12909,  -- It is time... Time for the Galkan race to rise up and break free from our shackles.
        JUST_LIKE_THE_TIME_WHEN_THE_HERO_DARKSTEEL                            = 12910,  -- Just like the time when the hero, Darksteel Hurricane, stood up against the tyranny of the Humes so many years ago!
        HURRAH                                                                = 12911,  -- Hurrah!!!
        WHAT_IS_THE_MEANING_OF_THIS_UNAUTHORIZED_PUBLIC                       = 12912,  -- What is the meaning of this? Unauthorized public gatherings are strictly prohibited!
        I_TAKE_IT_YOU_RE_THE_LEADER_OF                                        = 12913,  -- I take it you're the leader of this rabble? Adjourn this illegal gathering immediately! Or else--
        HM                                                                    = 12914,  -- Hm?
        YOU_I_KNOW_YOUR_FACE_WHY_YOU_RE                                       = 12915,  -- You... I know your face... Why, you're a Mythril Musketeer! Explain yourself this instant!
        SEE_FOR_YOURSELVES_MY_FELLOW_GALKA                                    = 12916,  -- See for yourselves, my fellow Galka!
        THIS_IS_THE_HUMES_TWISTED_NOTION_OF_JUSTICE                           = 12917,  -- This is the Humes' twisted notion of justice! Their mouths spew forth the law, while their hands reach for a blade!
        THE_ONES_WHO_UNJUSTLY_IMPRISONED_WEREI_AND_GUMBAH                     = 12918,  -- The ones who unjustly imprisoned Werei and Gumbah are none other than the self-proclaimed military police standing here before you!
        SCOUNDRELS                                                            = 12919,  -- Scoundrels!
        DON_T_THINK_WE_LL_STAND_QUIETLY_BY                                    = 12920,  -- Don't think we'll stand quietly by and let you military police dogs frame our respected Chairman Pale Eagle as well!
        S_STAND_DOWN_STAND_DOWN_I_SAY_DON                                     = 12921,  -- S-stand down! Stand down, I say! Don't do anything stupid!
        THAT_S_ENOUGH_FUN_AND_GAMES                                           = 12922,  -- That's enough fun and games.
        ZEID_I_KNEW_YOU_D_COME                                                = 12923,  -- Zeid! I knew you'd come!
        ID_12924                                                              = 12924,  -- !?
        ZEID_WHAT_IS_THE_MEANING_OF_THIS                                      = 12925,  -- Zeid!? What is the meaning of this?
        MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_FIVE_MOONS_YOU_ARE_UNDER_ARREST                     = 12926,  -- Mythril Musketeer Five Moons. You are under arrest for treason and slander.
        IS_THIS_A_JOKE_THE_ONES_WHO_BROUGHT                                   = 12927,  -- Is this a joke!? The ones who brought forth false accusations against Chairman Pale Eagle should be arrested, not I! Am I not right, Zeid?
        ID_12928                                                              = 12928,  -- ...
        ZEID_2                                                                = 12929,  -- Zeid...?
        THIS_LOOSE_CANNON_OF_YOURS_IS_A_DISGRACE                              = 12930,  -- This loose cannon of yours is a disgrace to the Mythril Musketeers. Our superiors will hear of this, make no mistake about it.
        FEEL_FREE_TO_DO_AS_YOU_PLEASE                                         = 12931,  -- Feel free to do as you please.
        NEEDLESS_TO_SAY_CONSIDERING_HIS_ROLE_AS_THE                           = 12932,  -- Needless to say, considering his role as the ringleader, he'll be taken into our custody. I trust there will not be any objections.
        ZEID_IS_THERE_NOT_A_SPECK_OF_GALKAN                                   = 12933,  -- Zeid! Is there not a speck of Galkan pride left in you?
        PRIDE_YOU_SAY_I_HAVE_PRIDE_IN_WHAT                                    = 12934,  -- Pride, you say? I have pride in what I do, not who I am.
        I_CAN_T_BELIEVE_I_M_HEARING_THIS                                      = 12935,  -- I can't believe I'm hearing this from you--a Galka!
        WHAT_IS_THE_SOURCE_OF_THIS_COMMOTION                                  = 12936,  -- What is the source of this commotion?
        YOUR_EXCELLENCY_THIS_MAN_HAS_BEEN_ARRESTED_FOR                        = 12937,  -- Your Excellency, this man has been arrested for inciting rebellious sentiments within young Galka.
        HMM_THIS_IS_DISCONCERTING_INDEED                                      = 12938,  -- Hmm, this is disconcerting indeed.
        WHY_THIS_IS_A_FAMILIAR_FACE_IF_MY                                     = 12939,  -- Why, this is a familiar face. If my memory serves me correctly, you are Mythril Musketeer Five M--
        GALAGG_THE_NAME_S_GALAGG_AND_DON_T                                    = 12940,  -- Galagg! The name's Galagg, and don't you forget it!
        I_M_WARNING_YOU_KARST_THIS_ISN_T                                      = 12941,  -- I'm warning you, Karst: This isn't over. We Galka will not stand idly by while the chairman has his honor defaced. Even if you lock me up, someone else will rise in my place and--
        MIND_YOUR_MANNERS_BEFORE_THE_SENATOR                                  = 12942,  -- Mind your manners before the senator!
        UGH                                                                   = 12943,  -- Ugh!
        THAT_S_ENOUGH_OFFICER_VIOLENCE_WILL_NOT_BE                            = 12944,  -- That's enough, officer! Violence will not be tolerated, not even towards detainees and prisoners!
        I_I_BEG_YOUR_PARDON_YOUR_EXCELLENCY                                   = 12945,  -- I-I beg your pardon, Your Excellency.
        NOW_GALAGG_WAS_IT                                                     = 12946,  -- Now, Galagg, was it?
        I_DEREK_KARST_WILL_SPEAK_WITH_CHAIRMAN_PALE                           = 12947,  -- I, Derek Karst, will speak with Chairman Pale Eagle in person and confirm the truth for myself. This, I solemnly promise.
        TAKE_HIM_AWAY                                                         = 12948,  -- Take him away!
        AH_2                                                                  = 12949,  -- Ah, %.
        I_M_SORRY_YOU_HAD_TO_WITNESS_WHAT                                     = 12950,  -- I'm sorry you had to witness what just transpired.
        IN_AN_UNFORTUNATE_TURN_OF_EVENTS_SUSPICION_OVER                       = 12951,  -- In an unfortunate turn of events, suspicion over the plot behind Senator Werner's assassination has been cast upon Chairman Pale Eagle.
        WE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_WERE_GIVEN_ORDERS_TO_CONDUCT                    = 12952,  -- We Mythril Musketeers were given orders to conduct a preliminary investigation.
        WHILE_FIVE_MOONS_HAD_BEEN_OBSERVED_VOICING_HIS                        = 12953,  -- While Five Moons had been observed voicing his belief in Chairman Pale Eagle's innocence with increasing fervor, no one thought much of it. Until one day he disappears from headquarters all together. The rest, well, you've seen with your own eyes.
        NICOLAUS_WE_NEED_TO_FOCUS_ON_THE_TASK                                 = 12954,  -- Nicolaus, we need to focus on the task at hand.
        WITH_REGARDS_TO_THE_REASON_BEHIND_FIVE_MOON                           = 12955,  -- With regards to the reason behind Five Moon's sudden change of heart, do we have anything to speculate upon?
        ACTUALLY_WE_FOUND_A_BOOK_LYING_IN_HIS                                 = 12956,  -- Actually, we found a book lying in his room--one that's been causing quite a stir recently.
        A_BOOK_YOU_SAY                                                        = 12957,  -- A book, you say?
        IT_S_A_CHRONICLED_ACCOUNT_OF_THE_UNSUCCESSFUL                         = 12958,  -- It's a chronicled account of the unsuccessful attempts to capture Darksteel Hurricane, the infamous assassin who shook the very foundation of the Republic several years back.
        IT_WOULD_APPEAR_THAT_THIS_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_HAS                     = 12959,  -- It would appear that this Darksteel Hurricane has attained cult status as of late. He's idolized among the younger generation of Galka as a hero and role model.
        OF_ALL_PEOPLE_THEY_CHOOSE_TO_IDOLIZE_A                                = 12960,  -- Of all people, they choose to idolize a murderer... Nicolaus, we're going.
        NOW_IF_YOU_LL_EXCUSE_US                                               = 12961,  -- Now, if you'll excuse us, %.
        OH_IT_S_YOU_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR                                        = 12962,  -- Oh, it's you. You're looking for Captain Klara?
        SHE_S_RECEIVING_A_GUEST_RIGHT_NOW_SENATOR                             = 12963,  -- She's receiving a guest right now. Senator Karst, in fact.
        I_WAS_SPECIFICALLY_INSTRUCTED_NOT_TO_LET_ANYONE                       = 12964,  -- I was specifically instructed not to let anyone through...but hey, it's you!
        SIR_I_BESEECH_YOU_TO_RECONSIDER                                       = 12965,  -- Sir, I beseech you to reconsider.
        CHAIRMAN_PALE_EAGLE_HASN_T_YET_BEEN_CLEARED                           = 12966,  -- Chairman Pale Eagle hasn't yet been cleared of suspicion. Meeting with him alone under these circumstances would be ill-advised.
        I_AM_NOT_UNMINDFUL_OF_YOUR_CONCERN_CAPTAIN                            = 12967,  -- I am not unmindful of your concern, Captain. But I must honor the promise I made to your man to seek out the truth for myself.
        IF_I_CANNOT_DISSUADE_YOUR_EXCELLENCY_PLEASE_GRANT                     = 12968,  -- If I cannot dissuade Your Excellency, please grant me permission to accompany you.
        WHILE_I_APPRECIATE_YOUR_COMMITMENT_I_CANNOT_ALLOW                     = 12969,  -- While I appreciate your commitment, I cannot allow it. This meeting at Zegham Hill must be between only myself and the chairman.
        BUT_SIR_WITH_BEASTMAN_FORCES_PROWLING_THE_GUSTABERG                   = 12970,  -- But sir, with beastman forces prowling the Gustaberg region, precautions must be taken--
        THIS_DISCUSSION_IS_OVER_CAPTAIN_THIS_MATTER_IS                        = 12971,  -- This discussion is over, Captain. This matter is to be kept in the strictest confidence.
        THIS_APPLIES_TO_YOU_TOO_ADVENTURER                                    = 12972,  -- This applies to you too, adventurer.
        Y_YOUR_EXCELLENCY                                                     = 12973,  -- Y-Your Excellency...
        CAPTAIN_IS_IT_TRUE_FIVE_MOONS_IS_BEING                                = 12974,  -- Captain! Is it true Five Moons is being detained by the military police!?
        I_M_AFRAID_SO                                                         = 12975,  -- I'm afraid so.
        THE_NEW_FIVE_MOONS_IS_A_GREAT_DEAL                                    = 12976,  -- The new Five Moons is a great deal more stubborn than the one we used to know. He has been maintaining his silence since arrest. Continuing to do so would be tantamount to admitting his own guilt.
        DAMN_IT                                                               = 12977,  -- Damn it!
        VOLKER_WHERE_DO_YOU_THINK_YOU_RE_GOING                                = 12978,  -- Volker, where do you think you're going?
        I_M_GOING_TO_GO_SLAP_SOME_SENSE                                       = 12979,  -- I'm going to go slap some sense back into Five Moons and then bring him back.
        YOU_D_ONLY_BE_WASTING_YOUR_TIME_ONLY                                  = 12980,  -- You'd only be wasting your time. Only Captain Klara has authorization from the military police to meet with Five Moons. Furthermore, it wouldn't be in their best interest to release him.
        CAPTAIN_WHAT_DO_YOU_PROPOSE                                           = 12981,  -- Captain, what do you propose...
        FIVE_MOON_S_CHARGES_ARE_SERIOUS_IF_THEY                               = 12982,  -- Five Moon's charges are serious. If they stick, I would be forced to dismiss him from the Mythril Musketeers, to say nothing of the hefty sentence should he be convicted.
        IF_HE_DOES_NOT_BREAK_HIS_SILENCE_AND                                  = 12983,  -- If he does not break his silence--and soon--there's precious little I can do for him.
        LEAVE_HIM_BE_VOLKER_HE_CLEARLY_HAS_HIS                                = 12984,  -- Leave him be, Volker. He clearly has his sights set on martyrdom. There's no point going against that wish.
        ZEID_YOU_OF_ALL_PEOPLE                                                = 12985,  -- Zeid! You, of all people...
        HM_I_JUST_HAD_A_THOUGHT_CAPTAIN_IF                                    = 12986,  -- Hm... I just had a thought. Captain, if I may.
        IF_THE_ALLEGATIONS_OF_CHAIRMAN_PALE_EAGLE_S                           = 12987,  -- If the allegations of Chairman Pale Eagle's involvement in the assassination is disproved, wouldn't the charges being brought against Five Moons be lightened, even if nullification is out of the question?
        ID_12988                                                              = 12988,  -- ...!
        I_HAVE_A_FAVOR_TO_ASK_OF_YOU                                          = 12989,  -- %. I have a favor to ask of you.
        I_WANT_YOU_TO_ACCOMPANY_VOLKER_TO_SENATOR                             = 12990,  -- I want you to accompany Volker to Senator Karst's meeting with Chairman Pale Eagle.
        CAPTAIN_2                                                             = 12991,  -- Captain...?
        REPUBLICAN_LAW_RECOGNIZES_THE_GRAVITY_OF_THIRD_PARTY                  = 12992,  -- Republican law recognizes the gravity of third-party evidence.
        THEREFORE_IF_ANY_FRUIT_COMES_OF_THE_SECRET                            = 12993,  -- Therefore, if any fruit comes of the secret meeting at Zegham Hill and the chairman's involvement in the assassination is disproved...
        YOUR_PRESENCE_AS_EYEWITNESS_MAY_BE_PIVOTAL_IN                         = 12994,  -- Your presence as eyewitness may be pivotal in the case for Five Moons.
        PREPARE_FOR_IMMEDIATE_DEPARTURE_VOLKER_IT_WAS_A                       = 12995,  -- Prepare for immediate departure, Volker. It was a mistake allowing the senator to leave unescorted. Should anything run afoul, protect His Excellency with your life.
        I_MUST_FIRST_ATTEND_TO_FIVE_MOONS_I                                   = 12996,  -- I must first attend to Five Moons. I will be right behind you, %.
        IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_SENATOR_KARST_HE                                = 12997,  -- If you're looking for Senator Karst, he's already left for his meeting with Chairman Pale Eagle at Zegham Hill in North Gustaberg.
        TERRIBLE_NEWS_FIVE_MOONS_HAS_BROKEN_OUT_OF                            = 12998,  -- Terrible news! Five Moons has broken out of jail!
        I_HATE_TO_IMAGINE_WHAT_WOULD_HAPPEN_IF                                = 12999,  -- I hate to imagine what would happen if we don't find him before the military police do. We're counting on you, Detective %!
        COMRADE_GALAGG                                                        = 13000,  -- Comrade Galagg!
        I_VE_SUCCESSFULLY_DETAINED_MY_HUME_SUPERIOR_OFFICER                   = 13001,  -- I've successfully detained my Hume superior officer in the Musketeer ranks!
        GOOD_WORK_COMRADE_GHIOGGO_AND_DONE_MOST_EXPEDITIOUSLY                 = 13002,  -- Good work, Comrade Ghioggo, and done most expeditiously. And what of our own?
        REGRETFULLY_A_SMALL_HANDFUL_OF_OUR_BROTHERS_REFUSED                   = 13003,  -- Regretfully, a small handful of our brothers refused to join the cause. They, too, have been detained as you ordered.
        THAT_IS_MOST_UNFORTUNATE_BUT_THOSE_WHO_DON                            = 13004,  -- That is most unfortunate... But those who don't know true freedom cannot be blamed for their actions. I will speak with them myself when the time is right.
        FIVE_MOONS_CEASE_THIS_FOLLY_THIS_INSTANT                              = 13005,  -- Five Moons! Cease this folly this instant!
        VOLKER_2                                                              = 13006,  -- Volker...
        CAN_T_YOU_SEE_THAT_YOUR_ACTIONS_SERVE                                 = 13007,  -- Can't you see that your actions serve only to smear shame upon Galkan honor?
        LISTEN_TO_ME_WITH_CAPTAIN_KLARA_S_BACKING                             = 13008,  -- Listen to me. With Captain Klara's backing, we can make a direct appeal to the president. We have an honest chance of--
        ID_13009                                                              = 13009,  -- !?
        FIVE_MOONS_IS_IT_YOUR_INTENTION_TO_DETAIN                             = 13010,  -- Five Moons, is it your intention to detain me also?
        AFTER_ALL_WE_VE_BEEN_THROUGH_TO_YOU                                   = 13011,  -- After all we've been through, to you, am I no different from all the other Humes!?
        TROUBLING_NEWS_COMRADE_GALAGG                                         = 13012,  -- Troubling news, Comrade Galagg!
        WHAT_IS_IT_COMRADE_DABEM                                              = 13013,  -- What is it, Comrade Dabem?
        WE_VE_JUST_RECEIVED_WORD_THAT_OUR_REGIMENT                            = 13014,  -- We've just received word that our regiment patrolling North Gustaberg has been set upon by the Quadav Elite Guard, and is currently retreating for the capital.
        HMPH_THAT_WOULD_BE_THE_REGIMENT_GIVEN_TO                              = 13015,  -- Hmph. That would be the regiment given to the care of Glenagg. It seems the task was beyond one with his meager experience.
        WHAT_ARE_THE_ENEMY_NUMBERS                                            = 13016,  -- What are the enemy numbers?
        THE_QUADAVS_ARE_ESTIMATED_TO_BE_BETWEEN_TWO                           = 13017,  -- The Quadavs are estimated to be between two to three thousand shells strong, and are marching straight for the capital at this very moment!
        WHAT_B_BUT_WE_HAVE_NOT_MORE_THAN                                      = 13018,  -- What!? B-but we have not more than a few units under our command that can be mobilized!
        WHAT_WILL_WE_DO_COMRADE_GALAGG                                        = 13019,  -- What will we do, Comrade Galagg?
        WHY_THIS_IS_OUR_LONG_AWAITED_CHANCE                                   = 13020,  -- Why, this is our long-awaited chance...
        LET_THE_TURTLEBACKS_COME_IN_THEIR_TENS_OF                             = 13021,  -- Let the turtlebacks come in their tens of thousands--it makes no difference to us. We, the Galka, will repel their offensive and show the cowardly Humes the true meaning of courage!
        F_FIVE_MOONS                                                          = 13022,  -- F-Five Moons...
        CHAAAAAARGE                                                           = 13023,  -- Chaaaaaarge!!!
        ID_13024                                                              = 13024,  -- !!!
        VOLKER_3                                                              = 13025,  -- Volker!
        CAPTAIN_WHAT_WAS_THAT_THUNDEROUS_EXPLOSION                            = 13026,  -- Captain...! What was that thunderous explosion?
        THE_QUADAV_SHIELDWARRIORS_ARE_BOMBARDING_US_WITH_THEIR                = 13027,  -- The Quadav Shieldwarriors are bombarding us with their siege turrets.
        SIEGE_TURRETS_BUT_HOW_DID_THEY_SO_QUICKLY                             = 13028,  -- Siege turrets!? But how did they so quickly prepare for siege warfare?
        THE_SIEGE_TURRETS_WERE_STOCKPILED_WITHIN_A_NEARBY                     = 13029,  -- The siege turrets were stockpiled within a nearby abandoned mine. We must destroy them, or else the city will be reduced to piles of rubble.
        BUT_FIVE_MOONS_IS_STILL                                               = 13030,  -- But, Five Moons is still--
        LEAVE_HIM_BE_HE_HAS_ABANDONED_THE_MYTHRIL                             = 13031,  -- Leave him be. He has abandoned the Mythril Musketeers, and his welfare is no longer our concern.
        I_TRULY_UNDERSTAND_HOW_YOU_FEEL_VOLKER_BUT                            = 13032,  -- I truly understand how you feel, Volker, but we're racing against time.
        THAT_BOMBARDMENT_WAS_MERELY_A_PREPARATORY_DISCHARGE_FROM              = 13033,  -- That bombardment was merely a preparatory discharge from no more than three turrets.
        THAT_IS_NOT_AN_UNREASONABLE_AMOUNT_WITH_WHICH                         = 13034,  -- That is not an unreasonable amount with which to deal for Five Moons and his outfit.
        WHILE_FIVE_MOONS_HOLDS_BACK_THE_ENEMY_OFFENSIVE                       = 13035,  -- While Five Moons holds back the enemy offensive, we make for the Ruhotz Silvermines. Zeid has reason to believe it is there that a great many more siege turrets have been stashed.
        I_KNOW_NOT_WHY_THE_REMAINING_TURRETS_HAVE                             = 13036,  -- I know not why the remaining turrets have yet to be included in the Quadav offensive, but I dread to imagine the carnage should they be brought to the battlefront.
        THE_SIEGE_TURRETS_MUST_BE_DESTROYED_BEFORE_THEY                       = 13037,  -- The siege turrets must be destroyed before they can be employed against us.
        CAPTAIN_HOW_WILL_THIS_OPERATION_BE_CONDUCTED                          = 13038,  -- Captain, how will this operation be conducted?
        THE_SIEGE_TURRETS_ARE_TAUTLY_LINED_WITH_ANIMAL                        = 13039,  -- The siege turrets are tautly lined with animal hide, making them extremely fire-resistant. We will need to use ignis powder to destroy them.
        IGNIS_POWDER_DEFINITELY_NOT_SOMETHING_YOU_LEARN_ABOUT                 = 13040,  -- Ignis powder... Definitely not something you learn about in alchemy class.
        DUE_TO_THE_NOT_INCONSIDERABLE_RISK_INVOLVED_IF                        = 13041,  -- Due to the not inconsiderable risk involved if the substance were to be placed in the hands of laymen, we will be recruiting the services of the Special Operations Squadron in this particular mission. No one can handle explosives as fleetly and safely as they.
        SPECIAL_OPERATIONS_SQUADRON_THE_SITUATION_IS_INDEED_GRAVE             = 13042,  -- Special Operations Squadron... The situation is indeed grave when the SOS call is made. That leaves the matter of ignis powder procurement.
        THE_PRESIDENT_HIMSELF_IS_SEEING_TO_THE_RELEASE                        = 13043,  -- The president himself is seeing to the release of ignis powder from the Metalworks' munitions storeroom.
        CAPTAIN_IF_I_MAY_BE_PERMITTED_TO_ASSIST                               = 13044,  -- Captain, if I may be permitted to assist in its transportation? While I do not claim to be an expert on its application, my knowledge will surely be of some use in handling such a volatile substance.
        PERMISSION_GRANTED_ONE_CAN_NEVER_TAKE_TOO_MANY                        = 13045,  -- Permission granted. One can never take too many precautions when it comes to ignis powder.
        AND_WE_WILL_NEED_YOUR_ASSISTANCE_ALSO_DURING                          = 13046,  -- And %, we will need your assistance also during the blasting operation.
        OPERATION_MEMBERS_WILL_REGROUP_WITHIN_THE_RUHOTZ_SILVERMINES          = 13047,  -- Operation members will regroup within the Ruhotz Silvermines, where the remaining siege turrets are hoarded.
        YOU_LL_BE_NEEDING_THIS_KEY_TO_GAIN                                    = 13048,  -- You'll be needing this key to gain entrance. We're relying on you, %.
        ZEID_NICOLAUS_VOLKER_WITH_ME                                          = 13049,  -- Zeid, Nicolaus, Volker! With me!
        GHIOGGO_BE_STRONG_NOW_STAY_WITH_ME                                    = 13050,  -- Ghioggo! Be strong, now! Stay with me!
        C_COMRADE_GALAGG_OUR_DEEDS_THIS_DAY                                   = 13051,  -- C-Comrade Galagg... Our deeds...this day...
        YES_GHIOGGO_ON_THIS_GLORIOUS_DAY_WE_RESTORED                          = 13052,  -- Yes, Ghioggo... On this glorious day, we restored pride and honor to the Galkan name. The tale of your valor will go down in history and be retold for all time.
        I_M_HAPPY_TO_HEAR_THAT                                                = 13053,  -- I'm happy...to hear that...
        TH_THIS_CAN_T_BE_HAPPENING                                            = 13054,  -- Th...this can't be happening...
        NOOOOOOOOO                                                            = 13055,  -- Nooooooooo!!!
        IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS                          = 13056,  -- If you're looking for the Mythril Musketeers, they've left to see to the deployment of the Special Ops crew. The captain is expecting you at the Ruhotz Silvermines, so off you go now.
        HOW_MANY_TIMES_DO_I_HAVE_TO_TELL                                      = 13057,  -- How many times do I have to tell you, he's not here! By now Comrade Galagg would have detained all Hume officers and seized all key facilities in the Republic.
        THAT_RASH_YOUNG_FOOL_HURRY_AND_TAKE_ME                                = 13058,  -- That rash young fool... Hurry and take me to him!
        ID_13059                                                              = 13059,  -- !?
        WHAT_IN_THE_WORLD                                                     = 13060,  -- What in the world!?
        WEREI                                                                 = 13061,  -- Werei!
