        W_WE_WERE_COMPLETELY_OUTNUMBERED_WE_DON_T                             = 13063,  -- W-we were completely outnumbered. We don't know how much longer these gates will hold...
        ID_13064                                                              = 13064,  -- ...!
        WEREI_LOOK_OVER_THERE                                                 = 13065,  -- Werei, look over there!
        HUH_THE_HUMES_HAVE_BEEN_SET_FREE_HAS                                  = 13066,  -- Huh? The Humes have been set free!? Has something happened to Comrade Galagg?
        ALL_OF_YOU_LISTEN_UP_AND_LISTEN_WELL                                  = 13067,  -- All of you, listen up and listen well! These Hume officers have been released from detainment.
        BE_ASSURED_THAT_I_HAVE_NOT_FORGOTTEN_THE                              = 13068,  -- Be assured that I have not forgotten the ill feeling you hold towards the Humes.
        BUT_NO_MATTER_HOW_LITTLE_LOVE_THERE_MAY                               = 13069,  -- But no matter how little love there may be between our two races, Bastok is our homeland, built brick by brick with the blood and sweat of our displaced Galkan ancestors who crossed the seas in search of a safe haven.
        NOW_IS_THE_TIME_TO_CAST_ASIDE_OUR                                     = 13070,  -- Now is the time to cast aside our differences and unite under one banner to protect our homeland!
        HURRAH_2                                                              = 13071,  -- Hurrah!!!
        WHAT_RE_YOU_LOITERING_AROUND_HERE_FOR_PRESIDENT                       = 13072,  -- What're you loitering around here for? President Prien's about to make an official statement, so head over to the President's Office right now!
        THANKS_TO_YOUR_SELFLESS_DISPLAY_OF_COURAGE_THE                        = 13073,  -- ...Thanks to your selfless display of courage, the greatest danger ever faced by our nation since its founding has successfully been averted.
        IT_IS_WITH_SUPREME_JUBILATION_THAT_I_NOW                              = 13074,  -- It is with supreme jubilation that I now stand before you and make this declaration: We have triumphed over the Quadav!
        BUT_OF_COURSE_THIS_VICTORY_WAS_NOT_WITHOUT                            = 13075,  -- But of course, this victory was not without cost. We must never forget our comrades who gave their lives in the line of duty, nor the innocent citizens who fell to the indiscriminate onslaught of the beastmen.
        PLEASE_JOIN_ME_NOW_IN_A_MOMENT_OF                                     = 13076,  -- Please join me now in a moment of silent prayer to the memory of those who are no longer with us...
        THANK_YOU                                                             = 13077,  -- Thank you.
        I_WOULD_NOW_LIKE_TO_TAKE_THIS_OPPORTUNITY                             = 13078,  -- I would now like to take this opportunity to make an announcement concerning a matter of great importance. I ask you all to listen well, and with open minds.
        THE_INCIDENT_WHEREIN_SENATOR_WERNER_WAS_BRUTALLY_MURDERED             = 13079,  -- The incident wherein Senator Werner was brutally murdered by a Tonberry assassin...
        I_AM_DEEPLY_ASHAMED_THAT_SUSPICION_BEHIND_THE                         = 13080,  -- I am deeply ashamed that suspicion behind the plot was falsely cast upon a law-abiding leading citizen like Chairman Pale Eagle.
        CHAIRMAN_PALE_EAGLE_IS_INNOCENT                                       = 13081,  -- Chairman Pale Eagle...is innocent?
        WHAT_S_THE_MEANING_OF_THIS                                            = 13082,  -- What's the meaning of this!?
        SENATOR_KARST_IF_YOU_COULD_BE_SO_KIND                                 = 13083,  -- Senator Karst, if you could be so kind?
        LISTEN_TO_WHAT_I_HAVE_TO_SAY_EVERYONE                                 = 13084,  -- Listen to what I have to say, everyone!
        I_MYSELF_WAS_DESIGNATED_THE_NEXT_VICTIM_OF                            = 13085,  -- I myself was designated the next victim of the Tonberry assassin.
        I_WOULD_HAVE_INDEED_SHARED_THE_SAME_FATE                              = 13086,  -- I would have indeed shared the same fate as the late Senator Werner--Goddess rest his soul--had it not been for the heroic sacrifice of Chairman Pale Eagle. It is to him that I owe my life.
        WHAT                                                                  = 13087,  -- What!?
        THE_CHAIRMAN_SAVED_THE_SENATOR_S_LIFE                                 = 13088,  -- The chairman saved the senator's life...?
        THE_PERSON_WHO_BROUGHT_FORTH_THE_ALLEGATIONS_AGAINST                  = 13089,  -- The person who brought forth the allegations against the chairman was none other than myself.
        IN_SPITE_OF_THIS_THE_CHAIRMAN_THREW_HIS                               = 13090,  -- In spite of this, the chairman threw his life on the line to save me, the man who sought to have him removed from his post. Would the real mastermind behind the assassination plot place another's life before his own?
        FOR_THOSE_OF_YOU_WHO_STILL_DOUBT_A                                    = 13091,  -- For those of you who still doubt, a floorplan of the Senator of Defense's office was discovered on the body of the Tonberry assassin. The true culprit behind the assassination has been determined.
        SO_CHAIRMAN_PALE_EAGLE_WAS_INNOCENT_ALL_ALONG                         = 13092,  -- So Chairman Pale Eagle was innocent all along!
        I_AM_UNRESERVEDLY_CONVINCED_OF_THE_CHAIRMAN_S                         = 13093,  -- I am unreservedly convinced of the chairman's innocence. As President, I wish to offer an official apology, and will do my utmost to see him restored to the honored post he so rightly deserves.
        AND_I_PROMISE_SWIFT_AND_FIRM_RETRIBUTION_AGAINST                      = 13094,  -- And I promise swift and firm retribution against the Beastman Confederate who have orchestrated this fiendish plot to destabilize our fair Republic.
        STAND_BY_ME_NOW_FOR_TOGETHER_WE_ARE                                   = 13095,  -- Stand by me now, for together we are strong!
        BUT_YOUR_EXCELLENCY_ALLOWANCES_CANNOT_BE_MADE_FOR                     = 13096,  -- ...But, Your Excellency, allowances cannot be made for charges of such grievous nature.
        YES_OF_THAT_I_AM_AWARE                                                = 13097,  -- Yes, of that I am aware...
        AS_A_REPRESENTATIVE_OF_THE_SECURITY_OFFICE_I                          = 13098,  -- As a representative of the Security Office, I therefore duly request the handover of the suspect, Mythril Musketeer Five Moons.
        IF_YOU_COULD_SPARE_JUST_A_FEW_MOMENTS                                 = 13099,  -- If you could spare just a few moments, I'd like to have a word with him.
        BUT_OF_COURSE_MISTER_PRESIDENT                                        = 13100,  -- But of course, Mister President.
        DO_YOU_HAVE_ANYTHING_TO_SAY_FOR_YOURSELF                              = 13101,  -- Do you have anything to say for yourself?
        I_SEE_SO_IT_IS_YOUR_INTENTION_TO                                      = 13102,  -- I see. So it is your intention to maintain silence to the end and make amends by paying with your life.
        DO_YOU_REALLY_THINK_YOU_CAN_ESCAPE_RESPONSIBILITY                     = 13103,  -- Do you really think you can escape responsibility so easily?
        ID_13104                                                              = 13104,  -- ...!?
        YOU_MAY_THINK_IT_HONORABLE_TO_DIE_BUT                                 = 13105,  -- You may think it honorable to die, but what of those who are left behind?
        WHAT_OF_THE_BEREAVED_FAMILIES_OF_THE_MANY                             = 13106,  -- What of the bereaved families of the many comrades who gladly gave their lives to your cause?
        AND_WHAT_OF_YOUR_FELLOW_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_WHO                        = 13107,  -- And what of your fellow Mythril Musketeers who all this time have been scrambling tirelessly to clear your name? Are they to suffer not only the loss of valuable manpower, but also bear the burden of your tarnished legacy?
        CAPTAIN_KLARA                                                         = 13108,  -- Captain Klara.
        IN_THIS_PERIOD_OF_TURMOIL_IS_IT_NOT                                   = 13109,  -- In this period of turmoil, is it not true that the absence of a single Mythril Musketeer could adversely affect the outcome of battle?
