        HEY_ZEID_ISN_T_THERE_ANYTHING_YOU_WANT                                = 13136,  -- Hey, Zeid. Isn't there anything you want to say to Five Moons?
        HMPH                                                                  = 13137,  -- Hmph...
        THE_SAME_OLD_INDEFATIGABLE_ZEID_IT_SEEMS                              = 13138,  -- The same old indefatigable Zeid, it seems.
        LEAVE_HIM_BE_AS_A_GALKA_ZEID_TOO                                      = 13139,  -- Leave him be. As a Galka, Zeid, too, would have much to think about on the recent happenings.
        NOW_AS_WAS_MENTIONED_BY_THE_PRESIDENT_WE                              = 13140,  -- Now, %. As was mentioned by the president, we would like your continued assistance. Can we count on your help in the upcoming operation?
        GOOD_I_KNEW_WE_COULD_DEPEND_ON_YOU                                    = 13141,  -- Good. I knew we could depend on you. Now, with regards to the next--
        UGH_2                                                                 = 13142,  -- Ugh...!
        CAPTAIN_ARE_YOU_FEELING_UNWELL                                        = 13143,  -- Captain? Are you feeling unwell?
        IT_IT_S_NOTHING_JUST_A_BOUT_OF                                        = 13144,  -- It...it's nothing. Just a bout of dizziness, nothing more...
        YOU_VE_BEEN_OVEREXERTING_YOURSELF_RECENTLY_CAPTAIN_WHY                = 13145,  -- You've been overexerting yourself recently, Captain. Why, I honestly don't recall the last time you were off duty. A good rest is definitely in order.
        YOU_MAY_HAVE_THE_RIGHT_OF_IT_VOLKER                                   = 13146,  -- You may have the right of it... Volker, see to the issues as listed on the agenda in my stead. I will not be absent long...
        UNDERSTOOD_CAPTAIN                                                    = 13147,  -- Understood, Captain.
        LET_S_POSTPONE_THE_BRIEFING_FOR_NOW_AND                               = 13148,  -- %, let's postpone the briefing for now and resume after the captain has sufficiently recovered.
        I_VE_NEVER_SEEN_CAPTAIN_KLARA_IN_SUCH                                 = 13149,  -- I've never seen Captain Klara in such a run-down state before. I hope it's nothing serious...
        OH_AND_I_HEARD_THE_GOOD_NEWS_FROM                                     = 13150,  -- Oh, and I heard the good news from Chief Sturm. Congratulations on being appointed the sixth member of the Mythril Musketeers!
        YOU_VE_MADE_IT_BIG_BUT_DON_T                                          = 13151,  -- You've made it big, but don't forget about the little guys. It may have been gross negligence, but it was I who let you through here in the first place! Come back here to show your appreciation to yours truly from time to time, eh?
        AAAAAAH                                                               = 13152,  -- Aaaaaah!!!
        WH_WHAT_WAS_THAT                                                      = 13153,  -- Wh-what was that!?
        IT_CAME_FROM_OVER_THERE                                               = 13154,  -- It came from over there!
        WHAT_IS_IT_WHAT_S_HAPPENED_2                                          = 13155,  -- What is it!? What's happened!?
        TH_THERE                                                              = 13156,  -- Th-there...
        ID_13157                                                              = 13157,  -- !!!
        IS_HE_D_DEAD                                                          = 13158,  -- Is he...d-dead?
        THE_CUTS_ON_HIS_FOREHEAD_ALMOST_LOOK_LIKE                             = 13159,  -- The cuts on his forehead almost look like a pattern...but where do I know it from?
        AH_I_THINK_I_REMEMBER_NOW_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE                         = 13160,  -- Ah! I think I remember now. Darksteel Hurricane... H-he's back!
        A_ARE_YOU_SERIOUS_WE_HAVE_TO_INFORM                                   = 13161,  -- A-are you serious!? We have to inform the military police right away!
        R_RIGHT_COME_ON_LET_S_GO                                              = 13162,  -- R-right! Come on, let's go!
        THERE_S_STILL_A_HINT_OF_WARMTH_TO                                     = 13163,  -- There's still a hint of warmth to the body. This man was slain not more than two, perhaps three, hours ago.
        ONE_CLEAN_SLASH_SEVERING_THE_SPINAL_CORD_WAS                          = 13164,  -- One clean slash severing the spinal cord was all it took. This is no ordinary killer we're dealing with.
        AND_THE_PATTERN_GRUESOMELY_CARVED_INTO_THE_VICTIM                     = 13165,  -- And the pattern gruesomely carved into the victim's forehead...
        THIS_IS_ALL_THE_EVIDENCE_WE_NEED_THE                                  = 13166,  -- This is all the evidence we need. The murderer's identity is beyond doubt.
        BLAST_IT_NOT_A_MOMENT_AFTER_WE_ANNOUNCE                               = 13167,  -- Blast it! Not a moment after we announce heightened security, and this happens right under our noses! The reputation of the military police will be in shambles!
        WE_VE_HAD_ENOUGH_NEGATIVE_PUBLICITY_FOR_ONE                           = 13168,  -- We've had enough negative publicity for one day. Send those sightseers on their way, and clean up the mess!
        YES_SIR_RIGHT_AWAY_SIR                                                = 13169,  -- Yes, sir! Right away, sir!
        WHAT_YOU_RE_ON_THE_TRAIL_OF_DARKSTEEL                                 = 13170,  -- What? You're on the trail of Darksteel Hurricane!? Well, you don't seem to be crazy, so I gather you're either a musketeer or part of that surly military police outfit.
        NOT_THAT_THAT_HAS_ANY_BEARING_ON_A                                    = 13171,  -- Not that that has any bearing on a law-abiding citizen like me, of course. But getting back on subject, I take it you already know that he wears a menacing scar on his forehead.
        THOSE_WHO_VE_MET_A_BRUTAL_END_BY                                      = 13172,  -- Those who've met a brutal end by his cruel hand have all turned up with an identical wound carved into their foreheads.
        SPECULATION_ABOUNDS_ON_HIS_MOTIVES_BUT_IF_YOU                         = 13173,  -- Speculation abounds on his motives, but if you ask me, only vengeance can so fuel a man's desire for blood.
        JUST_THINKING_ABOUT_IT_MAKES_MY_SKIN_CRAWL                            = 13174,  -- Just thinking about it makes my skin crawl. You certainly won't catch me going on late-night strolls any more. Nor do I intend to linger in the presence of a Galka whose forehead I cannot see. I advise you to do the same!
        D_DID_I_HEAR_YOU_RIGHT_YOU_RE                                         = 13175,  -- D-did I hear you right!? You're asking me what I know about Darksteel Hurricane!?
        WH_WHAT_S_THE_BIG_IDEA_INVITING_DEATH                                 = 13176,  -- Wh-what's the big idea, inviting death to my door with a conversation topic like that!? Sorry won't cut it if I end up being the next to lie in a pool of my own blood!
        WHAT_YOU_PROMISE_TO_CATCH_HIM_BEFORE_HE                               = 13177,  -- What? You promise to catch him before he can lay a finger on me, you say? A-alright then... But you didn't hear this from me, are we clear?
        HE_IS_SAID_TO_WIELD_A_GREAT_SWORD                                     = 13178,  -- He is said to wield a great sword with fearsome proficiency.
        I_DARE_NOT_IMAGINE_HOW_MUCH_BLOOD_HAS                                 = 13179,  -- I dare not imagine how much blood has been spilt in order to quench his blade's insatiable thirst...
        HM_YOU_RE_ON_THE_HUNT_FOR_DARKSTEEL                                   = 13180,  -- Hm? You're on the hunt for Darksteel Hurricane? So, the recent murders occurring within the Republic's walls have been traced back to him...
        FIRST_A_QUESTION_FROM_ME_DO_YOU_KNOW                                  = 13181,  -- First, a question from me. Do you know how the man came to be feared by the name Darksteel Hurricane?
        IT_S_INSPIRED_BY_NONE_OTHER_THAN_THE                                  = 13182,  -- It's inspired by none other than the suit of darksteel armor he dons. With it, he can materialize unnoticed and melt back into the shadows at will...or so the rumors claim.
        SUCH_IS_THE_SPEED_AT_WHICH_HE_DISPATCHES                              = 13183,  -- Such is the speed at which he dispatches his victims, their lives are said to leave them long before the empty vessel of their bodies can crumple to the ground in a crimson mess.
        HE_IS_NO_CREATURE_OF_THIS_WORLD_OF                                    = 13184,  -- He is no creature of this world. Of this, I am certain.
        SO_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_IS_RESPONSIBLE_FOR_THE_SERIAL                  = 13185,  -- So, Darksteel Hurricane is responsible for the serial killings...
        IT_S_FALLEN_TO_YOU_AND_THE_MYTHRIL                                    = 13186,  -- %, it's fallen to you and the Mythril Musketeers once again to bring him to justice before any more lives are lost!
        YOU_VE_ALREADY_BEEN_BRIEFED_BY_NICOLAUS_CORRECT                       = 13187,  -- You've already been briefed by Nicolaus, correct? Talk to the Goblin, Blatherix, and see if you can glean anything on the whereabouts of our suspect.
        YOU_BRING_ME_AND_AND_I_LL_COOK_2                                      = 13188,  -- You bring me %, %, and %, and I'll cook you up a dose of Goblin Dust. Get it? Got it? Good!
        HEADIN_TO_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_HEADQUARTERS_SOON_DRIFTLIX           = 13189,  -- Headin' to the Mythril Musketeers' headquarters soon? Driftlix, or Limpears, as he's known in our circle, is ready when you are.
        I_HEAR_YOU_RE_TAKING_PART_IN_THE                                      = 13190,  -- I hear you're taking part in the large-scale manhunt for Darksteel Hurricane out at the Vunkerl Inlet. You'd better keep your eyes peeled and your ears open if want to come back with your limbs intact--errr...I mean, you be careful out there, %!
        SO_THE_INTELLIGENCE_PROVIDED_BY_THAT_GOBLIN_LIMPEARS                  = 13191,  -- So the intelligence provided by that Goblin--Limpears, was it?--proved to be the real deal. If you run into the little fella again, tell him I apologize for my churlishness the other day.
        OH_IT_S_YOU_WHAT_S_THAT_YOU                                           = 13192,  -- Oh, it's you. What's that? You wanna thank Limpears?
        SORRY_BUT_YOU_JUST_MISSED_HIM_HE_LEFT                                 = 13193,  -- Sorry, but you just missed him. He left here just a minute ago, skippin' along and whistlin' an old Gobbie tune. I haven't seen him so cheerful since his boss died and the business went under.
        IT_S_ALL_THANKS_TO_THE_STABLE_FLOW                                    = 13194,  -- It's all thanks to the stable flow of work he's found with the Mythril Musketeers. Now that his future's secured, he can focus on the more important stuff in life, like family.
        SEEIN_HIM_HAPPY_PUTS_A_SMILE_ON_MY                                    = 13195,  -- Seein' him happy puts a smile on my face. I know you can't see it, but I guarantee it's there. Anyway, here's a little somethin' for you, so you can share in on our delight.
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_RE_SAYIN_YOU_WANNA                                    = 13196,  -- What's that you're sayin'? You wanna relive the Goblin experience?
        HEHEHEH_I_CAN_T_SAY_I_M_SURPRISED                                     = 13197,  -- Heheheh, I can't say I'm surprised. Those who've had a taste of what it's like to be a Gobbie can never go back! Here, take this and run along now. It's on the house!
        WHATCHA_GOT_FOR_ME_EH_HMMM_AND_LOOKS                                  = 13198,  -- Whatcha got for me, eh? Hmmm...%, %, and %. Looks like we're good to go. Pay close attention now, 'cause I'm only gonna do this once.
        STEP_ONE_COMBINE_THE_AND                                              = 13199,  -- Step one: combine the % and %.
        STEP_TWO_TOSS_IN_THE_LIKE_SO_IT                                       = 13200,  -- Step two: toss in the %...like so. It's all in the wrist, see.
        STEP_THREE_INCANT_THE_MAGIC_WORDS_AHEM_OOH                            = 13201,  -- Step three: incant the magic words. Ahem! Ooh Gobbie I love your way, every day`t I wanna be like you night and day`t
        OOPS_I_ALMOST_WENT_AND_FORGOT_TO_ADD                                  = 13202,  -- Oops, I almost went and forgot to add the active ingredient.
        BLATHERIX_PLUCKS_OUT_A_SINGLE_STRAND_OF_HAIR                          = 13203,  -- Blatherix plucks out a single strand of hair from inside his ear!
        AND_VOILA_HOME_STYLE_GOBLIN_DUST_JUST_LIKE                            = 13204,  -- And voila! Home-style Goblin Dust, just like Mama used to make!
        THE_MEETING_S_ABOUT_TO_START_SO_HURRY                                 = 13205,  -- The meeting's about to start, so hurry up and scoff it down. No time for water!
        AH_IT_S_HIGH_TIME_YOU_CAME_TO                                         = 13206,  -- Ah, it's high time you came to. They do say first-timers are hit the hardest. But there's no time for rest. We don't want to keep the others waitin'. We Gobbies are nothin' if not punctual, y'know?
        WELCOME_ONE_AND_ALL_TO_THE_PICTURESQUE_WAR                            = 13207,  -- Welcome, one and all, to the picturesque, war-ravaged Republic of Bastok. The 999th Meeting of Goblin Information Tycoons (GIT) is now in session.
        FIRST_ON_THE_AGENDA_THE_LATEST_FROM_EACH                              = 13208,  -- First on the agenda, the latest from each region. Muckpads, take it away.
        THE_SAN_D_ORIANS_HAVE_BEEN_PULLIN_THEIR                               = 13209,  -- The San d'Orians have been pullin' their hair out by the handful, wonderin' why they can't gain no ground on the Orcs. They suspect an infiltrator in their ranks, but they ain't gettin' no closer to the truth. They're growin' desperate, fellas, real desperate. Meanin' they'd be willin' to pay a premium for any tidbits of intel that might help turn the tide of war. Any of youse got somethin' on this, share it with yours truly and I'll make sure it's worth your while. Heh heh heh...
        UNDERSTOOD_NEXT_MUZZLESPOUT                                           = 13210,  -- Understood. Next, Muzzlespout.
        WE_GOTS_USSELVES_A_POTENTIAL_CUSTOMER_IN_DA                           = 13211,  -- We gots usselves a potential customer in da Yagudo. Dey wants da skinny on da Windurst crew, 'specially any dirts on da bandaged bigwig. I smells good beastcoin here, fellas--mountains o' it--and would 'preciate any extra pairs o' hands t' help wit da diggin'.
        HM_THAT_SOUNDS_MIGHTY_PROMISIN_I_LL_ASSIGN                            = 13212,  -- Hm, that sounds mighty promisin'. I'll assign Fuzzylens to assist you. Moving on, Limpears.
        I_UH_PICKED_ME_UP_SOME_DISCOUNT_GIGAS                                 = 13213,  -- I uh...picked me up some discount Gigas gossip from Leadav--um, I mean Sandtongue, when I like, went walkabout to the Vunkerl Inlet. Any takerurers? It's priced to move.
        LIMPEARS_THAT_INFORMATION_ISN_T_WORTH_ITS_WEIGHT                      = 13214,  -- ... Limpears, that information isn't worth its weight in chocobo bedding. Don't you have anythin' worth sharin'?
        G_GIMME_A_SEC_I_M_SURE_I                                              = 13215,  -- G-gimme a sec... I'm sure I got somethin'...
        Y_YEAH_THAT_S_IT_I_WAS_LIKE                                           = 13216,  -- Y-yeah, that's it! I was like, frolickin'--um, prospectin' out in West Sarutabaruraruta just the other day, when a whole bunch of lycopodium saplings sprout right b'fore my very eyes! I was totally like, Whoaaa! Howsabout that for a scoop, eh? Eh?
        SCOOP_YOU_VE_GOTTA_BE_KIDDIN_ME                                       = 13217,  -- Scoop? You've gotta be kiddin' me...
        YOU_CALL_YOURSELF_A_GIT_HANG_YOUR_HEAD                                = 13218,  -- You call yourself a GIT? Hang your head in shame!
        S_SORRY                                                               = 13219,  -- S-sorry...
        NOW_NOW_FELLAS_WE_RE_ALL_PLAYIN_ON                                    = 13220,  -- Now, now, fellas, we're all playin' on the same team here.
        FRESH_MARKETABLE_INFORMATION_AIN_T_ALWAYS_EASY_TO                     = 13221,  -- Fresh, marketable information ain't always easy to come by. I've got nothin' new to share this time, myself.
        BUT_I_DID_BRING_AN_ENTHUSIASTIC_BUYER_WITH                            = 13222,  -- But! I did bring an enthusiastic buyer with deep pockets near to burstin' with gil. Hear him/her] out, will ya?
        SORRY_BUT_I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THE_FELLA                                    = 13223,  -- Sorry, but I haven't seen the fella you're lookin' for. There ain't many Galka in San d'Oria, so I'd remember if I saw one like you described.
        AND_UNLESS_HE_S_GOTS_HISSELF_A_REAL                                   = 13224,  -- And unless he's gots hisself a real scorcher o' a ship, we won't be seein' him nowhere near Windurst in a hurry. Your guy could be in lots o' places, but definitely not da Federation.
        I_VE_LIKE_TOTALLY_SEEN_HIM                                            = 13225,  -- I've like, totally seen him.
        A_ARE_YOU_SURE_LIMPEARS_WE_RE_TALKIN                                  = 13226,  -- A-are you sure, Limpears!? We're talkin' about a Galka here, not a goobbue.
        HEY_I_M_LAZY_NOT_BLIND_I_KNOW                                         = 13227,  -- Hey, I'm lazy, not blind! I know what I saw. The Galka...he was like--
        WHAT_YOU_WAITIN_FOR_A_DRUM_ROLL_OR                                    = 13228,  -- What? You waitin' for a drum roll or somethin'? Go on, spit it out!
        SNIFF_SNIFF_SOMETHIN_STINKS_LIKE_PEOPLE                               = 13229,  -- <Sniff, sniff>... Somethin' stinks...like people.
        ID_13230                                                              = 13230,  -- ...!
        WELL_WE_ARE_IN_TOWN_YA_KNOW_A                                         = 13231,  -- Well, we are in town, ya know. A bit of man-reek's nothin' out of the ordinary.
        SNIFF_SNIFF_NO_HE_S_RIGHT_DA_STINK                                    = 13232,  -- <Sniff, sniff>... No. He's right. Da stink's close. Too close for comfort.
        YOU_YOU_RE_NO_GOBLIN_YOU_MIGHT_LIKE                                   = 13233,  -- You! You're no Goblin! You might like, be able to pull the wool over my eyes and stuff, but not my nose!
        BADGERMAW_WHADDAYA_TRYIN_TO_PULL_HERE                                 = 13234,  -- Badgermaw! Whaddaya tryin' to pull here!?
        YOU_USED_GOBLIN_DUST_DIDN_T_YA_KNOWIN                                 = 13235,  -- You used Goblin Dust, didn't ya? Knowin' full well it's forbidden! We oughts to turn ya into chocobo fodder!
        I_I_M_SORRY_I_DIDN_T_MEAN                                             = 13236,  -- I-I'm sorry! I didn't mean any harm!
        L_LET_ME_EXPLAIN_THIS_HERE_S_NO                                       = 13237,  -- L-let me explain. This here's no ordinary guest. He/She]'s the sixth member of the Mythril Musketeers!
        HAH_AND_I_M_THE_SHADOW_LORD                                           = 13238,  -- Hah! And I'm the Shadow Lord!
        A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER                                                   = 13239,  -- A Mythril Musketeer...
        HOLD_IT                                                               = 13240,  -- Hold it!
        I_GOT_A_PROPOSITION_FOR_YOU_TAKE_ME                                   = 13241,  -- I got a proposition for you. Take me to your headquarterurers, and I'll like, totally tell your captain everything I know about this so-called Darkspiel Furrymane.
        L_LIMPEARS_YOU_D_FORSAKE_THE_TIME_HONORED                             = 13242,  -- L-Limpears! You'd forsake the time-honored rules of our grandgobbies for a few extra beastcoins janglin' in your gobbiebag?
        RULES_SHMULES_IMAGINE_THE_POSSIBILITIES_OF_BEIN_IN                    = 13243,  -- Rules-shmules! Imagine the possibilities of bein' in the Mythril Musketeers' payroll. Is stickin' to a couple of moldy old traditions like, worth passin' up on such a delicious opportunity? Look me dead in the eye and tell me this isn't totally a win-win situation!
        HRM_HRMMM                                                             = 13244,  -- Hrm... Hrmmm...
        DANG_IT_LIMPEARS_YOU_REALLY_CAN_BE_PERSUASIVE                         = 13245,  -- Dang it, Limpears, you really can be persuasive sometimes, ya know that? Alright, then. I'm with ya on this one.
        AND_I_M_WIT_YA_TOO_YOU_GO                                             = 13246,  -- And I'm wit ya, too! You go and gets dem musketeers so hooked on our intel, dey won't knows what t' do witout us no more!
        HEH_LOOKS_LIKE_THE_SITUATION_WORKED_ITSELF_OUT                        = 13247,  -- Heh, looks like the situation worked itself out...
        H_HEY_IS_THAT_A_GOBLIN_STANDING_THERE                                 = 13248,  -- H-hey, %. Is that a Goblin standing there beside you or are these back-to-back sentry shifts taking their toll on me?
        OH_OKAY_GOOD_TO_HEAR_THAT_I_M                                         = 13249,  -- Oh, okay. Good to hear that I'm not hallucinating...yet. What? You're saying that the little fella can tell us where Darksteel Hurricane's hiding out?
        HMMM_SEEMS_TO_TRUST_YOU_SO_I_LL                                       = 13250,  -- Hmmm... % seems to trust you, so I'll let you through. But try anything funny, and you'll wonder why I have gentle in my name. You got that?
        AH_WE_VE_BEEN_WAITING_FOR_YOU                                         = 13251,  -- Ah, we've been waiting for you.
        HEY_THIS_IS_A_PRETTY_SPIFFY_PLACE_YOU                                 = 13252,  -- Hey, this is a pretty spiffy place you got here! I like your taste in interior design! So anyway, which one's the captain? Mister beardo, or the sweet-lookin' redhead?
        MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_CAPTAIN_KLARA_BESTER_AT_YOUR_SERVICE               = 13253,  -- Mythril Musketeers Captain, Klara Bester, at your service. And what may we call you?
        THE_NAME_S_DRIFT_UM_I_MEAN_LIMPEARS                                   = 13254,  -- The name's Drift--um, I mean, Limpears. I hear you're intererurested in like, catchin' a certain Galka I happen to have caught sight of recently. So...what's this morsel of information worth to ya?
        SHALL_WE_SAY_TEN_GOLD_BEASTCOINS                                      = 13255,  -- Shall we say...ten gold beastcoins?
        SPLUTTER_A_AHEM_I_DON_T_USUALLY_LIKE                                  = 13256,  -- <Splutter> A-ahem! I don't usually like, deal in spare change, but I'll let you off for a special price just this once. Seein' how, y'know, it's totally your first time and all.
        LISTEN_UP_THEN_THE_VUNKERL_INLET_THAT_S                               = 13257,  -- Listen up, then. The Vunkerl Inlet--that's where I spotted your Galka.
        OH_IS_THAT_ALL_YOU_HAVE_FOR_US                                        = 13258,  -- Oh? Is that all you have for us? Hmm, perhaps our beastcoins are better spent elsewhere...
        N_NO_WAIT_THERE_S_MORE_I_SAW                                          = 13259,  -- N-no, wait! There's more! I saw him near a...a waterfall. A place you people call, um, Pipsqueak Falls...or somethin' along those lines.
        ALL_LIVIN_THINGS_WHETHERURER_THEY_RE_PEOPLE_OR                        = 13260,  -- All livin' things--whetherurer they're people or beasties--need like, water to survive, yeah? And your Galka's no exception.
        PIPEREED_FALLS_THAT_S_IN_THE_VICINITY_OF                              = 13261,  -- Pipereed Falls... That's in the vicinity of Berchlingen Bridge, where our forces recently clashed with the enemy.
        YOU_HAVE_OUR_GRATITUDE                                                = 13262,  -- You have our gratitude.
        SHOULD_THIS_INFORMATION_LEAD_TO_THE_CAPTURE_OF                        = 13263,  -- Should this information lead to the capture of Darksteel Hurricane, I'll see to it that you receive further recompense for your troubles.
        WHOAAA_YOU_SURE_KNOW_HOW_TO_SCRATCH_A                                 = 13264,  -- Whoaaa! You sure know how to scratch a guy the right way, lady! Pleasure doin' business with ya!
        THE_PLEASURE_IS_ALL_OURS_LIMPEARS_THE_REPUBLIC                        = 13265,  -- The pleasure is all ours, Limpears. The Republic looks forward to your continued cooperation.
        HEEHEE_WAIT_TILL_THE_OTHERURERS_HEAR_ABOUT_THIS                       = 13266,  -- Heehee! Wait till the otherurers hear about this! I'm totally goin' down in history as the greatest GIT ever to have lived!
        CAPTAIN_KLARA_I_M_NOT_SURE_I_AGREE                                    = 13267,  -- Captain Klara. I'm not sure I agree with your stance on allowing beastmen to run amok in the Metalworks, within earshot of the President's Office.
        CAPTAIN_BARTHOLOMAUS_WHAT_A_PLEASANT_SURPRISE_I_WAS                   = 13268,  -- Captain Bartholomaus, what a pleasant surprise. I was just about to have word sent to you.
        THE_GOBLIN_WHOM_YOU_SAW_LEAVE_JUST_NOW                                = 13269,  -- The Goblin whom you saw leave just now furnished us with intelligence on the probable location of Darksteel Hurricane.
        THAT_GOBLIN_TRULY_I_FIND_THAT_RATHER_HARD                             = 13270,  -- That Goblin? Truly? I find that rather hard to believe...
        WE_HAVE_NO_REASON_TO_DOUBT_HIS_RELIABILITY                            = 13271,  -- We have no reason to doubt his reliability as an informant. My unit will hasten to the Vunkerl Inlet at the earliest opportunity.
        NEEDLESS_TO_SAY_WE_INTEND_TO_APPREHEND_THE                            = 13272,  -- Needless to say, we intend to apprehend the target upon discovery. Can we still count on the full cooperation of your First Brigade in this matter?
        C_CAPTAIN                                                             = 13273,  -- C-Captain!
        B_BUT_OF_COURSE_THE_FIRST_BRIGADE_WISHES                              = 13274,  -- B-but of course! The First Brigade wishes nothing more than the expeditious capture of Darksteel Hurricane. What is the strategy to be employed in this manhunt?
        THE_TARGET_S_CURRENT_BASE_OF_OPERATION_IS                             = 13275,  -- The target's current base of operation is believed to be within close proximity to Pipereed Falls in the Vunkerl Inlet. Search participants will form an ever-tightening grid of encirclement within a set radius of the location--
        WITH_THE_GOAL_OF_FLUSHING_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_OUT                     = 13276,  -- ...With the goal of flushing Darksteel Hurricane out onto Berchlingen Bridge, where he'll have no place to run or hide.
        YOU_READ_MY_MIND_CAPTAIN                                              = 13277,  -- You read my mind, Captain.
        VERY_WELL_I_WILL_HAVE_BOTH_MUSKETEERS_AND                             = 13278,  -- Very well. I will have both Musketeers and Junior Musketeers alike prepare for immediate departure.
        YOU_HAVE_OUR_GRATITUDE_2                                              = 13279,  -- You have our gratitude.
        CAPTAIN_CAPTURING_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_IS_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS       = 13280,  -- Captain... Capturing Darksteel Hurricane is the Mythril Musketeers' best shot at restoring its reputation. While I'm not oblivious to the assurance that greater numbers offer, our target is but one man--
        ID_7_IM_L_UM_G_LM_ILE7_CC                                             = 13281,  -- "&%7=_IM l%uM%="{*G"LM*)iLE7*cc
        VOLKER_MORE_INNOCENT_LIVES_MAY_BE_LOST_WHILE                          = 13282,  -- Volker. More innocent lives may be lost while we clamber about trying to regain the public's trust. What is the reputation of the Mythril Musketeers when compared to the safety of the citizens?
        Y_YOU_RE_RIGHT_MA_AM_PLEASE_FORGIVE                                   = 13283,  -- Y-you're right, ma'am. Please forgive my naivet%i.
        I_M_GLAD_YOU_UNDERSTAND_NOW_THEN_AND                                  = 13284,  -- I'm glad you understand. Now then. % and Volker, you two are to accompany me to the Vunkerl Inlet. Make ready to leave at once.
        ZEID_AND_THE_OTHERS_ARE_TO_REMAIN_AND                                 = 13285,  -- Zeid and the others are to remain and see to security within the capital, should our prey decide to make another appearance.
        YES_MA_AM_3                                                           = 13286,  -- Yes, ma'am!
        I_VE_HEARD_ALL_ABOUT_THE_GREAT_NEWS                                   = 13287,  -- %! I've heard all about the great news: Darksteel Hurricane is no more!
        NOW_ALL_CITIZENS_OF_BASTOK_EXCLUDING_MYSELF_OF                        = 13288,  -- Now all citizens of Bastok--excluding myself, of course, because I was never intimidated--won't have to live in fear anymore! Hurrah!
        I_SEE_SO_THAT_WAS_HOW_THE_LEGEND                                      = 13289,  -- I see... So that was how the legend of Darksteel Hurricane came to an end...
        UNFORTUNATELY_THE_MAN_S_MOTIVES_FOR_CHOOSING_THIS                     = 13290,  -- Unfortunately, the man's motives for choosing this particular juncture to resume his bloody reign went with him to the grave. For me, at least, this spells several sleepless nights to come.
        BE_THAT_AS_IT_MAY_WE_HAVE_TO                                          = 13291,  -- Be that as it may, we have to content ourselves with the knowledge that no more innocent blood will be shed. Besides, with the new responsibilities that have been entrusted to our unit, you won't have the luxury of time to dwell on such matters.
        ID_13292                                                              = 13292,  -- ...?
        I_RECEIVED_A_MESSAGE_FROM_CHAIRMAN_PALE_EAGLE                         = 13293,  -- I received a message from Chairman Pale Eagle just moments ago.
        THE_SENATE_HAS_PASSED_A_MOTION_TO_REAPPOINT                           = 13294,  -- The Senate has passed a motion to reappoint the Mythril Musketeers to its customary post by the president's side.
        TRULY_CAPTAIN                                                         = 13295,  -- Truly, Captain!?
        I_AM_PLEASED_TO_SAY_SO_IT_WOULD                                       = 13296,  -- I am pleased to say so. It would appear the powers that be recognized our contribution towards solving these latest incidents.
        A_CEREMONY_WILL_TAKE_PLACE_IN_THE_PRESIDENT                           = 13297,  -- A ceremony will take place in the President's Office shortly. Zeid and I have been invited to attend as representatives of our unit.
        NICOLAUS_PREPARE_THE_REPORT_TO_BE_FILED_TO                            = 13298,  -- Nicolaus, prepare the report to be filed to the Security Office. I will be making my rounds to the Department of Industry in the meantime.
        PHEW_LOOKS_LIKE_WE_MANAGED_TO_COME_OUT                                = 13299,  -- Phew. Looks like we managed to come out on top in this little in-house tussle with the First Brigade.
        YEAH                                                                  = 13300,  -- Yeah...
        IS_SOMETHING_TROUBLING_YOU_FIVE_MOONS                                 = 13301,  -- Is something troubling you, Five Moons?
        DON_T_MISUNDERSTAND_ME_I_M_AS_RELIEVED                                = 13302,  -- Don't misunderstand me--I'm as relieved as any of us here that the citizens can live in peace once more.
        YET_A_PART_OF_ME_STRUGGLES_TO_COME                                    = 13303,  -- Yet, a part of me struggles to come to terms with Darksteel Hurricane's death.
        ID_13304                                                              = 13304,  -- ...
        IT_S_SILLY_I_KNOW                                                     = 13305,  -- It's silly, I know.
        I_WILL_GO_TO_THE_VUNKERL_INLET                                        = 13306,  -- I will go to the Vunkerl Inlet.
        AS_BOTH_GALKA_AND_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_I_MUST                            = 13307,  -- As both Galka and Mythril Musketeer, I must confirm with my own eyes the death of a man who had once ruled my existence. Or else I fear there will be no closure for me in this lifetime.
        F_FIVE_MOONS_WAIT                                                     = 13308,  -- F-Five Moons, wait--
        LET_US_ACCOMPANY_HIM_IT_S_THE_LEAST                                   = 13309,  -- Let us accompany him, %. It's the least we can do for a comrade in this period of internal turmoil.
        CAPTAIN_3                                                             = 13310,  -- Captain.
        WHAT_IS_IT                                                            = 13311,  -- What is it?
        THE_ENCOUNTER_AT_THE_VUNKERL_INLET                                    = 13312,  -- The encounter at the Vunkerl Inlet...
        F_H                                                                   = 13313,  -- %%F)H
        ID_13314                                                              = 13314,  -- ...
        WHAT_OF_IT_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_LIES_DEAD_AND                          = 13315,  -- What of it? Darksteel Hurricane lies dead and all blemishes have been cleansed from the Mythril Musketeers' name. We could not have hoped for a more ideal ending to a messy affair. Do you not agree?
        SPARE_ME_THE_DECEPTION_CAPTAIN                                        = 13316,  -- Spare me the deception, Captain!
        WHO_WAS_IT_THAT_YOU_CROSSED_SWORDS_WITH                               = 13317,  -- Who was it that you crossed swords with on the bridge?
        ID_13318                                                              = 13318,  -- ...
        THAT_GALKA_WAS_NOT_DARKSTEEL_HURRICANE_YOU_KNOW                       = 13319,  -- That Galka was not Darksteel Hurricane! You know this to be true above any other!
        HAH_FOR_A_FLEETING_MOMENT_I_THOUGHT_THE                               = 13320,  -- Hah... For a fleeting moment, I thought the old you had returned, Zeid.
        SIMMER_DOWN_SOLDIER                                                   = 13321,  -- Simmer down, soldier.
        MIND_THAT_YOU_ACQUIT_YOURSELF_WELL_WHILE_WE                           = 13322,  -- Mind that you acquit yourself well while we're in the President's Office.
        YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_FIVE_MOONS_AND_NICOLAUS                            = 13323,  -- You're looking for Five Moons and Nicolaus? The two of them departed for the Vunkerl Inlet a short while ago in utter silence. I wonder why they'd want to go back there...
        OH_HELLO_THERE_IS_THERE_SOMETHING_I_CAN                               = 13324,  -- Oh, hello there, %. Is there something I can help you with?
        NICOLAUS_HAS_ASKED_YOU_TO_FETCH_YOU_SAY                               = 13325,  -- Nicolaus has asked you to fetch %, you say?
        WELL_YOU_RE_IN_LUCK_BECAUSE_I_WAS                                     = 13326,  -- Well, you're in luck, because I was issued one of these babies just yesterday for use in riot control. You can have it, as long as you promise to think of your friend Gentle Tiger when tossing it into an unsuspecting swarm of hostiles.
        DON_T_KEEP_NICOLAUS_WAITING_FOR_THE_NOW                               = 13327,  -- Don't keep Nicolaus waiting for the %, now. Off you go.
        WHAT_YOU_WANT_ANOTHER_I_SUPPOSE_I_COULD                               = 13328,  -- What? You want another %? I suppose I could give you my spare, but then, how am I supposed to keep myself entertained during those long, tedious night shifts? <Sigh>... Alright, alright! I'll let you have it! Just stop staring at me like that!
        HM_WHAT_S_THE_MATTER_YOU_LOOK_LIKE                                    = 13329,  -- Hm? What's the matter, %? You look like you've seen a Tonberry. Uh...not that I'm afraid of those cute little critters, of course...
        OH_CAPTAIN_KLARA_AND_ZEID_THE_TWO_OF                                  = 13330,  -- Oh, Captain Klara and Zeid? The two of them should be on their way to the President's Office as we speak.
        ZEID_DO_YOU_RECALL_MY_WORDS_TO_YOU                                    = 13331,  -- Zeid. Do you recall my words to you the day you joined the Mythril Musketeers?
        AS_CLEAR_AS_IF_IT_WERE_YESTERDAY_CAPTAIN                              = 13332,  -- As clear as if it were yesterday, Captain. You said to me that to forward the peace and prosperity of the Republic, one must be prepared to overcome unimaginable hardships.
        GLF_HH_P_3JF_F_IM_1_IFCC                                              = 13333,  -- GLf$Hh_p&_%=3jf$F`%_Im"%1/iFcc
        AND_FOR_THE_SAKE_OF_THIS_CAUSE_ONE                                    = 13334,  -- And for the sake of this cause, one must not scruple to employ whatever means necessary, be they fair or foul.
        THESE_WORDS_STAND_RESOLUTE_TO_THIS_DAY                                = 13335,  -- These words stand resolute to this day.
        DO_YOU_STILL_SHARE_THIS_BELIEF_WITH_ME                                = 13336,  -- Do you still share this belief with me, Zeid?
        I_HAVE_NEVER_BELIEVED_OTHERWISE_CAPTAIN_WERE_IT                       = 13337,  -- I have never believed otherwise, Captain. Were it not for you, I would have been condemned to live out the rest of my wretched life as a creature lesser than a beast.
        COME_WHAT_MAY_I_WILL_FOLLOW_YOU_TO                                    = 13338,  -- Come what may, I will follow you to the end.
        THEN_SWEAR_ME_THIS_ZEID                                               = 13339,  -- Then swear me this, Zeid.
        THAT_WHATEVER_YOU_MAY_WITNESS_FROM_THIS_POINT                         = 13340,  -- That whatever you may witness from this point onwards, you will never cease to believe in me.
        I_SWEAR_CAPTAIN                                                       = 13341,  -- I swear, Captain.
        MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_CAPTAIN_KLARA_BESTER_AND_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER         = 13342,  -- Mythril Musketeers Captain Klara Bester and Mythril Musketeer Zeid reporting.
        AH_KLARA_ZEID_IT_HAS_SIMPLY_BEEN_TOO                                  = 13343,  -- Ah, Klara, Zeid. It has simply been too long. I thank you for coming.
        IT_IS_WE_WHO_ARE_DEEPLY_HONORED_BY                                    = 13344,  -- It is we who are deeply honored by your invitation, Your Excellency.
        HAHAHA_LET_S_DO_AWAY_WITH_THE_POMP                                    = 13345,  -- Hahaha, let's do away with the pomp and ceremony, shall we? On your feet, the both of you.
        TRUTH_BE_TOLD_NONE_WAS_MORE_TROUBLED_THAN                             = 13346,  -- Truth be told, none was more troubled than I over the Mythril Musketeers' dismissal from its post.
        BUT_LOATH_AS_I_WAS_TO_BE_BEREFT                                       = 13347,  -- But loath as I was to be bereft of your unit's reassuring presence, regrettably, there were those of influence who weren't so favorably inclined following that incident. I fear I had little choice but to appease their demands.
        I_FERVENTLY_APOLOGIZE_FOR_THE_DISTRESS_MY_UNIT                        = 13348,  -- I fervently apologize for the distress my unit has caused.
        NO_MATTER_IT_S_ALL_IN_THE_PAST                                        = 13349,  -- No matter. It's all in the past now. Besides, true to your reputation, you have found a way back to my side again, and not a moment too soon.
        YOU_ARE_TOO_KIND_YOUR_EXCELLENCY_I_TOO                                = 13350,  -- You are too kind, Your Excellency. I, too, have waited long for this moment.
        FOR_TODAY                                                             = 13351,  -- For today...
        IS_THE_DAY_I_BATHE_MY_BLADE_IN                                        = 13352,  -- Is the day I bathe my blade in your blood!
        ID_13353                                                              = 13353,  -- ...!?
        K_KLARA_I_AM_NOT_SEEING_THE_HUMOR                                     = 13354,  -- K-Klara? I am not seeing the humor in this...
        ZEID_3                                                                = 13355,  -- Zeid.
        DON_T_FORGET_THE_OATH_YOU_SWORE                                       = 13356,  -- Don't forget the oath you swore.
        C_CAPTAIN_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING                                          = 13357,  -- C-Captain! What are you doing!?
        ID_13358                                                              = 13358,  -- !!!
        I_HAD_EXPECTED_BETTER_OF_YOU_VOLKER_I                                 = 13359,  -- I had expected better of you, Volker. I will not tolerate insubordination in any shape or form.
        ID_13360                                                              = 13360,  -- ...
        TAKING_A_BLADE_TO_ONE_OF_YOUR_OWN                                     = 13361,  -- Taking a blade to one of your own...
        WHAT_MADNESS_HAS_TAKEN_YOU_KLARA                                      = 13362,  -- What madness has taken you, Klara!?
        UGH_3                                                                 = 13363,  -- Ugh!
        HE_WHO_WOULD_CALL_HIMSELF_THE_LEADER_OF                               = 13364,  -- He who would call himself the leader of a nation must learn to be gracious in defeat.
        THE_TIME_OF_PARTING_IS_COME_FAREWELL_PRESIDENT                        = 13365,  -- The time of parting is come. Farewell, President Prien of the Republic of Bastok!
        ZEID_HAVE_YOU_SO_QUICKLY_FORGOTTEN_YOUR_OATH                          = 13366,  -- Zeid! Have you so quickly forgotten your oath? Stand down!
        CAPTAIN_PLEASE_CEASE_THIS_MADNESS                                     = 13367,  -- Captain! Please cease this madness!
        HM_THAT_WAS_THE_SOUND_OF_SWORDS_CLASHING                              = 13368,  -- Hm!? That was the sound of swords clashing!
        VOLKER_4                                                              = 13369,  -- Volker!
        CAPTAIN_SO_THE_SITUATION_IS_AS_WE_FEARED                              = 13370,  -- Captain... So the situation is as we feared...
        I_M_COMING_TO_YOUR_AID_ZEID                                           = 13371,  -- I'm coming to your aid, Zeid!
        ID_13372                                                              = 13372,  -- ...!
        ZEID_WHY_DO_YOU_INTERFERE                                             = 13373,  -- Zeid? Why do you interfere!?
        LISTEN_WELL_ZEID_THE_NEXT_TIME_WE_MEET                                = 13374,  -- Listen well, Zeid. The next time we meet...
        CAPTAIN_4                                                             = 13375,  -- Captain?
        IT_WILL_NOT_BE_ME_WHO_STANDS_BEFORE                                   = 13376,  -- It will not be me who stands before you!
        WHY_CAPTAIN_KLARA_I_HEARD_NOISES_AND_SO                               = 13377,  -- Why, Captain Klara. I heard noises and so rushed here--
        ID_13378                                                              = 13378,  -- !?
        TH_THAT_UNSHEATHED_BLADE                                              = 13379,  -- Th-that unsheathed blade...
        CAPTAIN_KLARA_2                                                       = 13380,  -- Captain Klara!?
        SOMETHING_IS_AMISS_WITH_ME_MEN                                        = 13381,  -- Something is amiss! With me, men!
        M_MISTER_PRESIDENT_ARE_YOU_UNHARMED                                   = 13382,  -- M-Mister President! Are you unharmed!?
        GREAT_KAISER_S_GHOST                                                  = 13383,  -- Great Kaiser's ghost!
        STAY_RIGHT_WHERE_YOU_ARE_ALL_OF_YOU                                   = 13384,  -- Stay right where you are, all of you!
        THAT_CAPTAIN_KLARA_WOULD_ATTEMPT_TO_TAKE_THE                          = 13385,  -- That Captain Klara would attempt to take the life of the president and even strike down Volker with murderous intent... None of this makes any sense!
        EVERY_SINGLE_MEMBER_OF_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_HAS                     = 13386,  -- Every single member of the Mythril Musketeers has been detained for questioning. Looks like you being overlooked in all this is the only silver lining we'll be seeing in this darkest of clouds...
        WITH_THE_INTENSITY_OF_THE_WAR_AGAINST_THE                             = 13387,  -- With the intensity of the war against the beastmen near to boiling, this internal discord couldn't have come at a worse time. I'm afraid to imagine what will become of the nation...
        YOU_RE_THE_REPUBLIC_S_ONLY_HOPE_PLEASE                                = 13388,  -- %! You're the Republic's only hope! Please don't abandon us in this hour of need!
        MMM_GALKAN_SAUSAGES_PUMPKIN_PIE_OM_NOM_NOM                            = 13389,  -- (Mmm, Galkan sausages...pumpkin pie...om nom nom nom...) ...Hm?
        OH_IT_S_YOU_FORGIVE_ME_EVER_SINCE                                     = 13390,  -- Oh, it's you, %. Forgive me. Ever since the attempt on the president's life, I haven't been sleeping so well at night.
        A_GUARDSMAN_LIKE_ME_S_GOT_PLENTY_OF                                   = 13391,  -- A guardsman like me's got plenty of time to ponder. No matter how much I rack my brains, though, I can't believe that Captain Klara was behind the heinous deed.
        COURSE_ALL_THE_OFFICIAL_ANNOUNCEMENTS_FROM_THE_PRESIDENT              = 13392,  -- 'Course, all the official announcements from the president's office are claiming it to be the work of a Tonberry, so's not to cause a public stir. Ah, were it only so!
        YOU_CAN_SAY_THAT_AGAIN_FRIEND                                         = 13393,  -- You can say that again, friend.
        WHY_IF_IT_ISN_T_NICOLAUS_AND_FIVE                                     = 13394,  -- Why, if it isn't Nicolaus and Five Moons! How fare the Mythril Musketeers?
        THEY_FARE_NOT_AT_ALL_I_M_AFRAID                                       = 13395,  -- They fare not at all, I'm afraid. Thanks to our erstwhile captain's foray into the field of presidential assassination, our glorious unit has been disbanded, and its members relegated to penal duty.
        WE_PROUDLY_STAND_BEFORE_YOU_AS_NICOLAUS_AND                           = 13396,  -- We proudly stand before you as Nicolaus and Five Moons of Disciplinary Company Skink. Zeid was sent to the field with Company Jackal, no doubt to perform some suitably arduous and trivial task.
        CONSIDER_YOURSELF_LUCKY_YOU_WERE_ONLY_AN_HONORARY                     = 13397,  -- Consider yourself lucky you were only an honorary member of our squad, %. Were you a full-fledged Musketeer, you'd surely have suffered the same fate.
        I_JUST_CAN_T_MAKE_SENSE_OF_IT                                         = 13398,  -- I just can't make sense of it, Nicolaus. What unholy madness could have driven an honorable soldier to such treachery?
        I_WISH_I_HAD_ANSWERS_FIVE_MOONS_BUT                                   = 13399,  -- I wish I had answers, Five Moons, but my deductive powers fail me this time. There's simply no logical motive that could account for the captain of the Mythril Musketeers drawing steel against the very man she was sworn to protect.
        AND_YET_THAT_S_EXACTLY_WHAT_SHE_DID                                   = 13400,  -- ...And yet that's exactly what she did. Even Volker was made to feel the wrath of her treasonous blade.
        THANKFULLY_HE_SUFFERED_ONLY_GRAZE_WOUNDS_STILL_ONE                    = 13401,  -- Thankfully, he suffered only graze wounds. Still, one thing remains clear. Captain Klara must be tracked down and made to answer for her crimes.
        SO_THIS_IS_WHERE_YOU_SLITHERY_SKINKS_SCURRIED                         = 13402,  -- So this is where you slithery Skinks scurried off to! We've got a situation on our hands!
        DISCIPLINARY_CAPTAIN_HERBERT_WHATEVER_IS_THE_MATTER                   = 13403,  -- Disciplinary Captain Herbert! Whatever is the matter?
        AHEM_WHATEVER_IS_THE_MATTER_SIR_I_M                                   = 13404,  -- Ahem. Whatever is the matter, sir. I'm your superior now, and you'd best not be forgetting! It's that masked meddler Zeid...he's deserted his unit!
        WHAT_2                                                                = 13405,  -- What!?
        YOU_HEARD_ME_I_SAID_HE_DESERTED_AN                                    = 13406,  -- You heard me, I said he deserted! An emergency dispatch just came in from the Jackal sergeant in Beadeaux. He says your surly comrade went off on a survey of Quadav territory, and failed to return with his squad.
        I_VE_ORDERED_A_HANDFUL_OF_MEN_TO                                      = 13407,  -- I've ordered a handful of men to join the search effort, and it's time you got off your pampered posteriors and joined them. You hear me, Skinks? That's an order!
        Y_YES_SIR_INCIDENTALLY_WOULD_YOU_HAPPEN_TO                            = 13408,  -- Y-yes sir! Incidentally, would you happen to have any insight into his destination? Any potential leads at all would be most--
        WHAT_DO_I_LOOK_LIKE_A_GOBLIN_TIPSTER                                  = 13409,  -- What do I look like, a Goblin tipster? I haven't the time or interest to keep up with every half-baked rumor brought to me! Besides, I've business in Eldieme. If you're going to bother someone, make it Sergeant Rainer of the Jackals. Now get lost! And next time I see you scrubs, that overgrown loafer had better be with you!
        DESERTION_THAT_DOESN_T_SOUND_AT_ALL_LIKE                              = 13410,  -- Desertion? That doesn't sound at all like the Zeid I know...
        AS_IF_WE_HADN_T_SUFFERED_ENOUGH_INDIGNITY                             = 13411,  -- As if we hadn't suffered enough indignity, now he flouts our superiors further? What could the man possibly be thinking? But I'm afraid we haven't the luxury to ponder his motives. If we don't find him, and soon, we can prepare for the worst...
        THE_WORST_YOU_SAY                                                     = 13412,  -- The worst, you say?
        THE_MAXIMUM_PENALTY_FOR_DESERTION_DURING_WARTIME_IS                   = 13413,  -- The maximum penalty for desertion during wartime is death, after all...and there are plenty of loose cannons in the disciplinary regiments looking to impress their superiors. If one of them were to find him, why, his sentence just might be carried out on the spot...
        THEN_WE_MUST_FIND_HIM_BEFORE_THE_OTHERS                               = 13414,  -- Then we must find him before the others do!
        YES_IF_WE_CAN_CONVINCE_HIM_TO_RETURN                                  = 13415,  -- Yes. If we can convince him to return of his own accord, there's still hope. But it'll be no small task to track him down without knowing his true intentions...
        IN_ANY_EVENT_THERE_S_NOTHING_TO_BE                                    = 13416,  -- In any event, there's nothing to be gained standing around here. Let's make for Beadeaux and see what clues this Sergeant Rainer may have for us.
        I_TRUST_YOU_RE_UP_TO_THE_TASK                                         = 13417,  -- I trust you're up to the task as well, %?
        EXCELLENT_WITH_OUR_THREE_HEADS_TOGETHER_WE_RE                         = 13418,  -- Excellent! With our three heads together, we're bound to come up with something. Very well then, let's be off!
        CAPTAIN_BARTHOLOMAUS_YOU_SAY_WHY_HE_WAS_IN                            = 13419,  -- Captain Bartholomaus, you say? Why, he was in the briefing room, last I saw.
        I_LL_WARN_YOU_THOUGH_HE_SEEMED_TO                                     = 13420,  -- I'll warn you, though--he seemed to be in an especially prickly mood. It would seem the investigation has taken a toll on us all...
        THE_ENROLLMENT_RECORDS_AND_WHAT_BUSINESS_WOULD_YOU                    = 13421,  -- The enrollment records? And what business would you have with those, hmm?
        FOR_ALL_I_KNOW_YOU_COULD_BE_SCHEMING                                  = 13422,  -- For all I know, you could be scheming with those treasonous friends of yours.
        AND_WHAT_IF_HE_SHE_WERE_BARTHOLOMAUS                                  = 13423,  -- And what if he/she] were, Bartholomaus?
        WELL_WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_THE_MYTHRIL                                     = 13424,  -- Well, well...if it isn't the Mythril Skinks. To what do I owe the honor?
        I_WAS_SIMPLY_OFFERING_YOUR_COLLEAGUE_A_PIECE                          = 13425,  -- I was simply offering your colleague a piece of honest advice: if he/she] wishes to stay on the right side of the law, it'd behoove him/her] to stay away from the likes of you.
        ANYHOW_YOUR_REQUEST_IS_AS_FUTILE_AS_IT                                = 13426,  -- Anyhow, your request is as futile as it is foolish. All records pertaining to your ignoble unit have been seized and locked away until the investigation is over.
        NOT_EVEN_MY_OWN_LOYAL_MEN_ARE_ALLOWED                                 = 13427,  -- Not even my own loyal men are allowed access, let alone a couple of misfits deemed unfit for duty by virtue of their connection to the very incident they now poke their meddling noses into.
        WHY_NOTHING_SHORT_OF_AUTHORIZATION_FROM_DISCIPLINARY_CAPTAIN          = 13428,  -- Why, nothing short of authorization from Disciplinary Captain Herbert could convince me otherwise. But don't despair. I'm sure he'd be simply thrilled to make such a request on behalf of a pair of Skinks as...distinguished...as you two. Ha ha ha!
        THERE_S_ONE_MAN_WHO_HASN_T_LOST                                       = 13429,  -- There's one man who hasn't lost his knack for adding insult to injury.
        STILL_WE_MUSTN_T_GIVE_IN_CAPTAIN_HERBERT                              = 13430,  -- Still, we mustn't give in! Captain Herbert said he had business at the Eldieme Necropolis. We can only hope that he takes pity on our plight.
        OH_NICOLAUS_JUST_CAME_RUSHING_THROUGH_HERE_LIKE                       = 13431,  -- Oh, %. Nicolaus just came rushing through here like a rabid fledermaus.
        WHATEVER_DO_YOU_SUPPOSE_HAS_GOTTEN_INTO_HIM                           = 13432,  -- Whatever do you suppose has gotten into him? At any rate, go on in. He should be right inside.
        AH_FIVE_MOONS_TOOK_THE_SCENIC_ROUTE_DID                               = 13433,  -- Ah, %, Five Moons! Took the scenic route, did you?
        FORGIVE_ME_I_SIMPLY_COULDN_T_BEAR_THE                                 = 13434,  -- Forgive me. I simply couldn't bear the wait, so I took it upon myself to peruse the records on my own.
        LITTLE_TO_MY_SURPRISE_IT_DIDN_T_TAKE                                  = 13435,  -- Little to my surprise, it didn't take long to come across a most...intriguing...passage.
        YOU_VE_FOUND_A_CLUE                                                   = 13436,  -- You've found a clue!?
        THE_ENTRY_IN_QUESTION_IS_DATED_C_E                                    = 13437,  -- The entry in question is dated C.E. 858, or roughly six years ago. It reads...
        AHEM_IN_THE_VICINITY_OF_HOARFANG_KEEP_IN                              = 13438,  -- <Ahem> ...In the vicinity of Hoarfang Keep in Beaucedine, Captain Klara Bester of the Mythril Musketeers captured and took into custody the Galka War Cloud...
        CAPTURED_WHAT_COULD_THIS_MEAN_WHAT_COULD_ZEID                         = 13439,  -- Captured...!? What could this mean? What could Zeid possibly have done that would call for his capture!? Who...was he?
        I_M_AFRAID_THE_REPORT_GOES_INTO_NO                                    = 13440,  -- I'm afraid the report goes into no further detail. Still, to be chased out to the far reaches of such savage territory, it's clear enough he was up to no good.
        WAIT_HOARFANG_WHY_DOES_THAT_NAME_RING_SO                              = 13441,  -- Wait...Hoarfang? Why does that name ring so familiar to me...?
        YES_YES_OF_COURSE                                                     = 13442,  -- ...Yes! Yes, of course!
        THAT_WAS_THE_SITE_OF_THE_GALKAN_MASSACRE                              = 13443,  -- That was the site of the Galkan massacre!
        THE_GALKAN_MASSACRE_AH_YOU_SPEAK_OF_THE                               = 13444,  -- The Galkan...massacre? Ah, you speak of the Thirteenth!
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_THE_TALE_IT_WAS_SOME                                   = 13445,  -- Have you heard the tale, %? It was some seven years ago. The Thirteenth Regiment was dispatched to Beaucedine for a particularly perilous campaign against the beastmen.
        BUT_THE_THIRTEENTH_WAS_NO_ORDINARY_UNIT_IT                            = 13446,  -- But the Thirteenth was no ordinary unit...it was comprised entirely of Galka, you see. Some even say it was for this reason that they were chosen for such a dangerous mission. It cannot be denied, given how deep prejudices ran in those days.
        UNFORTUNATELY_THE_TALE_COMES_TO_A_TRAGIC_END                          = 13447,  -- Unfortunately, the tale comes to a tragic end. Reports from the front said that they fought dauntlessly against a foe who vastly outnumbered them. In the end, not a single brave soldier was to return.
        NICOLAUS_COULD_THERE_BE_SOME_CONNECTION_BETWEEN_ZEID                  = 13448,  -- Nicolaus, could there be some connection between Zeid's disappearance and the fate of the Thirteenth?
        AS_IT_STANDS_IT_S_THE_ONLY_LEAD                                       = 13449,  -- As it stands, it's the only lead we've got. Come, %, Five Moons! Let us make for Beaucedine...for Hoarfang!
        I_TOO_FEEL_WE_WILL_FIND_OUR_ANSWERS                                   = 13450,  -- I, too, feel we will find our answers there. But let us be cautious... The glacier is not a forgiving place.
        SAY_IT_ISN_T_SO_IS_IT_TRUE                                            = 13451,  -- Say it isn't so, %! Is it true that Zeid has been arrested and imprisoned!? Why, that man was like a brother to me! The most honorable soldier I've ever known! Ever since the day he saved me from the black blade of Bi'Gho Headtaker, I swore to myself that I'd follow him to the ends of the earth if he asked, I would, and question his honor not one minute, one second for as long as I lived! He was framed! Framed, I tell you! And I'll see to it that he suffers not a day longer in whatever dark, dank, musty gaol they've got him locked away in if I have to storm in there, bash some gaoler heads, and rip open the cold iron bars of his cell with my own bare hands! Do you hear me, Zeid!? Gentle Tiger will not rest until your honor is restored!!!
        AH_AHEM_FORGIVE_ME_MY_EMOTIONS_GOT_THE                                = 13452,  -- Ah...! <Ahem> Forgive me, %. My emotions got the better of me for a moment there. (I hope I wasn't overheard!)
        PHEW_THAT_WAS_A_CLOSE_ONE_BUT_WEREN                                   = 13453,  -- (Phew, that was a close one! But weren't you able to persuade the others to listen to reason?)
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_HAPPENED_OUT_AT                                     = 13454,  -- (I don't know what happened out at the glacier, but surely Zeid deserves a chance to clear his name! Nicolaus and Five Moons are inside. You must talk to them and see what can be done. Our friend is counting on us, %!)
        AH_I_TRUST_YOUR_JOURNEY_BACK_FROM_THE                                 = 13455,  -- Ah, %. I trust your journey back from the glacier was uneventful?
        IT_WOULD_SEEM_THE_RUMORS_ARE_TRUE_ZEID                                = 13456,  -- It would seem the rumors are true: Zeid has been locked away in a maximum-security cell of the Benedikt Watchtower. Captain Bartholomaus took great pleasure in informing me of this fact personally. There is no word yet as to what his punishment will be, but it'll not be light, I assure you.
        I_VE_CONVEYED_THE_NEWS_TO_VOLKER_AS                                   = 13457,  -- I've conveyed the news to Volker as well. The events at Beaucedine, Zeid and Klara's past, the true identity of Darksteel Hurricane...
        LET_IT_SUFFICE_TO_SAY_THAT_HE_WAS                                     = 13458,  -- Let it suffice to say that he was in a state of disbelief. The two joined the Mythril Musketeers together, and he was closer to Zeid than any save the captain herself. And yet, he knew nothing of all this.
        I_CAN_STILL_HARDLY_BELIEVE_IT_MYSELF                                  = 13459,  -- I can still hardly believe it myself...
        NO_GALKA_WHO_HAS_EVER_FELT_THE_STING                                  = 13460,  -- No Galka who has ever felt the sting of prejudice could begrudge him the depths of bitterness and hate he must have borne for the Humes since that day. But to allow that to turn him to wanton, reckless murder...
        I_FULLY_INTENDED_TO_FILE_AN_OFFICIAL_REPORT                           = 13461,  -- I fully intended to file an official report to the Security Office on Darksteel Hurricane's identity.
        VOLKER_WOULD_HAVE_NONE_OF_THAT_HOWEVER_HE                             = 13462,  -- ...Volker would have none of that, however. He still believes in them, and insists that Captain Klara must have had due reason for taking Zeid under her wing.
        TRULY_HAVE_HIS_INJURIES_GONE_TO_HIS_HEAD                              = 13463,  -- Truly, have his injuries gone to his head? It seems clear to me that any shred of honor once possessed by our one-time comrades is gone, and we deal now with little more than two common criminals.
        STILL_I_CANNOT_SIMPLY_DISREGARD_THE_WORDS_OF                          = 13464,  -- Still, I cannot simply disregard the words of my superior. We will refrain from notifying the authorities until we can ascertain their motives beyond a shadow of a doubt. Mum's the word on what you've seen, %.
        ANYHOW_FORGIVE_ME_I_SHOULDN_T_BURDEN_YOU                              = 13465,  -- ...Anyhow, forgive me. I shouldn't burden you with my musings on matters beyond your control.
        VOLKER_HAS_NEAR_RECOVERED_FROM_HIS_WOUNDS_AND                         = 13466,  -- Volker has near recovered from his wounds, and will soon be restored to active duty. Five Moons and I must return to Company Skink as well.
        YOUR_ASSISTANCE_HAS_BEEN_GREATLY_APPRECIATED_UNTIL_WE                 = 13467,  -- Your assistance has been greatly appreciated, %. Until we meet again.
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_SAY_NICOLAUS_AND_FIVE                                 = 13468,  -- What's that you say? Nicolaus and Five Moons have returned to their unit!?
        DO_THEY_INTEND_TO_LEAVE_ZEID_TO_ROT                                   = 13469,  -- Do they intend to leave Zeid to rot away in his cell? Will they sit idly by as he is sentenced to death!?
        HE_WAS_THEIR_COMRADE_ARE_BONDS_OF_MYTHRIL                             = 13470,  -- He was their comrade! Are bonds of mythril so brittle as this?
        I_WORRY_FOR_ZEID_THE_LOOK_IN_YOUR                                     = 13471,  -- I worry for Zeid, %. The look in your eyes tells me you feel the same.
        I_KNOW_WHY_DON_T_YOU_PAY_A                                            = 13472,  -- I know! Why don't you pay a visit to Benedikt Watchtower? Surely your company would raise his spirits, and there just might be a way to help restore his good name.
        HERE_TAKE_THIS_AND_TELL_ZEID_THAT_IT                                  = 13473,  -- Here, take this, and tell Zeid that it's from his loyal friends. That no matter how many turn against him, there are those of us who will always believe!
        WHAT_ZEID_HAS_ESCAPED_FROM_THE_WATCHTOWER                             = 13474,  -- What!? Zeid has escaped from the watchtower?
        AS_MUCH_AS_I_BELIEVE_IN_HIS_INNOCENCE                                 = 13475,  -- (As much as I believe in his innocence, surely this isn't the way! Why, this will only compound his guilt!)
        THERE_MUST_BE_SOMETHING_WE_CAN_DO                                     = 13476,  -- There must be something we can do...
        IS_SOMETHING_THE_MATTER_FRIEND                                        = 13477,  -- Is something the matter, friend?
        NICOLAUS_FIVE_MOONS_YOU_MUST_LISTEN                                   = 13478,  -- Nicolaus! Five Moons! You must listen!
        I_CAN_HARDLY_BELIEVE_IT_BUT                                           = 13479,  -- I can hardly believe it, but...
        WH_WHAT_ZEID_HAS_VANISHED_AGAIN                                       = 13480,  -- Wh-what!? Zeid has vanished again!?
        I_WORRY_FOR_HIM_FRIENDS_IS_THERE_NOTHING                              = 13481,  -- I worry for him, friends! Is there nothing to be done to save him from his fate?
        I_M_AFRAID_THE_TIME_FOR_THAT_IS                                       = 13482,  -- I'm afraid the time for that is long past. He had a choice, and has clearly chosen the traitor's path.
        BESIDES_FIVE_MOONS_AND_I_MUST_SOON_MAKE                               = 13483,  -- Besides, Five Moons and I must soon make for Xarcabard.
        THE_ALLIED_FORCES_ARE_LOCKED_IN_A_BITTER                              = 13484,  -- The Allied Forces are locked in a bitter and crucial struggle against the Beastman Confederate. With the ranks of our army thinned, the disciplinary regiments have been summoned to the front lines.
        WE_CAN_ILL_AFFORD_TO_BE_DISTRACTED_BY                                 = 13485,  -- We can ill afford to be distracted by those two any longer. Though it pains me as well, we must wash our hands of them once and for all.
        YOU_CAN_T_MEAN_THIS_SURELY_YOU_DON                                    = 13486,  -- You can't mean this...! %! Surely you don't mean to abandon him too?
        IF_ANYONE_CAN_BRING_HIM_BACK_AND_MAKE                                 = 13487,  -- If anyone can bring him back and make him see reason, it's you! Ah, if only we knew where the Captain has taken him...
        XARCABARD                                                             = 13488,  -- Xarcabard!?
        WHY_DIDN_T_YOU_SAY_SO_SOONER_DO                                       = 13489,  -- ...! Why didn't you say so sooner, %? Do you realize what this means!? None other than the president himself leads our army's advance in Xarcabard!
        NO_NICOLAUS_DOES_THE_CAPTAIN_MEAN_TO                                  = 13490,  -- No...! Nicolaus, does the captain mean to--?
        I_D_STAKE_MY_LIFE_ON_IT_AND                                           = 13491,  -- I'd stake my life on it! And if she finds him, I don't care how many guards he has in his retinue--it won't be enough.
        WE_HAVEN_T_A_MOMENT_TO_LOSE                                           = 13492,  -- %. We haven't a moment to lose.
        YOU_MUST_GO_TO_XARCABARD_AND_INFORM_THE                               = 13493,  -- You must go to Xarcabard and inform the field commanders of the danger. Then you must join up with the Republican Army, and do everything in your power to see that no harm befalls the president.
        WE_MUST_TRAVEL_WITH_COMPANY_SKINK_BUT_WILL                            = 13494,  -- We must travel with Company Skink, but will follow as soon as we are able. Can we count on you, %?
        EXCELLENT_WE_MAY_HAVE_LOST_ZEID_BUT_YOU                               = 13495,  -- Excellent. We may have lost Zeid, but you're a staunch ally as ever.
        IS_REQUIRED_FOR_ANY_SOLDIER_TO_BE_ACCEPTED                            = 13496,  -- % is required for any soldier to be accepted into the president's retinue.
        I_LL_ASK_DISCIPLINARY_CAPTAIN_HERBERT_TO_PREPARE                      = 13497,  -- I'll ask Disciplinary Captain Herbert to prepare one. With the information you've given us, I'm sure we can convince him of the urgency of our cause.
        NOW_GODDESS_SPEED_YOU_WE_SHALL_MEET_AGAIN                             = 13498,  -- Now Goddess speed you, %! We shall meet again in Xarcabard!
        IF_IT_ISN_T_HERO_OF_THE_REPUBLIC                                      = 13499,  -- If it isn't %, hero of the Republic! Why, the entire Metalworks is abuzz with talk of how you saved the president's life!
        HOW_DID_WE_HEAR_YOU_SAY                                               = 13500,  -- How did we hear, you say?
        WHY_A_DISPATCH_JUST_CAME_IN_FROM_THE                                  = 13501,  -- Why, a dispatch just came in from the front lines. The president leads the Republican Army on an advance deeper north into Xarcabard--we've got the beastmen on the run, %!
        BUT_IS_IT_TRUE_THAT_CAPTAIN_KLARA_MADE                                = 13502,  -- But is it true that Captain Klara made another attempt on his life? And what of Zeid!?
        I_SEE_SO_THE_FIEND_THAT_TARGETS_OUR                                   = 13503,  -- I see...so the fiend that targets our president is not the true Captain Klara, but a demonic impostor? Now there's a tale to chill the blood!
        BUT_WITH_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_BACK_ON_THE                           = 13504,  -- But with the Mythril Musketeers back on the job--and you at their side--the Republic couldn't be in better hands. We're counting on you, %!
        NICOLAUS_AND_FIVE_MOONS_HAVE_ALREADY_LEFT_FOR                         = 13505,  -- Nicolaus and Five Moons have already left for Beadeaux. Weren't you going to join them?
        YOUR_COMRADES_JUST_LEFT_FOR_THE_ELDIEME_NECROPOLIS                    = 13506,  -- Your comrades just left for the Eldieme Necropolis. Said they had urgent business with Captain Herbert?
        NICOLAUS_SAID_HE_AND_FIVE_MOONS_WERE_HEADED                           = 13507,  -- Nicolaus said he and Five Moons were headed for Beaucedine! What errand calls them to such a dangerous place?
        WHAT_YOU_RE_GOING_TOO_TAKE_CARE_OF                                    = 13508,  -- What? You're going too!? Take care of yourself, %. The monsters prowling that Goddess-forsaken glacier are something fierce!
        HOW_CAN_YOU_JUST_STROLL_AROUND_HERE_WHILE                             = 13509,  -- How can you just stroll around here while Zeid rots away in Benedikt Watchtower? Have a heart, %!
        THE_PRESIDENT_NO_THE_WHOLE_REPUBLIC_IS_COUNTING                       = 13510,  -- The President--no, the whole Republic--is counting on you, %. You must make for Xarcabard!
        WHAT_YOU_VE_LOST_YOUR_I_D_EXPECTED                                    = 13511,  -- What!? You've lost your %? I'd expected better of you, %!
        IF_IT_WERE_ME_SURE_I_M_DROPPING                                       = 13512,  -- If it were me, sure, I'm dropping and fumbling things all the time--why do you think I'm still a doorman after all these years?--but you... Anyway, here's a spare copy for you. Try to hold on to this one!
        WE_MAY_HAVE_DRIVEN_THE_BEASTMEN_BACK_BUT                              = 13513,  -- We may have driven the beastmen back, but their advance will not be stayed so easily. Stay wary, %!
        OH_THERE_YOU_ARE_VOLKER_S_BEEN_LOOKING                                = 13514,  -- Oh, there you are, %! Volker's been looking all over for you.
        SAYS_HE_S_GOT_AN_URGENT_MATTER_BOUT                                   = 13515,  -- Says he's got an urgent matter 'bout Captain Klara to discuss. I'm not privy to the details, but you'd best head inside straight away.
        AH_YOU_VE_COME_EXCELLENT                                              = 13516,  -- Ah, %, you've come. Excellent.
        I_OWE_YOU_A_DEBT_OF_GRATITUDE_FOR                                     = 13517,  -- I owe you a debt of gratitude for your service the other day. Thanks in no small part to your efforts, our forces have gained the upper hand in Xarcabard.
        AS_FOR_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_WE_LL_BE                                = 13518,  -- As for the Mythril Musketeers, we'll be taking advantage of this situation to redouble our efforts in pursuit of Captain Klara. Nicolaus, if you would.
        AHEM_YES_FIRST_LET_US_REVIEW_WHAT_WE                                  = 13519,  -- Ahem, yes. First, let us review what we've gleaned so far.
        IT_IS_CLEAR_BEYOND_A_SHADOW_OF_A                                      = 13520,  -- It is clear beyond a shadow of a doubt that our erstwhile leader--or whatever is posing as her--is in league with the Confederate in some capacity.
        THEREFORE_IT_STANDS_TO_REASON_THAT_SHE_HAS                            = 13521,  -- Therefore, it stands to reason that she has ensconced herself deep in the stronghold of our foe. Yes...in Castle Zvahl.
        THE_ALLIED_FORCES_WILL_BE_MOUNTING_A_SIEGE                            = 13522,  -- The Allied Forces will be mounting a siege effort on the castle, and we'll be moving out to join them. This should afford us the perfect opportunity to track down the Captain.
        ALLOW_ME_TO_BE_BLUNT_OUR_MISSION_WILL                                 = 13523,  -- Allow me to be blunt, %. Our mission will take us to the very heart of enemy territory--right under the Shadow Lord's twisted nose.
        THERE_IS_NO_GUARANTEE_THAT_WE_WILL_ESCAPE                             = 13524,  -- There is no guarantee that we will escape with our lives. And yet, we would have no other fight at our side. Will you stand with us?
        WILL_YOU_STAND_WITH_US_UNTIL_THE_END                                  = 13525,  -- Will you stand with us? Until the end. I am sorry...
        THE_FATE_OF_THE_REPUBLIC_IS_AT_STAKE                                  = 13526,  -- The fate of the Republic is at stake, %. I beg you to reconsider.
        THANK_YOU_EVER_THE_STALWART_ALLY_YOU_ARE                              = 13527,  -- Thank you, %. Ever the stalwart ally, you are.
        IF_WE_ARE_SETTLED_THEN_LET_US_BE                                      = 13528,  -- If we are settled, then let us be off. Action, not talk, will win the day.
        A_MOMENT_IF_YOU_WOULD                                                 = 13529,  -- %. A moment, if you would.
        I_WILL_SPEAK_FRANKLY_WITH_YOU_MY_CONSCIENCE                           = 13530,  -- I will speak frankly with you: my conscience does not sit well about being forced to work together with Zeid. The man we once called comrade has been revealed to be naught more than a cold-blooded murderer.
        WERE_IT_NOT_A_DIRECT_ORDER_FROM_THE                                   = 13531,  -- Were it not a direct order from the President, I would have excused myself from this mission. Mark my words--as soon as we are finished, I will not so much as look that man in the eye again for as long as I live.
        SIGH_NICOLAUS                                                         = 13532,  -- <Sigh>... Nicolaus...
        IN_ANY_EVENT_STANDING_AROUND_HERE_CHATTING_WILL                       = 13533,  -- In any event, standing around here chatting will get us no closer to any answers. We must make for Castle Zvahl.
        SEE_TO_YOUR_PREPARATIONS_AND_JOIN_US_AS                               = 13534,  -- See to your preparations and join us as soon as you are ready. I need not remind you that time is of the essence.
        THE_TRUTH_WILL_NOT_ELUDE_OUR_GRASP_THIS                               = 13535,  -- The truth will not elude our grasp this time.
        YOU_RE_STILL_HERE_ZEID_AND_THE_OTHERS                                 = 13536,  -- You're still here, %? Zeid and the others have already left for Castle Zvahl.
        IF_ONLY_I_COULD_JOIN_YOU_WHY_I                                        = 13537,  -- If only I could join you! Why, I'd have that Shadow Lord crying for mercy before he could so much as raise that twisted, towering blade of his...sharp enough to, uh...cleave a full-grown Galka c-clean in... Er, ah...on second thought, never mind that. Safe travels!
        WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_MAKING_HIS_HER                                       = 13538,  -- Well! If it isn't % making his/her] triumphant return!
        I_VE_ALREADY_HEARD_HOW_YOU_MANAGED_TO                                 = 13539,  -- I've already heard how you managed to save Captain Klara from the foul clutches of darkness. Spectacularly done, %!
        ZEID_AND_THE_OTHERS_WHY_THEY_RE_WITH                                  = 13540,  -- Zeid and the others? Why, they're with the President--as you should be! He's returned from the field especially for this occasion!
        MY_FRIENDS_I_AM_PLEASED_TO_SEE_YOUR                                   = 13541,  -- My friends. I am pleased to see your safe return.
        NEVER_WOULD_I_HAVE_SUSPECTED_THAT_CAPTAIN_KLARA                       = 13542,  -- Never would I have suspected that Captain Klara was possessed by one of those foul creatures...
        AND_YET_REFLECTING_BACK_ON_THE_PAST_MONTHS                            = 13543,  -- And yet, reflecting back on the past months, it explains much.
        IN_MY_IGNORANCE_I_THOUGHT_IT_MERELY_THE                               = 13544,  -- In my ignorance, I thought it merely the travails of war that weighed on her mind. To think that she was waging an even fiercer battle all this time. A battle for her very soul...
        THE_KNOWLEDGE_THAT_SHE_MAY_LOSE_HERSELF_COMPLETELY                    = 13545,  -- The knowledge that she may lose herself completely, that at any moment she might turn her blade against her beloved comrades... It must have been harrowing, indeed.
        THIS_I_KNOW_KLARA_IS_FORTUNATE_INDEED_TO                              = 13546,  -- This I know: Klara is fortunate indeed to have friends such as you. Were it not for your efforts, there is little doubt we would have lost her long ago.
        ON_BEHALF_OF_THE_ENTIRE_REPUBLIC_YOU_HAVE                             = 13547,  -- On behalf of the entire republic, you have my gratitude.
        AND_YET_OUR_BATTLE_IS_FAR_FROM_OVER                                   = 13548,  -- And yet, our battle is far from over.
        THE_LATEST_REPORT_HAS_JUST_COME_IN_FROM                               = 13549,  -- The latest report has just come in from the front lines. Thanks to the efforts of the Allied infiltration unit, we've finally secured a direct line of attack against the enemy stronghold.
        THE_ALLIED_FORCES_WILL_MOVE_AGAINST_CASTLE_ZVAHL                      = 13550,  -- The Allied Forces will move against Castle Zvahl with the full brunt of its strength. I will personally lead the Republican Army in support of this offensive.
        I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_MARCH_WITH_ME_UNDER                                  = 13551,  -- I would have you march with me. Under normal circumstances, you'd have earned yourselves a rest for your efforts, but I'm afraid that is a luxury we cannot afford.
        MISTER_PRESIDENT_DOES_THIS_MEAN                                       = 13552,  -- Mister President...does this mean--?
        BY_PRESIDENTIAL_DECREE_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_ARE_HEREBY              = 13553,  -- By presidential decree, the Mythril Musketeers are hereby reinstated in full.
        ZEID_UNTIL_SUCH_TIME_AS_CAPTAIN_KLARA_IS                              = 13554,  -- Zeid. Until such time as Captain Klara is fit to return to duty, I would have you serve as acting captain in her stead.
        CLEARLY_THE_BONDS_YOU_SHARE_ARE_AS_STRONG                             = 13555,  -- Clearly, the bonds you share are as strong--nay, stronger--than the metal from which you take your name. Let these bonds of friendship be your strength, and even the darkest shadow will prove no match for you.
        YES_SIR                                                               = 13556,  -- Yes, sir!
        AND_YOU                                                               = 13557,  -- And you, %...
        YOU_HAIL_FROM_A_DISTANT_REALM_THIS_I                                  = 13558,  -- You hail from a distant realm, this I know. Despite this, you have made one sacrifice after the next in our Republic's name.
        IT_WOULD_BE_NO_EXAGGERATION_TO_SAY_THAT                               = 13559,  -- It would be no exaggeration to say that without your unflagging efforts, Bastok would not stand as strong as it does today.
        AS_A_TOKEN_OF_MY_GRATITUDE_I_GIVE                                     = 13560,  -- As a token of my gratitude, I give you this.
        FURTHERMORE_FROM_THIS_DAY_FORWARD_YOU_SHALL_BE                        = 13561,  -- Furthermore, from this day forward you shall be a full-fledged member of the Mythril Musketeers. The Republic would have your strength for as long as it stands.
        THREE_CHEERS_FOR_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER                                    = 13562,  -- Three cheers for Mythril Musketeer %!
        THEY_TELL_ME_OUR_GUARDSMAN_GENTLE_TIGER_HAS                           = 13563,  -- They tell me our guardsman Gentle Tiger has dubbed you the Sixth Musketeer. I will do him one better: I hereby bestow upon you the designation of Mythril Musketeer Zero.
        A_WAYFARER_FROM_FAR_OFF_LANDS_YOU_ARE                                 = 13564,  -- A wayfarer from far-off lands you are, and yet serve our nation as loyally as any true Bastoker ever has. Never lose sight of your origins, for it is your unique background that allows you to serve us as no other can.
        ONCE_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_FOREVER_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER                  = 13565,  -- Once a Mythril Musketeer, forever a Mythril Musketeer. The Republic is stronger for your presence, %. Promise us that it will always be so.
        SIMPLY_INCREDIBLE_WHY_THE_ZERO_DESIGNATION_IS_AN                      = 13566,  -- Simply incredible... Why, the zero designation is an honor that's been granted to only the most illustrious musketeers in the history of our unit.
        I_MUST_CONFESS_TO_FEELING_A_BIT_OF                                    = 13567,  -- I must confess to feeling a bit of jealousy, %. But just you wait: I fully expect to distinguish myself in the none-too-distant future!
        IT_HAS_BEEN_AND_ALWAYS_WILL_BE_AN                                     = 13568,  -- %. It has been--and always will be--an honor to fight by your side.
        WITH_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_BACK_IN_ACTION_THE                        = 13569,  -- With the Mythril Musketeers back in action, the Republic truly has nothing to fear!
        I_WAS_HOLDIN_OUT_THAT_MY_EFFORTS_MIGHT                                = 13570,  -- I was holdin' out that my efforts might've warranted a decoration from the President as well. Hey, keepin' this door here safe from the beastman onslaught isn't easy, you know! Ah, well. There's always next time.
        YOU_THERE_HAVE_YOU_HAPPENED_TO_COME_INTO                              = 13571,  -- You, there. Have you happened to come into possession of any sealed containers in your crossings with the beastmen?
        SOME_OF_OUR_BRAVEST_SOLDIERS_HAVE_RECENTLY_BEEN                       = 13572,  -- Some of our bravest soldiers have recently been bringing back a number of such containers following successful invasions of beastman strongholds. Our hope was that within they would contain some sensitive intel we could exploit. Only, upon returning, all those who came in contact with these containers began to die off inexplicably, one after the other.
        AT_PRESENT_THE_ALLIED_FORCES_ARE_TREATING_THESE                       = 13573,  -- At present, the Allied Forces are treating these as cases of assassination by the Beastman Confederate elite. It would seem they are willing to go to any length to prevent the contents of these containers from being made known.
        SHOULD_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_GET_YOUR_HANDS_ON                                = 13574,  -- Should you happen to get your hands on any such container, it is imperative that you bring it back here with all haste and turn it in to an agent.
        JUST_AS_WE_SUSPECTED_THIS_CONTAINS_A_GREAT                            = 13575,  -- Just as we suspected. This contains a great deal of information that will prove vital to our cause. Hm, what's this? Not sure what to make of this... Doesn't seem to be terribly important. Here, why don't you hang onto it? See if you can't get some use out of it down the road.
        JUST_AS_WE_SUSPECTED_THIS_CONTAINS_A_GREAT_2                          = 13576,  -- Just as we suspected. This contains a great deal of information that will prove vital to our cause. I'll keep it here under strict supervision while we investigate its contents. Job well done, soldier.
        THE_S                                                                 = 13577,  -- The [Royal Army of San d'Oria/Republican Army of Bastok/Federal Forces of Windurst]'s [funds have increased/resources have increased/supplies have increased/reconnaissance has improved/skill has risen/production has risen/morale has risen/prosperity has risen]!
        MY_DEAR_COUNT_BOREL_IT_IS_GOOD_TO                                     = 13578,  -- My dear Count Borel, it is good to see you again!
        WE_HAD_RECEIVED_WORD_THAT_YOU_WOULD_BE                                = 13579,  -- We had received word that you would be coming.
        GOOD_TO_SEE_YOU_ALSO_RADFORD_MY_APOLOGIES                             = 13580,  -- Good to see you also, Radford. My apologies for the late notice. And pray excuse my brashness, but time is of the essence. How soon may we present ourselves to His Excellency?
        WORD_OF_YOUR_ARRIVAL_HAS_ALREADY_REACHED_THE                          = 13581,  -- Word of your arrival has already reached the president's ears. This way, please.
        WELCOME_TO_OUR_FAIR_REPUBLIC                                          = 13582,  -- Welcome to our fair republic.
        IT_IS_MY_UNDERSTANDING_THAT_YOU_BRING_A                               = 13583,  -- It is my understanding that you bring a matter of grave importance to this discussion table. I hope you don't mind my legati taking part.
        NO_NOT_AT_ALL_YOUR_EXCELLENCY_NOW_IF                                  = 13584,  -- No, not at all, Your Excellency. Now, if you'll allow me to explain the events which have led to this sudden visit...
        JEUNO_IS_TO_SURRENDER                                                 = 13585,  -- ...Jeuno is to surrender?
        THAT_THE_VERY_ARCHITECT_OF_THE_ALLIANCE_COULD                         = 13586,  -- That the very architect of the alliance could have had such a drastic change of heart is inconceivable...
        ON_DELIVERING_THE_NEWS_TO_KING_DESTIN_SIR                             = 13587,  -- On delivering the news to King Destin, Sir Nag'molada appended that the three nations, too, should make ready for unconditional surrender. Throwing down our swords, however, is the last thing on the mind of San d'Orians.
        AS_IT_IS_OURS                                                         = 13588,  -- As it is ours.
        A_JEUNOAN_SURRENDER_WOULD_HAVE_A_CALAMITOUS_EFFECT                    = 13589,  -- A Jeunoan surrender would have a calamitous effect on the war, and must be avoided no matter the cost. To this end, San d'Oria will dispatch a contingent of knights to aid in the Duchy's defense. And now, the Kingdom humbly asks that our ally, Bastok, too, lends soldiers to this most worthy of causes.
        WHAT_SAY_YOU_ALL                                                      = 13590,  -- What say you all?
        AS_MUCH_AS_WE_D_LIKE_TO_RUSH                                          = 13591,  -- As much as we'd like to rush to Jeuno's aid, to put it bluntly, we haven't the capacity to do so. We've incurred heavy losses over the course of this accursed war. Any further dints to our rank, and we'd have no choice but to consider conscripting civilians.
        I_MUST_CONCUR_IN_OUR_CURRENT_STATE_SENDING                            = 13592,  -- I must concur. In our current state, sending away even a small contingent of soldiers would be tantamount to cutting off our own sword arms on the eve of battle.
        BUT_BUT                                                               = 13593,  -- But, but...
        THE_FOURTH_DIVISION_TOO_SUFFERS_FROM_A_SEVERE                         = 13594,  -- The Fourth Division, too, suffers from a severe shortage of hands. Countless Republican soldiers--good men and women--were felled at the Battle of Grauberg. Grave though the situation in Jeuno may be, I fear we have no soldiers to spare. However...
        IT_PAINS_ME_TO_HAVE_TO_SAY_THIS                                       = 13595,  -- It pains me to have to say this, Count Borel. But given the circumstances, Bastok cannot answer the call.
        WE_ASK_FOR_YOUR_UNDERSTANDING_IN_BETTER_TIMES                         = 13596,  -- We ask for your understanding. In better times, such a discussion would not even have been necessary.
        FOURTH_DIVISION_SEVENTH_COHORS_PRAEFECTUS_ZAZARG_REPORTING            = 13597,  -- Fourth Division, Seventh Cohors Praefectus, Zazarg, reporting!
        ZAZARG_WHAT_IS_THE_MEANING_OF_THIS_INTRUSION                          = 13598,  -- Zazarg, what is the meaning of this intrusion?
        MY_APOLOGIES_AS_THE_HEAD_OF_THE_FOURTH                                = 13599,  -- My apologies. As the head of the Fourth Division, it was I who called upon the praefectus.
        YES_AND_MY_APOLOGIES_FOR_GATECRASHING_THIS_LITTLE                     = 13600,  -- Yes, and my apologies for gatecrashing this little party, and eavesdropping and whatnot...
        BUT_ENOUGH_BEATING_AROUND_THE_BUSH_AHEM_MISTER                        = 13601,  -- But, enough beating around the bush. Ahem! Mister President, sir! Requesting permission to lead the Seventh Cohors in Jeuno's defense, sir!
        ID_13602                                                              = 13602,  -- ...
        YOU_DON_T_NEED_TO_WORRY_ABOUT_MANPOWER                                = 13603,  -- You don't need to worry about manpower, if that's what's on your mind. As of late, my unit's received a generous injection of young blood raring to prove themselves on the battlefield.
        YOU_RE_JOKING_SURELY_THE_SEVENTH_COHORS_ARE                           = 13604,  -- You're joking, surely? The Seventh Cohors are more akin to a basket of rotten eggs than a military unit. What can a bunch of untried social misfits hope to achieve?
        GAHAHAHAHA_LEGATUS_BERGER_IF_YOU_DON_T_MIND                           = 13605,  -- Gahahahaha! Legatus Berger, if you don't mind sparing a bit of your precious time, it'd be my pleasure to give you an inspection tour of the Seventh Cohors.
        SEE_THE_LADS_AND_LASSES_WITH_YOUR_OWN                                 = 13606,  -- See the lads and lasses with your own eyes, and even you will be compelled to retract your rotten eggs comment. And that comes with the Zazarg guarantee!
        IT_S_QUITE_THE_MYSTERY_BUT_ALL_WHO                                    = 13607,  -- It's quite the mystery, but all who join the Seventh Cohors--even the disagreeable types abandoned by society as lost causes--undergo a transformation and are reborn as disciplined soldiers.
        THEY_SURE_ARE_WITH_OVER_THERE_BEING_ONE                               = 13608,  -- They sure are, with % over there being one of my more notable achievements. Who'd believe that the fine soldier standing before you now used to be a foul-mouthed hellraiser?
        THE_YOUNG_UNS_IN_MY_UNIT_ARE_EAGER                                    = 13609,  -- The young'uns in my unit are eager and prepared to suit up at a moment's notice. All they need is for me to give the word.
        AND_AS_AN_ADDED_CONVENIENCE_IT_APPEARS_THAT                           = 13610,  -- And as an added convenience, it appears that a sizeable chunk of the beastman force camping out about Jeuno is made up of Quadav--our specialty!
        UNLIKE_US_THOUGH_THE_FOLKS_OVER_IN_JEUNO                              = 13611,  -- Unlike us, though, the folks over in Jeuno haven't had much experience dealing with the turtlemen and their thick shells. That's why they've been having it rough all this time.
        NOBODY_HERE_DISCOUNTS_THE_DUCHY_S_STRATEGIC_IMPORTANCE                = 13612,  -- Nobody here discounts the Duchy's strategic importance, that much we've established. If she were to fall to the beastmen, it'd only be a matter of time before the three nations follow suit.
        LET_US_GO_AND_LEND_A_HAND_TO                                          = 13613,  -- Let us go and lend a hand to our Jeunoan brothers and sisters, I say!
        I_BEG_YOU_TO_CONSIDER_MISTER_PRESIDENT_ROUGH                          = 13614,  -- I beg you to consider, Mister President. Rough-mannered as Zazarg is, I can attest to his leadership and prowess on the battlefield.
        GAHAHAHAHA                                                            = 13615,  -- Gahahahaha!
        VERY_WELL_PRAEFECTUS_ZAZARG_HAVE_YOUR_UNIT_MOBILIZED                  = 13616,  -- Very well... Praefectus Zazarg, have your unit mobilized. I leave the matter in your hands.
        NOW_WE_RE_TALKING_THANK_YOU_SIR_MISTER                                = 13617,  -- Now we're talking! Thank you, sir, Mister President, sir!
        THE_SEVENTH_COHORS_WILL_STRIKE_OUT_FOR_JEUNO                          = 13618,  -- The Seventh Cohors will strike out for Jeuno without delay.
        TH_THANK_YOU_SIR                                                      = 13619,  -- Th-thank you, sir!
        GAHAHAHA_NOW_NOW_LIL_MISSY_I_HAVEN_T                                  = 13620,  -- Gahahaha! Now, now, lil' missy. I haven't done anything deserving of such an enthusiastic display of gratitude.
        THERE_S_NOTHING_SPECIAL_ABOUT_HELPING_OUT_FRIENDS                     = 13621,  -- There's nothing special about helping out friends in need. And nationality sure as hell's got nothing to do with it, either. Am I right?
        YES_SIR_2                                                             = 13622,  -- Yes, sir!
        WHAT_IS_IT_I_M_BURIED_UP_TO                                           = 13623,  -- What is it? I'm buried up to my ears in duties right now. It'll have to wait.
        DURING_WARTIME_NATIONS_TEND_TO_BECOME_FIXATED_ONLY                    = 13624,  -- During wartime, nations tend to become fixated only on the happenings within their borders, blinding themselves to the bigger picture. We hope your mission to recruit Windurst's aid will be fruitful.
        WE_WISH_THE_SEVENTH_COHORS_EVERY_SUCCESS_ON                           = 13625,  -- We wish the Seventh Cohors every success on their mission. Perhaps we should strap some explosives onto Zazarg, as a precautionary measure.
        WITH_SUPPLIES_RUNNING_DANGEROUSLY_LOW_AND_FEWER_AND                   = 13626,  -- With supplies running dangerously low and fewer and fewer soldiers returning from the battlefield each day, the situation is indeed grim. It would seem that shortages are the only things we have in abundance...
        LOOKING_FOR_A_HALF_ELVAAN_HALF_HUME_LASS                              = 13627,  -- Looking for a half-Elvaan, half-Hume lass with a shock of red hair, eh? Sorry, but I've seen no one around here fitting that description.
        MY_RECORDS_SHOW_THAT_THE_MAN_WOMAN_YOU                                = 13628,  -- My records show that the man/woman] you mention--%--is indeed an active member of the Seventh Cohors.
        FURNISH_ME_WITH_A_LETTER_OF_INTRODUCTION_SIGNED                       = 13629,  -- Furnish me with a letter of introduction signed in his/her] name, and we'll get you started on the aptitude test.
        YOU_NEED_A_SIGNED_LETTER_FROM_Y_YOU                                   = 13630,  -- You need a signed letter from %? Y-you see, I've reasons to keep my induction a secret from him/her]...
        SORRY_BUT_YOUR_PERSONAL_CIRCUMSTANCES_ARE_NONE_OF                     = 13631,  -- Sorry, but your personal circumstances are none of my concern. If you can't provide the requested documentation, I'll have to see you off.
        AWWW                                                                  = 13632,  -- Awww...
        GAHAHAHA_AND_WHAT_BRINGS_YOU_HERE_LIL_LADY                            = 13633,  -- Gahahaha! And what brings you here, lil' lady? Got a mind to join my jovial band of misfits, eh? Be all you can be?
        IT_JUST_SO_HAPPENS_THAT_I_VE_GOT                                      = 13634,  -- It just so happens that I've got this one task that wants for doin'.
        ONE_OF_OUR_MEN_GEBHARDT_S_HIS_NAME                                    = 13635,  -- One of our men--Gebhardt's his name--is posted out in North Gustaberg, at a watchtower named Eduard. Silly name, I know. The deal is, we need supplies delivered there. Would you be up for it?
        B_BUT_SIR_THAT_THAT_S_THE_APTITUDE                                    = 13636,  -- B-but, sir! That...that's the aptitude test!
        I_THINK_I_CAN_REMEMBER_MY_OWN_TEST                                    = 13637,  -- I think I can remember my own test, soldier. And so what if we let her have a shot? It's no skin off our noses. We can worry about trivial details later.
        OFF_YOU_GO_WITH_THESE_HERE_SUPPLIES_LIL                               = 13638,  -- Off you go with these here supplies, lil' lady. We're countin' on you!
        TH_THANK_YOU_FOR_THE_OPPORTUNITY_SIR_I                                = 13639,  -- Th-thank you for the opportunity, sir! I promise to be equal to the task!
        HM_2                                                                  = 13640,  -- Hm?
        LIKE_I_SAID_HAVEN_T_SEEN_HER_LIKE                                     = 13641,  -- Like I said, haven't seen her like around here. If she ever comes by, though, I'll be sure to let you know.
        IF_SHE_EVER_COMES_BY_THOUGH_I_LL                                      = 13642,  -- If she ever comes by, though, I'll be sure to let you know.
        GAHAHAHA_SO_THAT_WAS_YOU_DANCIN_CIRCLES_AROUND                        = 13643,  -- Gahahaha! So that was you dancin' circles around them Orcs back in the bowels of Jeuno! This certainly puts things into perspective.
        HEHEHE_IT_S_VERY_KIND_OF_YOU_TO                                       = 13644,  -- Hehehe. It's very kind of you to remember, sir.
        EVEN_A_FOOL_COULD_SEE_YOU_VE_GOT                                      = 13645,  -- Even a fool could see you've got both spirit and skill aplenty. You'd be a valuable addition to the Seventh Cohors, I've no doubt.
        GASP                                                                  = 13646,  -- <Gasp>!
        BUT_I_M_AFRAID_I_CAN_T_GRANT                                          = 13647,  -- ...But I'm afraid I can't grant your wish.
        WH_WHAT_BUT_WHY                                                       = 13648,  -- Wh-what? But...why?
        YOU_HAVEN_T_SO_MUCH_AS_SAID_IT                                        = 13649,  -- You haven't so much as said it, but your motivation for joinin' us is none other than to help %, correct?
        ID_13650                                                              = 13650,  -- !!!
        GAHAHAHAHA_HIT_THE_NAIL_SMACK_BANG_ON_THE                             = 13651,  -- Gahahahaha! Hit the nail smack-bang on the head, did I? You and % are close, like brother and sister/sisters]. I did see you two in action back at the Duchy, after all.
        BUT_TAKE_MY_ADVICE_IF_YOU_RE_TRULY                                    = 13652,  -- But take my advice. If you're truly of a mind to help %, don't just go blindly followin' his/her] footsteps. Keep to your own path, and work towards becomin' the person that only you can be. That's how you build the foundation for an unbeatable team.
        BEIN_HIS_HER_CLOSE_COMRADE_YOU_SHOULD_KNOW                            = 13653,  -- Bein' his/her] close comrade, you should know better than most that worries are wasted on %. You might've already heard, but your friend's been leavin' his/her] positive influence all over the Republic. Even the Mythril Musketeers--the president's right arm--hold him/her] in high esteem. That says a great deal, doesn't it?
        BEIN_HIS_HER_CLOSE_COMRADE_YOU_SHOULD_KNOW_2                          = 13654,  -- Bein' his/her] close comrade, you should know better than most that worries are wasted on %. In the short time he/she]'s been with the Seventh Cohors, %'s already shown tremendous potential.
        WHAT_S_MORE_I_VE_GOT_THIS_FEELIN                                      = 13655,  -- What's more, I've got this feelin'...
        THAT_DISTANCE_NO_MATTER_HOW_GREAT_CAN_NEVER                           = 13656,  -- That distance, no matter how great, can never keep the two of you apart for long.
        ID_13657                                                              = 13657,  -- ...!
        SO_BE_AT_EASE_AND_KEEP_WALKIN_YOUR                                    = 13658,  -- So be at ease and keep walkin' your own path, lil' lady. %'s in good hands here, and that's a promise.
        THANK_YOU_SIR                                                         = 13659,  -- Thank you, sir!
        SEARCHIN_FOR_SOMEONE_EH_RED_HAIR_LONG_EARS                            = 13660,  -- Searchin' for someone, eh? Red hair, long ears, sassy...
        HMMM_SOUNDS_MIGHTY_FAMILIAR_BUT_I_CAN_T                               = 13661,  -- Hmmm... Sounds mighty familiar, but I can't for the life of me remember where from. Might've been a friend of a friend.
        LILISETTE_I_THANK_YOU_BOTH_FOR_YOUR_COOPERATION                       = 13662,  -- Lilisette, %, I thank you both for your cooperation.
        WITH_YOUR_INVALUABLE_ASSISTANCE_OUR_MISSION_TO_ENTREAT                = 13663,  -- With your invaluable assistance, our mission to entreat the aid of the two nations was a success.
        ALL_THAT_REMAINS_NOW_IS_TO_RELAY_WORD                                 = 13664,  -- All that remains now is to relay word to Jeuno and ensure that no acts of folly such as surrender take place.
        YES_MY_LORD                                                           = 13665,  -- Yes, my lord!
        I_FEAR_THIS_IS_WHERE_WE_MUST_PART                                     = 13666,  -- I fear this is where we must part. My duties require that I be at my king's side.
        TAKE_THIS_LETTER_AND_SEE_IT_SAFELY_TO                                 = 13667,  -- Take this letter and see it safely to the hands of Archduke Kam'lanaut.
        AFTER_YOU_HAVE_DONE_SO_BE_ON_STANDBY                                  = 13668,  -- After you have done so, be on standby to receive our knights upon their arrival.
        UNDERSTOOD_SIR                                                        = 13669,  -- Understood, sir!
        MAY_THE_GODDESS_KEEP_YOU                                              = 13670,  -- May the Goddess keep you...
        CAN_T_YOU_SEE_THAT_I_M_OCCUPIED                                       = 13671,  -- Can't you see that I'm occupied with my duties? I'm far too busy defending this realm from the forces of darkness to engage in idle chit-chat with ungrateful civilians like you. Now, begone!
        GREETINGS_YOUR_TIRELESS_EFFORTS_ON_BEHALF_OF_THE                      = 13672,  -- Greetings! Your tireless efforts on behalf of the Allied Forces are well known in these parts!
        WHAT_A_COINCIDENCE_THAT_YOU_STOPPED_BY_AS                             = 13673,  -- What a coincidence that you stopped by. As a matter of fact, I have an offer that might prove interesting for you.
        I_M_NOT_ALLOWED_TO_REVEAL_MY_SOURCES                                  = 13674,  -- I'm not allowed to reveal my sources, but let it suffice to say that a substantial treasure hoard has been unearthed!
        THE_AREA_IN_WHICH_THIS_TREASURE_WAS_FOUND                             = 13675,  -- The area in which this treasure was found was one recently annexed to our territory thanks in no small part to your valiant efforts, so I simply had to let you in on the news.
        THERE_IS_ONE_SMALL_CATCH_HOWEVER_WORD_HAS                             = 13676,  -- There is one small catch, however. Word has it that a frightening monster has staked out the surrounding environs as its lair, and laid claim to the riches within.
        ORDINARILY_A_RECLUSIVE_BEAST_IT_HAS_BEEN_SIGHTED                      = 13677,  -- Ordinarily a reclusive beast, it has been sighted only on the rarest of occasions. In an odd coincidence, each of the search parties that encountered it happened to be carrying a % at the time...
        CURIOUS_IS_IT_NOT_YET_AS_THE_RUMOR                                    = 13678,  -- Curious, is it not? Yet, as the rumor has spread, many brave souls are trying to get their hands on these %, in the hope that they might draw out and slay the beast, and dispossess it of its treasure.
        WHERE_CAN_YOU_GET_YOUR_HANDS_ON_ONE                                   = 13679,  -- Where can you get your hands on one, you ask? Ohoho... What would you say if I told you that I just happen to have one with me right here?
        I_PROCURED_IT_FROM_MY_SOURCES_JUST_FOR                                = 13680,  -- I procured it from my...sources, just for you! After all, you have as much claim to the riches as any of those would-be treasure hunters.
        MIND_YOU_THESE_AREN_T_EASY_TO_COME                                    = 13681,  -- Mind you, these aren't easy to come by. If we didn't swear allegiance to the same nation, I'd have to charge a fee of # Allied Notes, but...
        SEEING_AS_YOU_RE_SUCH_A_STAUNCH_ALLY                                  = 13682,  -- Seeing as you're such a staunch ally to our cause, I'd be willing to let it go for only #. Do we have a deal?
        DEAL_YOU_CURRENTLY_POSSESS_A_N_DEAL_NO                                = 13683,  -- Deal? (You currently possess # A.N.) Deal. No thanks.
        REALLY_PROCEED_WITH_THE_TRANSACTION_YES_ON_SECOND                     = 13684,  -- Really proceed with the transaction? Yes. On second thought...
        THAT_S_A_SHAME_WELL_IF_YOU_CHANGE                                     = 13685,  -- That's a shame. Well, if you change your mind, I suggest you come back quickly. Now that our forces occupy the area, there's no telling when the beast might move on to greener pastures...
        WONDERFUL_YOU_WON_T_REGRET_IT_WITH_THIS                               = 13686,  -- Wonderful! You won't regret it. With this, the treasure is as good as yours!
        I_M_AFRAID_YOU_HAVEN_T_ENOUGH_ALLIED                                  = 13687,  -- I'm afraid you haven't enough Allied Notes...
        I_D_APPRECIATE_IF_YOU_COULD_SHARE_THIS                                = 13688,  -- I'd appreciate if you could share this news with your comrades as well. A chance like this doesn't come every day, you know, and word has it there's more than enough treasure to go around.
        THE_MONSTER_LURKS_WITHIN_THE_REGION_RECENTLY_BROUGHT                  = 13689,  -- The monster lurks within the region recently brought under [San d'Orian/Bastokan/Windurstian] control. Make haste, and may the Goddess protect you!
        OH_IT_S_YOU_AGAIN_LET_ME_GUESS                                        = 13690,  -- Oh, it's you again! Let me guess. You've come back for the %. Am I right or am I right?
        HOW_ABOUT_IT_RIGHT_YOU_ARE_ACTUALLY_NO                                = 13691,  -- How about it? Right you are. Actually, no...
        YES_I_M_AFRAID_I_HAVE_NO_TIME                                         = 13692,  -- Yes? I'm afraid I have no time at the moment. Come back later, and we'll talk.
        GREETINGS_AND_WELL_MET_I_AM_A_VOIDWATCH                               = 13693,  -- Greetings and well met. I am a Voidwatch scientist charged with researching the potential uses of atmacite.
        THOSE_WHO_POSSESS_MAY_COME_TO_ME_TO                                   = 13694,  -- Those who possess % may come to me to have their hard-won atmacite infused. Stratum abyssite also falls within my domain, so present to me any whose properties you wish to have analyzed.
        AH_I_M_ALSO_AUTHORIZED_TO_TELEPORT_FOLK                               = 13695,  -- Ah, I'm also authorized to teleport folk to operation sites. Quite versatile, aren't I?
        I_BEG_OF_YOU_FRIEND_LEND_US_YOUR                                      = 13696,  -- I beg of you, friend. Lend us your stout sword arm in the fight to protect Vana'diel from the Voidwalker threat.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_HAVE                                 = 13697,  -- What will you do? Nothing for now. Have stratum abyssite examined. Request teleportation. Analyze atmacite. Ask about atmacite. Ask about atmacite enrichment.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_INFUSED                              = 13698,  -- What will you do? Nothing for now. Infused: % (lv.#) Infused: % (lv.#) Infused: % (lv.#) Purge atmacite. Infuse atmacite. Enrich atmacite.
        INFUSE_WHICH_ATMACITE_CRUOR_NONE_FOR_NOW_LV                           = 13699,  -- Infuse which atmacite? (Cruor: #) None for now. % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#) Previous page. Next page.
        INFUSING_THE_LV_REQUIRES_CRUOR                                        = 13700,  -- Infusing the % (lv.#) requires # cruor.
        INFUSE_LV_YES_NO                                                      = 13701,  -- Infuse % (lv.#)? Yes. No.
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_ENOUGH_CRUOR_3                                        = 13702,  -- You do not have enough cruor.
        WHICH_ATMACITE_NONE_FOR_NOW_LV_LV_LV                                  = 13703,  -- [Infuse/Purge] which atmacite? None for now. % (lv.#) % (lv.#) % (lv.#)
        PURGE_LV_YES_NO                                                       = 13704,  -- Purge % (lv.#)? Yes. No.
        EXPENDS_CRUOR_AND_IS_NOW_INFUSED_WITH_LV                              = 13705,  -- % expends # cruor and is now infused with % (lv.#)!
